pairs.source: 1	The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God;
pairs.target: 1 Itihleh sibungas Gah deꞌ paguh tentang Yesus Kristus, Onak Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 2	As it is written in the prophets, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.
pairs.target:
2 Gah deꞌ Paguh inoh mulai kodaꞌ deꞌ moꞌ nulis nabi Yesaya daang
buk-e noꞌuh-e,
“In Topaꞌ, ‘Ningaꞌ mey! Okuꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ pait Kuꞌ dioꞌ soꞌ
Muꞌu, saꞌ-e sidia olan saꞌan Muꞌu.’

pairs.source: 3	The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.
pairs.target:
3 Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ luꞌow-luꞌow-e sina deꞌ padang pasil, in-e, ‘Sidia
olan saꞌan Topaꞌ, nongon olan saꞌan-E.’ ”

pairs.source: 4	John did baptize in the wilderness, and preach the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins.
pairs.target:
4 Samah kodaꞌ deꞌ obuah nulis inoh, wat noh leh Yohanes Pembaptis
nog deꞌ padang pasil tanon tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ, “Togan olan deꞌ jaꞌat
nyeꞌ moꞌ baptis saꞌ Topaꞌ ngapun dosa muꞌ!” In Yohanes.

pairs.source: 5	And there went out unto him all the land of Judaea, and they of Jerusalem, and were all baptized of him in the river of Jordan, confessing their sins.
pairs.target:
5 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa soꞌ
propinsi Yudea duoh suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ loꞌo deꞌ kota Yerusalem odi ngojit oniꞌ
deꞌ tanon Yohanes, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ngakuꞌ suaꞌ dosa-e. Yohanes moꞌ
baptis odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ deꞌ sungi Yordan.

pairs.source: 6	And John was clothed with camel’s hair, and with a girdle of a skin about his loins; and he did eat locusts and wild honey;
pairs.target:
6 Yohanes pakai jubah bulun unta duoh soot kupuang kulit, yohmoꞌ
pinguman-e kadis duoh piꞌin bonyih.

pairs.source: 7	And preached, saying, There cometh one mightier than I after me, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose.
pairs.target:
7 Yohanes moꞌ magah tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ
bogoꞌ gah deꞌ in-e, “Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ lobih ayuh-E soꞌ okuꞌ, yaꞌ nog mokuaꞌ
okuꞌ. Nyuduk bukaꞌ tolin kasut-E tuang doiꞌ geh nyam kuꞌ patut.

pairs.source: 8	I indeed have baptized you with water: but he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost.
pairs.target:
8 Okuꞌ
baptis ingan pakai piꞌin, pak-e Iyoh yaꞌ baptis ingan pakai Iyang Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 9	And it came to pass in those days, that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized of John in Jordan.
pairs.target:
9 Takal inoh Yesus nog soꞌ kota Nazaret deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ propinsi Galilea,
Yohanes moꞌ baptis Iyoh daang Sungi Yordan.

pairs.source: 10	And straightway coming up out of the water, he saw the heavens opened, and the Spirit like a dove descending upon him:
pairs.target:
10 Takal Yesus moꞌ maꞌad soꞌ piꞌin keꞌ doyoh, Iyoh moꞌ ningaꞌ longit
tibukaꞌ, Iyang Topaꞌ moꞌ muun map deꞌ tun Yesus mun manuk asang mun-e.

pairs.source: 11	And there came a voice from heaven, [saying], Thou art my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.
pairs.target:
11 Yohmoꞌ ogiꞌ sina soꞌ longit deꞌ in-e, “Muꞌu leh Onak deꞌ ngibalaꞌ Kuꞌ, deꞌ
odaꞌ kila Kuꞌ munuas.”

pairs.source: 12	And immediately the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness.
pairs.target:
12 Takal moꞌ mokuaꞌ baptis, Iyang Topaꞌ moꞌ toban Yesus deꞌ padang
pasil.

pairs.source: 13	And he was there in the wilderness forty days, tempted of Satan; and was with the wild beasts; and the angels ministered unto him.
pairs.target:
13 Yesus moꞌ loꞌo danoꞌ pat puluꞌ onu, Laja Muat munua moꞌ suba-E.
Topat Yoh loꞌo inoh bogoꞌ binatang deꞌ ogiꞌ bisa-e duoh deꞌ gaus loꞌo danoꞌ,
malaikat-malaikat moꞌ nog tulung-E.

pairs.source: 14	Now after that John was put in prison, Jesus came into Galilee, preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God,
pairs.target: 14 Takal Yohanes Pembaptis moꞌ obuah takap, Yesus moꞌ odi keꞌ propinsi Galilea magah Gah deꞌ Paguh soꞌ Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 15	And saying, The time is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand: repent ye, and believe the gospel.
pairs.target:
15 Iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Moꞌ nog takal Topaꞌ moꞌ yaꞌ mulai militah jadin Laja.
Togan leh olan deꞌ jaꞌat nyeꞌ moꞌ bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Gah deꞌ paguh soꞌ Topaꞌ!”

pairs.source: 16	Now as he walked by the sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and Andrew his brother casting a net into the sea: for they were fishers.
pairs.target:
16 Takal Yesus ponu nunaꞌ bingon donu Galilea, Iyoh moꞌ ningaꞌ Simon
duoh madih-e Andreas ngijaling ikian, dop-e inoh leh kiloja odop-e deꞌ
duwoh.

pairs.source: 17	And Jesus said unto them, Come ye after me, and I will make you to become fishers of men.
pairs.target:
17 Yesus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Jaꞌ nunaꞌ Okuꞌ! Deꞌ dioꞌ
ingan kiloja kalik ikian, pak-e adin Okuꞌ ngajal odaꞌ ingan kalik manusia
saꞌ-a nunaꞌ Okuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 18	And straightway they forsook their nets, and followed him.
pairs.target:
18 Simon duoh Andreas lasuꞌ togan jaling-e yohmoꞌ odi
nunaꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 19	And when he had gone a little further thence, he saw James the [son] of Zebedee, and John his brother, who also were in the ship mending their nets.
pairs.target:
19 Iyoh moꞌ lanyut pimonu-e, Iyoh moꞌ ningaꞌ Yakobus duoh Yohanes.
Odop-e deꞌ duwoh onak Zebedeus. Odop-e deꞌ duwoh kiloja nopung jaling-e
daang olud.

pairs.source: 20	And straightway he called them: and they left their father Zebedee in the ship with the hired servants, and went after him.
pairs.target:
20 Yesus moꞌ mogan odop-e deꞌ duwoh, odop-e deꞌ duwoh lasuꞌ
togan samaꞌ-a duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ kiloja saꞌan-e daang olud, yohmoꞌ lasuꞌ nunaꞌ
Yesus.

pairs.source: 21	And they went into Capernaum; and straightway on the sabbath day he entered into the synagogue, and taught.
pairs.target:
21 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E nog kota Kapernaum. Takal-e moꞌ nog
onu simayang ulang Yahudi deꞌ nang nyaꞌa onu Sabat, Yesus molot kaang
topat simayang agama Yahudi yohmoꞌ mulai ngajal.

pairs.source: 22	And they were astonished at his doctrine: for he taught them as one that had authority, and not as the scribes.
pairs.target:
22 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa ilan
ningaꞌ wat Iyoh ngajal, dop-e oniꞌ deꞌ ngajal-E tok diꞌ nyaꞌa ponai yaꞌ
nyakal-e, idoh diꞌ-e kodaꞌ pingajal gulu-gulu agama Yahudi.

pairs.source: 23	And there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,
pairs.target:
23 Takal inoh ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ obuah bikalui muat munua, molot kaang
boli simayang agama ulang Yahudi, yohmoꞌ nang bogan-e,

pairs.source: 24	Saying, Let [us] alone; what have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of Nazareth? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of God.
pairs.target:
24 “Oi Yesus ulang Nazaret, oni nai Ingan kaso koꞌih? Podo Ingan yaꞌ
katuab koꞌih? Puꞌan kuꞌ osi Ingan, Ingan leh deꞌ kakuꞌ Topaꞌ, deꞌ pait
Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 25	And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him.
pairs.target:
25 Yesus moꞌ nang muat munua inoh, “Maꞌ bidaluag! Buu luah soꞌ nyaꞌa
itih!”

pairs.source: 26	And when the unclean spirit had torn him, and cried with a loud voice, he came out of him.
pairs.target:
26 Muat munua inoh moꞌ ulih-ulih guyang gusuak gonan nyaꞌa inoh,
muat munua nang bogan-e daang-e buu luah.

pairs.source: 27	And they were all amazed, insomuch that they questioned among themselves, saying, What thing is this? what new doctrine [is] this? for with authority commandeth he even the unclean spirits, and they do obey him.
pairs.target:
27 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa danoꞌ obuaꞌ
ilan-e, yohmoꞌ bisikian duoh dingan-e deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ, in-e, “Oni deꞌ wat
itih? Nyaꞌa itih ngajal pakai punuaꞌ kuasa. Iyoh sina tuduꞌ muat munua
odaꞌ buu luah, muat munua moꞌ lasuꞌ luah!”

pairs.source: 28	And immediately his fame spread abroad throughout all the region round about Galilee.
pairs.target: 28 Gah inoh moꞌ popah katiꞌ-kanih keꞌ suaꞌ propinsi Galilea.

pairs.source: 29	And forthwith, when they were come out of the synagogue, they entered into the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.
pairs.target:
29 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E buu soꞌ topat simayang
agama Yahudi inoh, yohmoꞌ odi keꞌ boli Simon duoh Andreas. Yakobus
duoh Yohanes suwaꞌ odi duoh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 30	But Simon’s wife’s mother lay sick of a fever, and anon they tell him of her.
pairs.target:
30 Takal-e molot kaang
boli, ogiꞌ nyaꞌa tanon tuduꞌ Yesus nang tua Simon deꞌ dayung monam
modud, yoh guling deꞌ topat boꞌos-e.

pairs.source: 31	And he came and took her by the hand, and lifted her up; and immediately the fever left her, and she ministered unto them.
pairs.target:
31 Yesus moꞌ odi sinok tua Simon inoh
yohmoꞌ kagong tongan-e tulung odaꞌ mokat, onam-e moꞌ lasuꞌ mokuaꞌ,
iyoh moꞌ mokat, yohmoꞌ nguliaꞌ pinguman saꞌan ayua odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 32	And at even, when the sun did set, they brought unto him all that were diseased, and them that were possessed with devils.
pairs.target:
32 Takal onu moꞌ yaꞌ ngalom, bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ toban ulang-ulang deꞌ
monam duoh deꞌ obuah bikalui muat munua nog tuduꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 33	And all the city was gathered together at the door.
pairs.target:
33 Nyaꞌa deꞌ
bogoꞌ moꞌ nog tikuluk deꞌ bolot tiban-e.

pairs.source: 34	And he healed many that were sick of divers diseases, and cast out many devils; and suffered not the devils to speak, because they knew him.
pairs.target:
34 Yesus moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ
deꞌ bipasia-pasia onam tiboꞌi-e mokuaꞌ duoh kasig muat munua soꞌ gonan
nyaꞌa, pak-e Yesus diꞌ-e odaꞌ muat munua sina, dop-e muat munua puꞌan
osi Yesus inoh.

pairs.source: 35	And in the morning, rising up a great while before day, he went out, and departed into a solitary place, and there prayed.
pairs.target:
35 Onu tiaꞌ pagi-e takal onu aluaꞌ bosow, Yesus moꞌ mokat boꞌos yohmoꞌ
odi keꞌ sopaꞌ kota deꞌ doiꞌ nyaꞌa daꞌ-e. Danoꞌ Yesus bidoa.

pairs.source: 36	And Simon and they that were with him followed after him.
pairs.target: 36 Simon duoh ayua dingan-e moꞌ odi kalik Yesus.

pairs.source: 37	And when they had found him, they said unto him, All [men] seek for thee.
pairs.target:
37 Takal odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ moꞌ tapod Yesus, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ in-e, “Suaꞌ nyaꞌa bolipotak
kalik Ingan.”

pairs.source: 38	And he said unto them, Let us go into the next towns, that I may preach there also: for therefore came I forth.
pairs.target:
38 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Jaꞌ otoꞌ odi keꞌ topat deꞌ bokon deꞌ
sinok-sinok soꞌ katiꞌ, saꞌ Okuꞌ tanon geh Gah deꞌ paguh soꞌ Topaꞌ danoꞌ.
Dop-e inoh leh ngan Okuꞌ nog.”

pairs.source: 39	And he preached in their synagogues throughout all Galilee, and cast out devils.
pairs.target:
39 Yesus ponu kodak suaꞌ propinsi Galilea, Yoh ngajal nyaꞌa Gah deꞌ
Paguh deꞌ topat-topat simayang agama Yahudi duoh kasig muat munua
soꞌ nyaꞌa.

pairs.source: 40	And there came a leper to him, beseeching him, and kneeling down to him, and saying unto him, If thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.
pairs.target:
40 Ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ obuah onam kulit deꞌ bijakit nog tuduꞌ
Yesus, yohmoꞌ bikunyug deꞌ sulung jowin Yesus. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh mitiaꞌ
masiꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus, yohmoꞌ in-e, “Simoꞌ Ingan laꞌan, Ingan tapod odaꞌ okuꞌ
mokuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 41	And Jesus, moved with compassion, put forth [his] hand, and touched him, and saith unto him, I will; be thou clean.
pairs.target:
41 Yesus moꞌ tok-tok masiꞌ tuduꞌ-e. Iyoh moꞌ tomaꞌ gonan nyaꞌa inoh
daang-e in-e, “Laꞌan Kuꞌ, mokuaꞌ leh!”

pairs.source: 42	And as soon as he had spoken, immediately the leprosy departed from him, and he was cleansed.
pairs.target:
42 Takal inoh geh onam kulit-e deꞌ
bijakit lasuꞌ musuap yohmoꞌ mokuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 43	And he straitly charged him, and forthwith sent him away;
pairs.target:
43 Yesus moꞌ odaꞌ iyoh buu duoh
ulih-ulih jaman-e, in-E,

pairs.source: 44	And saith unto him, See thou say nothing to any man: but go thy way, shew thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing those things which Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.
pairs.target:
44 “Maꞌ muꞌu tanon tuduꞌ osi sijaꞌ-a, pak-e odi leh
tuduꞌ pimipin agama Yahudi saꞌ-a pilisa muꞌu, tok mokuaꞌ ke doh keh muꞌu.
Mokuaꞌ inoh nyeꞌ simoliah binatang saꞌan Topaꞌ kodaꞌ deꞌ tanon Musa, deꞌ
jadin bukti tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ dop-e muꞌu moꞌ bonal-bonal mokuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 45	But he went out, and began to publish [it] much, and to blaze abroad the matter, insomuch that Jesus could no more openly enter into the city, but was without in desert places: and they came to him from every quarter.
pairs.target:
45 Pak-e nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ mokuaꞌ monam inoh odi katiꞌ kanih diꞌ-e
mokuaꞌ-mokuaꞌ silita tanon wat Yesus odaꞌ iyoh mokuaꞌ soꞌ onam kulit-e.
Yesus moꞌ diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ ponai molot bitanga odop-e daang kota. Iyoh moꞌ jok-e
loꞌo deꞌ sopaꞌ kota deꞌ doiꞌ nyaꞌa loꞌo daꞌ-a, pak-e nyaꞌa diꞌ-e obuaꞌ-obuaꞌ
nog soꞌ niꞌ-soꞌ niꞌ tuduꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 1	And again he entered into Capernaum, after [some] days; and it was noised that he was in the house.
pairs.target:
1 Kudu-kudu onu mokuaꞌ inoh, Yesus odi lagiꞌ keꞌ Kapernaum. Nyaꞌa
moꞌ ngojit gah nang Iyoh ogiꞌ deꞌ boli.

pairs.source: 2	And straightway many were gathered together, insomuch that there was no room to receive [them], no, not so much as about the door: and he preached the word unto them.
pairs.target:
2 Nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ nog
ngubun-E, mulai soꞌ bolot tiban nog aang boli punuaꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa. Yesus
moꞌ tanon Gah soꞌ Topaꞌ tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ inoh.

pairs.source: 3	And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy, which was borne of four.
pairs.target:
3 Takal-E aluaꞌ sina, nog pat naꞌan nyaꞌa tawiak niꞌ naꞌan dali deꞌ kobos
gonan-e, yoh toban tuduꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 4	And when they could not come nigh unto him for the press, they uncovered the roof where he was: and when they had broken [it] up, they let down the bed wherein the sick of the palsy lay.
pairs.target:
4 Saai nyaꞌa sikiya bogoꞌ, odop-e deꞌ pat
inoh diꞌ-e tapod molot bitapod duoh Yesus. Yoh moꞌ toban maꞌad keꞌ
bungan boli, yoh moꞌ nglibuang bungan totok Yesus mujuag. Yoh moꞌ
pimuun nyaꞌa deꞌ kobos gonan-e inoh deꞌ sulung jowin Yesus baya topat
guling-e.

pairs.source: 5	When Jesus saw their faith, he said unto the sick of the palsy, Son, thy sins be forgiven thee.
pairs.target:
5 Takal Yesus ningaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ sukup-sukup bisayaꞌ, Iyoh moꞌ
sina tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kobos gonan-e inoh, in-e, “Dosa-dosa muꞌ moꞌ obuah
ngapun.”

pairs.source: 6	But there were certain of the scribes sitting there, and reasoning in their hearts,
pairs.target:
6 Pak-e ogiꞌ kudu-kudu naꞌan gulu agama ulang Yahudi deꞌ guluꞌ danoꞌ
moꞌ in-e daang otin-e,

pairs.source: 7	Why doth this [man] thus speak blasphemies? who can forgive sins but God only?
pairs.target:
7 “Puus manah Yoh nyamah odop-E duoh Topaꞌ!
Jok-e Topaꞌ deꞌ tapod ngapun dosa nyaꞌa neh.”

pairs.source: 8	And immediately when Jesus perceived in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, he said unto them, Why reason ye these things in your hearts?
pairs.target:
8 Takal inoh geh Yesus lasuꞌ puꞌan daang otin-E, oni deꞌ pikil odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ, Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Oni nai ingan bipikil deꞌ in inoh daang otin
ingan?

pairs.source: 9	Whether is it easier to say to the sick of the palsy, [Thy] sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and take up thy bed, and walk?
pairs.target:
9 Ki deꞌ sonang dooꞌ, tanon tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kobos gonan-e inoh nang,
‘Dosamuꞌ moꞌ obuah ngapun’ keh, ‘Mokat, nyeꞌ moꞌ toban topat guling muꞌ
nyeꞌ moꞌ ponu’?

pairs.source: 10	But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (he saith to the sick of the palsy,)
pairs.target:
10 Pak-e saꞌ ingan puꞌan-e, daang dunia itih Onak Manusia
ogiꞌ kuasa-E ngapun dosa manusia.” Yoh moꞌ sina tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kobos  gonan-e inoh,

pairs.source: 11	I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy bed, and go thy way into thine house.
pairs.target:
11 “Mokat nyeꞌ moꞌ toban topat guling muꞌ, nyeꞌ moꞌ buu
motas!”

pairs.source: 12	And immediately he arose, took up the bed, and went forth before them all; insomuch that they were all amazed, and glorified God, saying, We never saw it on this fashion.
pairs.target:
12 Yoh moꞌ mokat daang-e lasuꞌ mit topat guling-e. Yohmoꞌ buu luah,
takal inoh geh nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ ningaꞌ iyoh. Yoh ngan-e suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ
ilan-e, yohmoꞌ mudi Topaꞌ daang-e in-e, “Mulan toꞌ ningaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ wat
itih!”

pairs.source: 13	And he went forth again by the sea side; and all the multitude resorted unto him, and he taught them.
pairs.target:
13 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus paliꞌ odi lagiꞌ keꞌ pang donu Galilea. Bogoꞌ nyaꞌa
nog tuduꞌ-E, Yoh moꞌ ngajal-e.

pairs.source: 14	And as he passed by, he saw Levi the [son] of Alphaeus sitting at the receipt of custom, and said unto him, Follow me. And he arose and followed him.
pairs.target:
14 Takal Yesus aluaꞌ ponu danoꞌ, Yoh ningaꞌ ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ
tukang nagih suke deꞌ adon Lewi onak Alfeus, guluꞌ deꞌ topat nyaꞌa bayal
suke saꞌan kerajaan Romawi. Yesus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ-e, “Jaꞌ nunaꞌ Okuꞌ!”
Lewi moꞌ mokat mujuag yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ nunaꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 15	And it came to pass, that, as Jesus sat at meat in his house, many publicans and sinners sat also together with Jesus and his disciples: for there were many, and they followed him.
pairs.target:
15 Takal Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E man deꞌ boli Lewi, bogoꞌ
ulang-ulang deꞌ tukang nagih suke duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ nang nyaꞌa ulang
bidosa suwaꞌ man samah-samah duoh ayua odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, dop-e bogoꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ nunaꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 16	And when the scribes and Pharisees saw him eat with publicans and sinners, they said unto his disciples, How is it that he eateth and drinketh with publicans and sinners?
pairs.target:
16 Ogiꞌ kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi ningaꞌ Yesus
suwaꞌ man duoh ulang-ulang pinagih suke duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ sobot nyaꞌa nang
ulang deꞌ bidosa inoh. Yoh moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus, “Oni
nai gulu muꞌ suwaꞌ man duoh tukang pinagih suke duoh ulang deꞌ bidosa
inoh?”

pairs.source: 17	When Jesus heard [it], he saith unto them, They that are whole have no need of the physician, but they that are sick: I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.
pairs.target:
17 Takal Yesus ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ nang odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, Yoh moꞌ nyawot-e,
“Nyaꞌa deꞌ sehat diꞌ-e pilelu doktol, jok-e nyaꞌa deꞌ monam. Idoh diꞌ kuꞌ
nog mogan nyaꞌa deꞌ bonal, pak-e okuꞌ nog mogan nyaꞌa deꞌ bidosa.”

pairs.source: 18	And the disciples of John and of the Pharisees used to fast: and they come and say unto him, Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast, but thy disciples fast not?
pairs.target:
18 Ogiꞌ onu-e takal pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yohanes Pembaptis duoh gulu-gulu
agama ulang Yahudi puasa. Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa nog tuduꞌ Yesus yohmo bisikian,
“Oni nai pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yohanes Pembaptis duoh gulu-gulu agama ulang
Yahudi puasa, pak-e pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Ingan diꞌ-e puasa?”

pairs.source: 19	And Jesus said unto them, Can the children of the bridechamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them? as long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.
pairs.target:
19 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e pakai nang silita, “Moꞌ nyaꞌa biluman kawin,
podo tamu-tamu-e diꞌ-e man? Takal nyaꞌa deꞌ kawin aluaꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ, totu
nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ aluaꞌ man.

pairs.source: 20	But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.
pairs.target:
20 Pak-e ogiꞌ takal-e nyaꞌa toban nyaꞌa deꞌ kawin inoh toban buu. Takal
inoh leh diꞌ nyaꞌa tiyaꞌ man-nuak.

pairs.source: 21	No man also seweth a piece of new cloth on an old garment: else the new piece that filled it up taketh away from the old, and the rent is made worse.
pairs.target:
21 Doiꞌ-e ogiꞌ nyaꞌa nopung bojuh deꞌ oma pakai kain deꞌ baꞌuh. Dop-e
moꞌ-e kain topung deꞌ baꞌuh inoh bikinyot yoh moꞌ notak bojuh deꞌ moꞌ
oma, totak-e moꞌ bitamah ayuh.

pairs.source: 22	And no man putteth new wine into old bottles: else the new wine doth burst the bottles, and the wine is spilled, and the bottles will be marred: but new wine must be put into new bottles.
pairs.target:
22 Watnoh geh doiꞌ nyaꞌa ngisiꞌ piꞌin anggul deꞌ baꞌuh daang topat deꞌ
moꞌ oma, dop-e piꞌin anggul deꞌ baꞌuh muab, topat-e deꞌ oma inoh moꞌ
totak. Luban-e soꞌ duwoh-e tibuang. Totu leh piꞌin anggul deꞌ baꞌuh, nyaꞌa
naꞌ daang topat deꞌ baꞌuh geh!” In Yesus.

pairs.source: 23	And it came to pass, that he went through the corn fields on the sabbath day; and his disciples began, as they went, to pluck the ears of corn.
pairs.target:
23 Takal Onu Sabat, Yesus ponu duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E ngilusuꞌ umoh
gandum. Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ pilai, yohmoꞌ tuk kiluang gandum yoh moꞌ
man-e.

pairs.source: 24	And the Pharisees said unto him, Behold, why do they on the sabbath day that which is not lawful?
pairs.target:
24 Ulang Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi moꞌ sina tuduꞌ Yesus, “Ningaꞌ,
oni nai pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Ingan nai oniꞌ deꞌ diꞌ nyaꞌa soꞌon nai-e daang Onu
Sabat?”

pairs.source: 25	And he said unto them, Have ye never read what David did, when he had need, and was an hungred, he, and they that were with him?
pairs.target:
25 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Aluaꞌ doiꞌ keh ingan basa daang Kitab? Oni deꞌ
nai Daud noꞌuh-e? Takal iyoh duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-e pilai doiꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ
man-e.

pairs.source: 26	How he went into the house of God in the days of Abiathar the high priest, and did eat the shewbread, which is not lawful to eat but for the priests, and gave also to them which were with him?
pairs.target:
26 Takal Abyatar deꞌ jadin pimipin deꞌ paling ayuh-e, Daud molot
kaang topat nyaꞌa nyomah Topaꞌ. Yoh duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-e moꞌ man
kueh deꞌ ngin nyaꞌa tuduꞌ Topaꞌ, nunaꞌ atulan agama otoꞌ jok-e pimipin
agama Yahudi deꞌ soꞌon man kueh inoh.”

pairs.source: 27	And he said unto them, The sabbath was made for man, and not man for the sabbath:
pairs.target:
27 Yesus moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ, “Topaꞌ nai Onu Sabat saꞌan manusia, idoh diꞌ-e
manusia saꞌan onu Sabat.

pairs.source: 28	Therefore the Son of man is Lord also of the sabbath.
pairs.target:
28 Onak Manusia leh deꞌ notu oni deꞌ soꞌon duoh
oniꞌ deꞌ diꞌ-e soꞌon nyaꞌa nai-e daang Onu Sabat.”

pairs.source: 1	And he entered again into the synagogue; and there was a man there which had a withered hand.
pairs.target:
1 Yesus moꞌ paliꞌ odi lagiꞌ keꞌ topat simayang agama Yahudi. Danoꞌ ogiꞌ
niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ tongan-e kobos niꞌ kawa.

pairs.source: 2	And they watched him, whether he would heal him on the sabbath day; that they might accuse him.
pairs.target:
2 Danoꞌ ogiꞌ kudu-kudu
naꞌan ulang Yahudi deꞌ ningaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ nai Yesus, simoꞌ Yesus odaꞌ nyaꞌa
deꞌ tongan-e kobos niꞌ kawa inoh mokuaꞌ daang Onu Sabat, odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ tapod yaꞌ nyalah-E.

pairs.source: 3	And he saith unto the man which had the withered hand, Stand forth.
pairs.target:
3 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tongan-e kobos
niꞌ kawa inoh, “Got mokat mujuag katiꞌ, keꞌ sulung jowin koꞌih!”

pairs.source: 4	And he saith unto them, Is it lawful to do good on the sabbath days, or to do evil? to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.
pairs.target:
4 Yesus
 moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ, “Moꞌ-e nunaꞌ atulan agama otoꞌ, oni
deꞌ patut otoꞌ nai daang Onu Sabat? Nai oniꞌ deꞌ paguh keh, nai oniꞌ deꞌ
jaꞌat? Tulung nyaꞌa odaꞌ idip keh nyeꞌ ngabos-e?”
Pak-e odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ loꞌo jaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 5	And when he had looked round about on them with anger, being grieved for the hardness of their hearts, he saith unto the man, Stretch forth thine hand. And he stretched [it] out: and his hand was restored whole as the other.
pairs.target:
5 Yesus ningaꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ daang-e tiwas, duoh kila-E susah,
dop-e nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ obuaꞌ kolas otin-e. Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ
tongan-e kobos niꞌ kawa inoh, “Suual tongan muꞌ.” Nyaꞌa inoh moꞌ suual
tongan-e, yohmoꞌ lasuꞌ mokuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 6	And the Pharisees went forth, and straightway took counsel with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.
pairs.target:
6 Mokuaꞌ inoh ulang Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi buu soꞌ topat simayang
inoh, yoh moꞌ biloneng duoh ulang Yahudi deꞌ nuaꞌ Laja Herodes ngan-e
yaꞌ ngabos Yesus.

pairs.source: 7	But Jesus withdrew himself with his disciples to the sea: and a great multitude from Galilee followed him, and from Judaea,
pairs.target:
7 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ buu keꞌ pang Donu Galilea. Yohmoꞌ
bogoꞌ nyaꞌa soꞌ propinsi Galilea duoh soꞌ propinsi Yudea bitunaꞌ duoh-E.

pairs.source: 8	And from Jerusalem, and from Idumaea, and [from] beyond Jordan; and they about Tyre and Sidon, a great multitude, when they had heard what great things he did, came unto him.
pairs.target:
8 Ogiꞌ geh deꞌ soꞌ kota Yerusalem, soꞌ Idumea soꞌ polad Sungi Yordan, soꞌ
kota Tirus, duoh kota Sidon. Suaꞌ ayua deꞌ munoꞌ nog dop-e yoh moꞌ ngojit
suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ moꞌ nai Yesus.

pairs.source: 9	And he spake to his disciples, that a small ship should wait on him because of the multitude, lest they should throng him.
pairs.target:
9 Yesus moꞌ odaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E sidia olud
saꞌan odop-E, dop-e nyaꞌa sikiya bogoꞌ, saꞌ Yoh diꞌ-e pisiat odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ
bitodod-todod duoh Yoh.

pairs.source: 10	For he had healed many; insomuch that they pressed upon him for to touch him, as many as had plagues.
pairs.target:
10 Bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ mokuaꞌ odaꞌ-E, yoh ngan suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ monam
bitodod-todod ngan-e yaꞌ odi sinok Yesus, saꞌ-e tapod tomaꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 11	And unclean spirits, when they saw him, fell down before him, and cried, saying, Thou art the Son of God.
pairs.target:
11 Nyaꞌa deꞌ
molot muat munua daang gonan-e, takal-e ningaꞌ Yesus yoh moꞌ nyuduk
bikunyug deꞌ sulung jowin Yesus daang-e nang bogan-e, “Ingan Onak
Topaꞌ!”

pairs.source: 12	And he straitly charged them that they should not make him known.
pairs.target:
12 Pak-e Yesus isin-isin jaman muat munua inoh tanon nang Iyoh
Onak Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 13	And he goeth up into a mountain, and calleth [unto him] whom he would: and they came unto him.
pairs.target:
13 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus maꞌad keꞌ tun punguꞌ. Yesus moꞌ ngijaꞌ ulang-ulang deꞌ yaꞌ pilih-E, saꞌ-a odi tuduꞌ odop-E danoꞌ. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ odi
tuduꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 14	And he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach,
pairs.target:
14 Yesus moꞌ pilih simoong duwoh naꞌan soꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ. Iyoh moꞌ
sobot nang rasul-rasul-E. Yesus moꞌ in-e, “Okuꞌ pilih ingan, sa' ingan suwaꞌ
duoh Okuꞌ, saꞌ Kuꞌ pait ingan odaꞌ magah Gah deꞌ Paguh soꞌ Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 15	And to have power to heal sicknesses, and to cast out devils:
pairs.target:
15 Okuꞌ
yaꞌ ngin kuasa tuduꞌ ingan odaꞌ ponai kasig pibuu muat munua.”

pairs.source: 16	And Simon he surnamed Peter;
pairs.target:
16 Deꞌ mutiꞌ leh adon-adon nyaꞌa deꞌ pilih-E: Simon deꞌ sobot Yesus geh
nang Petrus,

pairs.source: 17	And James the [son] of Zebedee, and John the brother of James; and he surnamed them Boanerges, which is, The sons of thunder:
pairs.target:
17 Yakobus duoh Yohanes, odop-e deꞌ duwoh itih onak Zebedeus. Odop-e
deꞌ duwoh itih, Yesus biladon nang Boanerges loti-e “Nyaꞌa deꞌ kodaꞌ Dudu.”

pairs.source: 18	And Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the [son] of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Canaanite,
pairs.target:
18 Ogiꞌ geh Andreas, Filipus, Bartolomeus, Matius, Tomas, Yakobus onak
Alfeus, Tadeus, Simon soꞌ uluk ulang Yahudi deꞌ bijuang odaꞌ Israel bebas
soꞌ kerajaan Romawi,

pairs.source: 19	And Judas Iscariot, which also betrayed him: and they went into an house.
pairs.target:
19 duoh Yudas Iskariot, nyaꞌa deꞌ yaꞌ jua Yesus tuduꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ buꞌui daꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 20	And the multitude cometh together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.
pairs.target:
20 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus paliꞌ ke boli. Pak-e nyaꞌa bogoꞌ nog tikuluk lagiꞌ
ngubun Iyoh, yoh ngan Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E diꞌ supot man.

pairs.source: 21	And when his friends heard [of it], they went out to lay hold on him: for they said, He is beside himself.
pairs.target:
21 Nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ in-e, “Iyoh itih moꞌ bakoꞌ!” Takal madih ayua-e moꞌ
ngojit gah inoh, yoh moꞌ odi mit-E.

pairs.source: 22	And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said, He hath Beelzebub, and by the prince of the devils casteth he out devils.
pairs.target:
22 Gulu-gulu agama Yahudi deꞌ nog soꞌ Yerusalem moꞌ in-e, “Iyoh itih
obuah nguasa odaꞌ Beelzebul! Laja suaꞌ muat munua inoh leh deꞌ ngin
kuasa daꞌ-E, ngan-e kasig muat munua.”

pairs.source: 23	And he called them [unto him], and said unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan?
pairs.target:
23 Yesus moꞌ mogan nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ inoh, yohmoꞌ in-e, “Wat ki Laja
Muat munua ponai yaꞌ kasig Laja Muat munua?”

pairs.source: 24	And if a kingdom be divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.
pairs.target:
24 Yesus lanyut sina-E pakai nang silita, in-E, “Simoꞌ-e ogiꞌ negeli deꞌ
diꞌ layat-e tilukum daang-e silalu bikaꞌi si odop-e idoh diꞌ-e taan tuui.

pairs.source: 25	And if a house be divided against itself, that house cannot stand.
pairs.target: 25 Lawang boꞌon deꞌ silalu bikiing bilawan tipan odop-e idoh diꞌ-e taan tuui.

pairs.source: 26	And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand, but hath an end.
pairs.target:
26 Simoꞌ Laja Muat munua bilawan si odop-e wat ki wat-e yaꞌ taan tuui?
Iyoh pasti obuaꞌ mutuab.

pairs.source: 27	No man can enter into a strong man’s house, and spoil his goods, except he will first bind the strong man; and then he will spoil his house.
pairs.target:
27 Niꞌ naꞌan tuang doiꞌ geh deꞌ taan molot kaang
boli nyaꞌa deꞌ dolas duoh mit halta-e, simoꞌ-e diꞌ-e pasung dioꞌ. Takal-e
moꞌ mokuaꞌ pasung-e ke yoh tapod mit halta-e.

pairs.source: 28	Verily I say unto you, All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies wherewith soever they shall blaspheme:
pairs.target:
28 Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan: Suaꞌ dosa deꞌ nai nyaꞌa duoh sina deꞌ jaꞌat
aluaꞌ tapod obuah ngapun.

pairs.source: 29	But he that shall blaspheme against the Holy Ghost hath never forgiveness, but is in danger of eternal damnation:
pairs.target:
29 Pak-e sina deꞌ jaꞌat deꞌ pijaꞌat Iyang Topaꞌ,
idoh diꞌ Topaꞌ tapod ngapun-e. Dosa inoh moꞌ lokat nah-nah.”

pairs.source: 30	Because they said, He hath an unclean spirit.
pairs.target:
30 Yesus
tanon deꞌ in inoh, dop-e odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ nang Yesus obuah nguasa Laja
Muat munua.

pairs.source: 31	There came then his brethren and his mother, and, standing without, sent unto him, calling him.
pairs.target:
31 Mokuaꞌ inoh, sinoꞌ duoh madih Yesus nog yaꞌ bitapod duoh-E. Odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ kajon deꞌ sopaꞌ, yoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa mogan Yesus.

pairs.source: 32	And the multitude sat about him, and they said unto him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren without seek for thee.
pairs.target:
32 Takal inoh,  bogoꞌ nyaꞌa nog guluꞌ sinok Yesus. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ in-e, “Ogiꞌ sinoꞌ
duoh madih Ingan kajon deꞌ sopaꞌ. Yoh yaꞌ bitapod duoh Ingan.”

pairs.source: 33	And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother, or my brethren?
pairs.target: 33 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Osi sinoꞌ Kuꞌ? Osi madih Kuꞌ?”

pairs.source: 34	And he looked round about on them which sat about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren!
pairs.target:
34 Yoh moꞌ
ningaꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ gulu' sinok odop-E, yohmoꞌ in-e, “Deꞌ mutiꞌ leh sinoꞌ
duoh madih Kuꞌ!

pairs.source: 35	For whosoever shall do the will of God, the same is my brother, and my sister, and mother.
pairs.target:
35 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nai oni' deꞌ laꞌan Topaꞌ, deꞌ munoꞌ leh
sinoꞌ duoh madih Kuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 1	And he began again to teach by the sea side: and there was gathered unto him a great multitude, so that he entered into a ship, and sat in the sea; and the whole multitude was by the sea on the land.
pairs.target:
1 Yesus paliꞌ ngajal lagiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bingon Donu Galilea. Nyaꞌa moꞌ bogoꞌ
nog ngubun-E. Iyoh odi guluꞌ kaang olud deꞌ ogiꞌ daang donu. Pak-e
nyaꞌa bogoꞌ mujuag deꞌ doyoh bingon donu.

pairs.source: 2	And he taught them many things by parables, and said unto them in his doctrine,
pairs.target: 2 Bogoꞌ oni' deꞌ ngajal Yesus pakai nang silita, Iyoh moꞌ silita in-E,

pairs.source: 3	Hearken; Behold, there went out a sower to sow:
pairs.target: 3 “Ngojit dioꞌ! Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ odi dabul biniaꞌ.

pairs.source: 4	And it came to pass, as he sowed, some fell by the way side, and the fowls of the air came and devoured it up.
pairs.target:
4 Takal-e dabul biniaꞌ-e,
ogiꞌ deꞌ labuꞌ deꞌ olan, yohmoꞌ nog manuk lasuꞌ man kabuaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 5	And some fell on stony ground, where it had not much earth; and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of earth:
pairs.target:
5 Ogiꞌ geh
deꞌ labuꞌ deꞌ tun tanaꞌ deꞌ bibatuh, yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ tumuꞌ dop-e tanaꞌ-e lidiaꞌ.

pairs.source: 6	But when the sun was up, it was scorched; and because it had no root, it withered away.
pairs.target:
6 Pak-e takal onu moꞌ putiak, tumuꞌ pimuluah inoh moꞌ pisok yoh moꞌ
kobos layuꞌ, dop-e aat-e diꞌ-e tuluap kaang tanaꞌ.

pairs.source: 7	And some fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.
pairs.target:
7 Ogiꞌ geh deꞌ labuꞌ deꞌ
siak duh deꞌ bilojaꞌ. Takal-e tumuꞌ, duh deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ molut-e yoh moꞌ
diꞌ-e ponai mokat tumuꞌ duoh bibuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 8	And other fell on good ground, and did yield fruit that sprang up and increased; and brought forth, some thirty, and some sixty, and some an hundred.
pairs.target:
8 Ogiꞌ geh deꞌ labuꞌ deꞌ tanaꞌ deꞌ
paguh. Yoh moꞌ tumuꞌ yoh moꞌ bibuaꞌ, ogiꞌ deꞌ taluh puluꞌ sidoh bogoꞌ,
ogiꞌ geh deꞌ nuam puluꞌ sidoh bogoꞌ, ogiꞌ geh deꞌ silatus sidoh bogoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 9	And he said unto them, He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.
pairs.target:
9 Takal Yesus moꞌ mokuaꞌ nang silita inoh, Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Osi deꞌ ogiꞌ
kojit-e saꞌ-e ngojit-e!”

pairs.source: 10	And when he was alone, they that were about him with the twelve asked of him the parable.
pairs.target:
10 Takal nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ buu duam Yesus sadiꞌ-e, pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E
baya simoong duwoh naꞌan rasul-E moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ Yesus, oni loti silita
deꞌ nang-E inoh.

pairs.source: 11	And he said unto them, Unto you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of God: but unto them that are without, all [these] things are done in parables:
pairs.target:
11 Yesus moꞌ nyawot in-E, “Tuduꞌ ingan Topaꞌ moꞌ tanon tentang oni
wat Iyoh militah jadin Laja. Pak-e tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon Okuꞌ tanon pakai
nang silita.

pairs.source: 12	That seeing they may see, and not perceive; and hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest at any time they should be converted, and [their] sins should be forgiven them.
pairs.target:
12 Okuꞌ nai wat inoh saꞌ-e jadi kodaꞌ daang Kitab, deꞌ in-e,
‘Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ telus ningaꞌ,
pak-e diꞌ-e ngiloti oni-oni-e.
Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ telus ngojit,
pak-e diꞌ-e ngiloti oni-oni-e.   
Simoꞌ-e ngiloti-e, yoh togan olan deꞌ jaꞌat,
yohmoꞌ paliꞌ tuduꞌ Okuꞌ,
Okuꞌ yaꞌ ngapun dosa-e.’ ”

pairs.source: 13	And he said unto them, Know ye not this parable? and how then will ye know all parables?
pairs.target:
13 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Simoꞌ ingan diꞌ
ingan ngiloti silita deꞌ nang Kuꞌ tiꞌ-e, silita deꞌ bokon tuang idoh geh diꞌ
ingan ngiloti-e.

pairs.source: 14	The sower soweth the word.
pairs.target:
14 Okuꞌ yaꞌ tanon loti silita deꞌ nang Kuꞌ tiꞌ-e: Nyaꞌa deꞌ dabul biniaꞌ,
iyoh leh deꞌ kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tukang magah Pingunang Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 15	And these are they by the way side, where the word is sown; but when they have heard, Satan cometh immediately, and taketh away the word that was sown in their hearts.
pairs.target:
15 Biniaꞌ deꞌ
labuꞌ deꞌ olan iyoh leh deꞌ kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngojit Pingunang Topaꞌ, pak-e
Laja Muat munua lasuꞌ mit Pingunang Topaꞌ deꞌ tuang-e ngojit-e .

pairs.source: 16	And these are they likewise which are sown on stony ground; who, when they have heard the word, immediately receive it with gladness;
pairs.target:
16 Biniaꞌ
deꞌ labuꞌ deꞌ topat deꞌ bibatuh, samah kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngojit Pingunang
Topaꞌ yohmoꞌ lasuꞌ tilimaꞌ daang otin deꞌ doon.

pairs.source: 17	And have no root in themselves, and so endure but for a time: afterward, when affliction or persecution ariseth for the word’s sake, immediately they are offended.
pairs.target:
17 Pak-e Pingunang Topaꞌ
inoh diꞌ-e tumuꞌ daang otin osuap-e, yoh moꞌ diꞌ-e taan tuui, takal idip-e
susah jolaꞌ iyoh moꞌ lasuꞌ diꞌ-e bisayaꞌ.

pairs.source: 18	And these are they which are sown among thorns; such as hear the word,
pairs.target:
18 Biniaꞌ deꞌ labuꞌ deꞌ totaꞌ lojaꞌ,
samah kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngojit Pingunang Topaꞌ,

pairs.source: 19	And the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, and the lusts of other things entering in, choke the word, and it becometh unfruitful.
pairs.target:
19 pak-e yoh bigaduh natong
pingidip-e, suka yaꞌ kaya, ngilipuang suaꞌ-suaꞌ oni' daang dunia. Pingunang
Topaꞌ inoh moꞌ obuah molut, yohmoꞌ diꞌ-e ponai bibuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 20	And these are they which are sown on good ground; such as hear the word, and receive [it], and bring forth fruit, some thirtyfold, some sixty, and some an hundred.
pairs.target:
20 Biniaꞌ deꞌ labuꞌ
deꞌ tanaꞌ deꞌ paguh, samah kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngojit Pingunang Topaꞌ, yohmoꞌ
tumuꞌ daang otin osuap-e, yoh moꞌ bibuaꞌ. Ogiꞌ deꞌ bibuaꞌ taluh puluꞌ sidoh
bogoꞌ, ogiꞌ deꞌ nuam puluꞌ sidoh bogoꞌ, ogiꞌ geh deꞌ silatus sidoh bogoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 21	And he said unto them, Is a candle brought to be put under a bushel, or under a bed? and not to be set on a candlestick?
pairs.target:
21 Yesus moꞌ lanyut silita-E lagi', “Doiꞌ-e ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tung lapu yohmoꞌ
ngilokuab-e pakai bona yoh moꞌ suan deꞌ libuaꞌ topat boꞌos-e. Pasti nyaꞌa
tung lapu, yohmoꞌ kajuag deꞌ topat deꞌ bigatung, saꞌ-e odaꞌ tana' jawaꞌ.

pairs.source: 22	For there is nothing hid, which shall not be manifested; neither was any thing kept secret, but that it should come abroad.
pairs.target:
22 Oniꞌ deꞌ diꞌ nyaꞌa ponai kilin-e adin, tiaꞌ tuang ponai geh nyaꞌa kilin-e.
Oniꞌ deꞌ diꞌ nyaꞌa puꞌan-e adin, tiaꞌ tuang ponai geh nyaꞌa puꞌan-e.

pairs.source: 23	If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.
pairs.target: 23 Osi deꞌ ogiꞌ kojit-e, saꞌ-e ngojit bonal-bonal.”

pairs.source: 24	And he said unto them, Take heed what ye hear: with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you: and unto you that hear shall more be given.
pairs.target:
24 Yoh moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ, “Ngojit bonal-bonal-e, pingajal deꞌ tanon Kuꞌ tuduꞌ
ingan! Oni wat oniꞌ deꞌ nai nyeꞌ duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon, wat inoh leh wat
Topaꞌ duoh odop nyeꞌ, makin lobih soꞌ inoh.

pairs.source: 25	For he that hath, to him shall be given: and he that hath not, from him shall be taken even that which he hath.
pairs.target:
25 Dop-e osi deꞌ moꞌ ogiꞌ oniꞌ
deꞌ kakuꞌ-e, yoh yaꞌ soꞌon lobih bogoꞌ lagiꞌ, pak-e nyaꞌa deꞌ doiꞌ oniꞌ, sit
oniꞌ deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ kakuꞌ-e, yaꞌ obuah mit geh.”

pairs.source: 26	And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as if a man should cast seed into the ground;
pairs.target:
26 Yesus moꞌ ngajal lagiꞌ pakai silita ngan-e tanon oni wat Topaꞌ militah
jadin Laja. Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ dabul biniaꞌ-e deꞌ umoh-e.

pairs.source: 27	And should sleep, and rise night and day, and the seed should spring and grow up, he knoweth not how.
pairs.target:
27 Takal
onu ngalom iyoh boꞌos, onu jawaꞌ yoh moꞌ mokat bo'os, yoh moꞌ ningaꞌ
biniaꞌ-e moꞌ tumuꞌ luah suk-e bitamah bigatung, pak-e diꞌ-e puꞌan oni wat
tumuꞌ-e inoh bitamah ayuh.

pairs.source: 28	For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself; first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear.
pairs.target:
28 Tanaꞌ umoh inoh leh deꞌ odaꞌ biniaꞌ inoh tumuꞌ nog-e bibuaꞌ, sibungas-e
bisuat, yoh moꞌ bisalaꞌ yoh moꞌ jadin buaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 29	But when the fruit is brought forth, immediately he putteth in the sickle, because the harvest is come.
pairs.target:
29 Simoꞌ gandum inoh moꞌ
masak, nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ umoh inoh moꞌ ngutuam-e, dop-e moꞌ nog onu-e
yaꞌ ngutuam.”

pairs.source: 30	And he said, Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God? or with what comparison shall we compare it?
pairs.target:
30 Yesus moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ, “Samah kodaꞌ oni otoꞌ yaꞌ baning Topaꞌ deꞌ
militah jadin Laja? Silita oni ngan toꞌ tanon-e?

pairs.source: 31	[It is] like a grain of mustard seed, which, when it is sown in the earth, is less than all the seeds that be in the earth:
pairs.target:
31 Takal Topaꞌ militah jadin Laja, inoh samah kodaꞌ silita itih: Luang
sabih deꞌ sukup alus kiluang-e soꞌ luang pimuluah deꞌ ogiꞌ daang dunia.

pairs.source: 32	But when it is sown, it groweth up, and becometh greater than all herbs, and shooteth out great branches; so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it.
pairs.target:
32 Pak-e takal-e tumuꞌ, yoh moꞌ jadin koyuh deꞌ ayuh soꞌ pimuluah kuduas
deꞌ bokon. Yoh moꞌ bidaꞌan ayuh, bogoꞌ manuk deꞌ bisolin daꞌ-a.”

pairs.source: 33	And with many such parables spake he the word unto them, as they were able to hear [it].
pairs.target:
33 Wat inoh leh Yesus ngajal nyaꞌa pakai bogoꞌ silita kodaꞌ inoh, deꞌ
tapod nyaꞌa ngiloti-e.

pairs.source: 34	But without a parable spake he not unto them: and when they were alone, he expounded all things to his disciples.
pairs.target:
34 Yesus silalu ngajal nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ pakai nang
silita. Pak-e takal-E jok-e duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, Yoh tanon susuaꞌ loti
pingunang-E tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 35	And the same day, when the even was come, he saith unto them, Let us pass over unto the other side.
pairs.target: 35 Takal ngumi inoh geh, Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, “Jaꞌ otoꞌ motas keꞌ polad donu.”

pairs.source: 36	And when they had sent away the multitude, they took him even as he was in the ship. And there were also with him other little ships.
pairs.target:
36 Yesus moꞌ muun kaang olud, pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E
moꞌ suwaꞌ muat duoh-E niꞌ olud. Yoh moꞌ togan nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ, pak-e ogiꞌ
geh nyaꞌa deꞌ nunaꞌ pakai olud deꞌ bokon.

pairs.source: 37	And there arose a great storm of wind, and the waves beat into the ship, so that it was now full.
pairs.target:
37 Aluaꞌ diꞌ-e tuui bilakat, sobak
libut moꞌ nog. Piꞌin gilumang moꞌ molot kaang olud-e, olud-e moꞌ tadoꞌ-e
yaꞌ kuuam.

pairs.source: 38	And he was in the hinder part of the ship, asleep on a pillow: and they awake him, and say unto him, Master, carest thou not that we perish?
pairs.target:
38 Takal inoh Yesus boꞌos deꞌ tun tilam deꞌ butut olud. Yohmoꞌ
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E guyang odaꞌ mokat. Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Gulu! Doh diꞌ Ingan
tolu nang otoꞌ yaꞌ kobos kuuam?”

pairs.source: 39	And he arose, and rebuked the wind, and said unto the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.
pairs.target:
39 Yesus moꞌ mokat, Yoh moꞌ nang sobak libut duoh sina tuduꞌ donu
inoh in-E, “Loꞌo! Maꞌ tiyaꞌ bilayaꞌ!” Sobak duoh gilumang moꞌ lasuꞌ loꞌo.

pairs.source: 40	And he said unto them, Why are ye so fearful? how is it that ye have no faith?
pairs.target:
40 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Oni nai ingan tolu? Oni nai
ingan diꞌ bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Okuꞌ?”

pairs.source: 41	And they feared exceedingly, and said one to another, What manner of man is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?
pairs.target:
41 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sukup tolu-e, yoh moꞌ in-e tipan odop-e, “Osi
sibonal-e Yoh itih, sape sobak libut, gilumang tuang tunuak geh tuduꞌ
sina-E?”

pairs.source: 1	And they came over unto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.
pairs.target:
1 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E nog keꞌ polad Donu Galilea,
topat ulang Gerasa loꞌo.

pairs.source: 2	And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit,
pairs.target:
2 Takal Yesus maꞌad soꞌ aang olud, ogiꞌ niꞌ
naꞌan dali deꞌ obuah bikalui muat munua deꞌ loꞌo deꞌ totaꞌ kubul odi tuduꞌ
Yesus.

pairs.source: 3	Who had [his] dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not with chains:
pairs.target: 3 Dali inoh doiꞌ nyaꞌa tapod yaꞌ mokos-e bial-e pakai late.

pairs.source: 4	Because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken in pieces: neither could any [man] tame him.
pairs.target:
4 Moꞌ paliꞌ-paliꞌ nyaꞌa pasung tongan poꞌon-e, pak-e late ngan nyaꞌa
pasung-e obuaꞌ motod-e, bosi deꞌ poꞌon-e tuang mugat-e geh. Dali inoh
sikiya dolas doiꞌ tiyaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ taan yaꞌ pasung-e.

pairs.source: 5	And always, night and day, he was in the mountains, and in the tombs, crying, and cutting himself with stones.
pairs.target:
5 Iyoh singonu singalom motak moliꞌ deꞌ totaꞌ kubul, deꞌ punguꞌ-punguꞌ
simadi-e nang bogan-e daang-e mupuꞌ gonan-e pakai batuh.

pairs.source: 6	But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him,
pairs.target:
6 Soꞌ juuaꞌ geh iyoh ningaꞌ takal Yesus nog, yoh moꞌ bikoduh tuduꞌ Yesus,
yohmoꞌ nyomah Yesus nog jowin-e sium tanaꞌ.

pairs.source: 7	And cried with a loud voice, and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, [thou] Son of the most high God? I adjure thee by God, that thou torment me not.
pairs.target:
7 Daang-e nang bogan-e,
“Yesus Onak Topaꞌ deꞌ sukup ayuh kuasa-E, oni wat Muꞌu yaꞌ duoh okuꞌ?
Daang adon Topaꞌ, okuꞌ bonal-bonal mitiaꞌ tuduꞌ Ingan maꞌ yaꞌ kanam
okuꞌ!”

pairs.source: 8	For he said unto him, Come out of the man, [thou] unclean spirit.
pairs.target:
8 Yoh ngan-e in inoh, dop-e Yesus sina tuduꞌ muat munua, “Luah leh soꞌ
nyaꞌa itih!”

pairs.source: 9	And he asked him, What [is] thy name? And he answered, saying, My name [is] Legion: for we are many.
pairs.target:
9 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ-e, “Osi adon muꞌu?” Muat munua daang gonan
nyaꞌa inoh moꞌ nyawot-E,
“Adon kuꞌ Legion, dop-e koꞌih bogoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 10	And he besought him much that he would not send them away out of the country.
pairs.target:
10 Paliꞌ-paliꞌ iyoh mitiaꞌ tuduꞌ
Yesus, saꞌ-E diꞌ-e kasig muat munua luah soꞌ topat inoh.

pairs.source: 11	Now there was there nigh unto the mountains a great herd of swine feeding.
pairs.target:
11 Diꞌ-e juuaꞌ soꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, bogoꞌ oyuaꞌ deꞌ kalik man-e deꞌ
tilipang punguꞌ.

pairs.source: 12	And all the devils besought him, saying, Send us into the swine, that we may enter into them.
pairs.target:
12 Muat munua moꞌ mitiaꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus, “Odaꞌ leh koꞌih
molot kaang gonan oyuaꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 13	And forthwith Jesus gave them leave. And the unclean spirits went out, and entered into the swine: and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the sea, (they were about two thousand;) and were choked in the sea.
pairs.target:
13 Yesus moꞌ odaꞌ muat munua deꞌ
munoꞌ luah soꞌ gonan dali inoh yohmoꞌ molot daang gonan kaban oyuaꞌ
deꞌ munoꞌ. Suaꞌ oyuaꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ bitabum soꞌ tilipang punguꞌ, kaang
donu yohmoꞌ kobos longod. Oyuaꞌ deꞌ kobos inoh kulang lobih ogiꞌ duwoh
libu polong.

pairs.source: 14	And they that fed the swine fled, and told [it] in the city, and in the country. And they went out to see what it was that was done.
pairs.target:
14 Ayua deꞌ jaga oyuaꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ bikoduh buu keꞌ kota, keꞌ
kupuaꞌ-kupuaꞌ deꞌ sinok ngan-e tanon gah inoh. Nyaꞌa moꞌ nog ningaꞌ oniꞌ  deꞌ magah-a inoh.

pairs.source: 15	And they come to Jesus, and see him that was possessed with the devil, and had the legion, sitting, and clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.
pairs.target:
15 Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ odi tuduꞌ Yesus yohmoꞌ ningaꞌ
dali deꞌ obuah bikalui muat munua inoh guluꞌ, yoh moꞌ pakai pimakai-e
daang-e diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ bakoꞌ. Suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nog deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ tolu.

pairs.source: 16	And they that saw [it] told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil, and [also] concerning the swine.
pairs.target:
16 Suaꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ ningaꞌ dali inoh duoh kaban oyuaꞌ inoh, moꞌ silita oni deꞌ moꞌ
ningaꞌ-a.

pairs.source: 17	And they began to pray him to depart out of their coasts.
pairs.target:
17 Nyaꞌa deꞌ loꞌo deꞌ Gerasa inoh moꞌ ulih-ulih mitiaꞌ odaꞌ Yesus buu soꞌ
topat inoh.

pairs.source: 18	And when he was come into the ship, he that had been possessed with the devil prayed him that he might be with him.
pairs.target:
18 Takal Yesus moꞌ muat kaang olud, dali deꞌ mokuaꞌ obuah bikalui
muat munua inoh mitiaꞌ odop-e yaꞌ suwaꞌ nunaꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 19	Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him, Go home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee.
pairs.target:
19 Pak-e Yesus jaman-e, yohmoꞌ in-e, “Paliꞌ negeh, tanon tuduꞌ madih
ayua muꞌ, oni deꞌ moꞌ nai Topaꞌ tuduꞌ muꞌu duoh tanon nang Topaꞌ masiꞌ
tuduꞌ muꞌu.”

pairs.source: 20	And he departed, and began to publish in Decapolis how great things Jesus had done for him: and all [men] did marvel.
pairs.target:
20 Dali inoh moꞌ buu, yohmoꞌ odi magah keꞌ topat deꞌ sobot nyaꞌa nang,
“Simoong Kota”. Danoꞌ iyoh moꞌ silita oni deꞌ moꞌ nai Yesus tuduꞌ odop-e.
Suaꞌ nyaꞌa ilan ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ silita-e.

pairs.source: 21	And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side, much people gathered unto him: and he was nigh unto the sea.
pairs.target:
21 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E paliꞌ motas Donu Galilea pakai olud.
Takal Yesus moꞌ nog polad donu, nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ bitodod-todod odi
ngumaꞌ Iyoh.

pairs.source: 22	And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name; and when he saw him, he fell at his feet,
pairs.target:
22 Pimipin topat simayang agama Yahudi deꞌ adon Yairus
nog tuduꞌ Yesus. Takal yoh moꞌ ningaꞌ Yesus, yohmoꞌ guluꞌ bikunyug deꞌ
sulung jowin-E.

pairs.source: 23	And besought him greatly, saying, My little daughter lieth at the point of death: [I pray thee], come and lay thy hands on her, that she may be healed; and she shall live.
pairs.target:
23 Daang-e in-e, “Tok-tok kuꞌ mitiaꞌ tulung tuduꞌ Ingan,
odi keꞌ boli kuꞌ dioꞌ, tomaꞌ gonan onak dayung kuꞌ deꞌ bonaꞌ, saꞌ-e mokuaꞌ,
duoh diꞌ-e kobos.”

pairs.source: 24	And [Jesus] went with him; and much people followed him, and thronged him.
pairs.target:
24 Yesus moꞌ lasuꞌ odi duoh Yairus. Nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ odi siuah-siuah-e
bitunaꞌ duoh Yesus daang-e bitodod-todod, soꞌ boit soꞌ toꞌuh-E.

pairs.source: 25	And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,
pairs.target:
25 Daang uluk nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan dayung deꞌ obuah onam
bubuꞌ, onam nog koꞌis-e deꞌ lika yoh noman-e, moꞌ simoong duwoh sowaꞌ
tuui-e.

pairs.source: 26	And had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had, and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse,
pairs.target:
26 Moꞌ puas yoh ngubat-e sape nog obuaꞌ halta benda-e, pak-e aluaꞌ
geh diꞌ-e mokuaꞌ. Makin onu makin bitamah bonaꞌ.

pairs.source: 27	When she had heard of Jesus, came in the press behind, and touched his garment.
pairs.target:
27 Dayung inoh moꞌ
ngojit oni' deꞌ moꞌ nai Yesus soꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ, yoh moꞌ odi sinok Yesus
soꞌ dug-E.

pairs.source: 28	For she said, If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole.
pairs.target:
28 Yohmoꞌ in-e daang otin-e, “Simoꞌ kuꞌ tapod tomaꞌ jubah-E,
okuꞌ pasti mokuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 29	And straightway the fountain of her blood was dried up; and she felt in [her] body that she was healed of that plague.
pairs.target: 29 Takal inoh geh yoh tomaꞌ jubah Yesus, onam koꞌis-e lasuꞌ mokuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 30	And Jesus, immediately knowing in himself that virtue had gone out of him, turned him about in the press, and said, Who touched my clothes?
pairs.target:
30 Takal inoh geh Yesus ngoon ogiꞌ kuasa deꞌ luah soꞌ odop-E. Yesus moꞌ   
kumiat tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ Yoh moꞌ sikian in-E, “Osi deꞌ tomaꞌ jubah
Kuꞌ?”

pairs.source: 31	And his disciples said unto him, Thou seest the multitude thronging thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?
pairs.target:
31 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ in-e, “Idoh keh Ingan ningaꞌ nyaꞌa bogoꞌ deꞌ
bitodod-todod? Oni nai Ingan sikian osi deꞌ tomaꞌ odop Ingan.”

pairs.source: 32	And he looked round about to see her that had done this thing.
pairs.target: 32 Yesus moꞌ ningaꞌ katiꞌ-kanih osi deꞌ tomaꞌ odop-E.

pairs.source: 33	But the woman fearing and trembling, knowing what was done in her, came and fell down before him, and told him all the truth.
pairs.target:
33 Dayung inoh
moꞌ kimotol tolu takal-e moꞌ puꞌan nang odop-e moꞌ mokuaꞌ, yoh moꞌ
guluꞌ bikunyug daang jowin-e sium tanaꞌ deꞌ sulung jowin Yesus, yoh moꞌ
ngakuꞌ nang odop-e deꞌ tomaꞌ jubah Yesus.

pairs.source: 34	And he said unto her, Daughter, thy faith hath made thee whole; go in peace, and be whole of thy plague.
pairs.target:
34 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ dayung
inoh, “Luban muꞌu bisayaꞌ punuaꞌ tuduꞌ Okuꞌ muꞌu moꞌ mokuaꞌ, paliꞌ leh
daang otin deꞌ bidanah. Muꞌu moꞌ tok-tok mokuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 35	While he yet spake, there came from the ruler of the synagogue’s [house certain] which said, Thy daughter is dead: why troublest thou the Master any further?
pairs.target:
35 Takal Yesus aluaꞌ sina, kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa soꞌ boli Yairus moꞌ nog
tanon in-e, “Onak dayung ingan moꞌ kobos, dusah tiyaꞌ nyeꞌ nyusah Gulu
neh!”

pairs.source: 36	As soon as Jesus heard the word that was spoken, he saith unto the ruler of the synagogue, Be not afraid, only believe.
pairs.target:
36 Pak-e Yesus diꞌ-e piduli oniꞌ deꞌ nang odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, Yesus moꞌ
sina tuduꞌ Yairus, “Maꞌ tolu, bisayaꞌ negeh!”

pairs.source: 37	And he suffered no man to follow him, save Peter, and James, and John the brother of James.
pairs.target:
37 Yesus moꞌ lasuꞌ ponu, Yoh
jaman nyaꞌa niꞌ naꞌan tuang diꞌ soꞌon geh nunaꞌ Odop-E, jok-e odaꞌ Petrus,
Yakobus duoh madih-e Yohanes.

pairs.source: 38	And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue, and seeth the tumult, and them that wept and wailed greatly.
pairs.target:
38 Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ nog boli Yairus,
yoh moꞌ ningaꞌ bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ siꞌian nang puas bogan-e.

pairs.source: 39	And when he was come in, he saith unto them, Why make ye this ado, and weep? the damsel is not dead, but sleepeth.
pairs.target:
39 Yesus molot,
Yoh moꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Oni nai ingan kiak kaung siꞌian deꞌ
in inoh neh? Onak opot itih idoh diꞌ-e kobos, iyoh jok-e boꞌos.”

pairs.source: 40	And they laughed him to scorn. But when he had put them all out, he taketh the father and the mother of the damsel, and them that were with him, and entereth in where the damsel was lying.
pairs.target:
40 Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ towoh Yesus. Yoh moꞌ odaꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ
luah. Yesus moꞌ toban sinoꞌ samaꞌ onak opot inoh duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E
molot kaang bilit-e.

pairs.source: 41	And he took the damsel by the hand, and said unto her, Talitha cumi; which is, being interpreted, Damsel, I say unto thee, arise.
pairs.target:
41 Yesus moꞌ kagong tongan onak dayung Yairus inoh,
Yoh moꞌ sina tuduꞌ-e, “Talita kum,” loti-e “Oi onak dayung, Okuꞌ odaꞌ muꞌu
mokat!”

pairs.source: 42	And straightway the damsel arose, and walked; for she was [of the age] of twelve years. And they were astonished with a great astonishment.
pairs.target:
42 Takal inoh geh onak dayung inoh moꞌ lasuꞌ mokat mujuag, yoh moꞌ
ponu. Takal inoh umul-e simoong duwoh sowaꞌ. Suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ
moꞌ sukup doon-e daang-e ilan-e.

pairs.source: 43	And he charged them straitly that no man should know it; and commanded that something should be given her to eat.
pairs.target:
43 Yesus moꞌ isin-isin jaman odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ tanon tuduꞌ osi sijaꞌ-e.
Yesus moꞌ in-e, “Ngin odaꞌ onak opot inoh man.”

pairs.source: 1	And he went out from thence, and came into his own country; and his disciples follow him.
pairs.target:
1 Soꞌ boli Yairus, Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E paliꞌ keꞌ kupuaꞌ-E Nazaret,
kupuaꞌ asal-E.

pairs.source: 2	And when the sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue: and many hearing [him] were astonished, saying, From whence hath this [man] these things? and what wisdom [is] this which is given unto him, that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?
pairs.target:
2 Takal Onu Sabat, Iyoh moꞌ mulai ngajal nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ deꞌ boli topat
simayang agama Yahudi. Suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ ngajal-E moꞌ sukup  ilan-e. Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ in-e, “Soꞌ ki soꞌ-E soꞌon ilmu deꞌ masam-masam?
Kuasa deꞌ oni wat-e deꞌ ogiꞌ daꞌ-A? Oni wat-e ngan-E ponai nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan
nyaꞌa?

pairs.source: 3	Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Joses, and of Juda, and Simon? and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended at him.
pairs.target:
3 Deꞌ puꞌan otoꞌ, Yoh itih onak tukang koyuh. Sinoꞌ-E Maria, duoh
kudu-kudu sudiꞌ-E deꞌ dali, Yakobus, Yoses, Yudas duoh Simon. Sudiꞌ-E
deꞌ dayung tuang ogiꞌ geh datiꞌ.” Noh leh ngan odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ doliaꞌ-e
tilimaꞌ Iyoh danoꞌ.

pairs.source: 4	But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honour, but in his own country, and among his own kin, and in his own house.
pairs.target:
4 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Daki-daki sijaꞌ-e nyaꞌa pimodo
tuduꞌ nabi, pak-e jok-e nyaꞌa deꞌ kupuaꞌ-e duoh madih ayua duoh sikiaꞌ
sudiꞌ-e deꞌ diꞌ-e pimodo tuduꞌ-e.”

pairs.source: 5	And he could there do no mighty work, save that he laid his hands upon a few sick folk, and healed [them].
pairs.target:
5 Danoꞌ, Iyoh diꞌ-e dapod nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa, jok-e kudu-kudu naꞌan
nyaꞌa deꞌ tomaꞌ-E deꞌ odaꞌ-E mokuaꞌ soꞌ onam-e.

pairs.source:
6	And he marvelled because of their unbelief. And he went round about the villages, teaching.
  7	And he called [unto him] the twelve, and began to send them forth by two and two; and gave them power over unclean spirits;
pairs.target:
6 Yesus sukup ilan-e, oni
nai nyaꞌa deꞌ kupuaꞌ-E diꞌ-e bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ odop-E. Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ ponu ngajal nyaꞌa keꞌ kupuaꞌ-kupuaꞌ deꞌ
bokon.
moꞌ mogan simoong duwoh naꞌan rasul-E. Iyoh moꞌ ngin
kuasa tuduꞌ-e saꞌ-e ponai kasig muat munua, yohmoꞌ odaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
odi ngaꞌ duwoh-duwoh.

pairs.source: 8	And commanded them that they should take nothing for [their] journey, save a staff only; no scrip, no bread, no money in [their] purse:
pairs.target:
8 Iyoh sibaya tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ jaman toban
balang-balang deꞌ yaꞌ pakai-e kodaꞌ onyad, duit, duoh bek. Jok nyeꞌ soꞌon
toban sikuud.

pairs.source: 9	But [be] shod with sandals; and not put on two coats.
pairs.target: 9 Jok nyeꞌ pakai silipal duoh bojuh deꞌ polong nyeꞌ sijaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 10	And he said unto them, In what place soever ye enter into an house, there abide till ye depart from that place.
pairs.target:
10 Iyoh moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ, “Simoꞌ ingan nog deꞌ kota, ogiꞌ nyaꞌa tilimaꞌ ingan
loꞌo deꞌ boli-e, nyeꞌ moꞌ ngilumon danoꞌ nog ingan buu paliꞌ soꞌ kota inoh.

pairs.source: 11	And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear you, when ye depart thence, shake off the dust under your feet for a testimony against them. Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city.
pairs.target:
11 Simoꞌ-e ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ topat soꞌ ingan odi, diꞌ-e tilimaꞌ ingan duoh doliaꞌ-e
ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ nang ingan, nyeꞌ moꞌ buu daang nyeꞌ nguguah lopu tana' soꞌ
lupaꞌ poꞌon ingan, saꞌ-e jadin tanda Topaꞌ yaꞌ ngukum odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 12	And they went out, and preached that men should repent.
pairs.target:
12 Takal-e mokuaꞌ ngojit sibaya Yesus, keꞌ simoong duwoh naꞌan rasul-E
moꞌ bilakat ponu, tanon tuduꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tapod-e, odaꞌ togan olan deꞌ
jaꞌat duoh paliꞌ keꞌ olan Topaꞌ, nyeꞌ moꞌ nunaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ nang-E.

pairs.source: 13	And they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick, and healed [them].
pairs.target:
13 Bogoꞌ
basa muat munua deꞌ kasig rasul-rasul Yesus, yoh gasak inyuaꞌ zaitun deꞌ
gonan nyaꞌa deꞌ monam odaꞌ mokuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 14	And king Herod heard [of him]; (for his name was spread abroad:) and he said, That John the Baptist was risen from the dead, and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him.
pairs.target:
14 Laja Herodes moꞌ ngojit gah tentang Yesus, dop-e adon-E moꞌ timogah katiꞌ-kanih. Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nang, “Yohanes Pembaptis paliꞌ idip baꞌuh, iyoh
ngan-e ogiꞌ kuasa-e nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa.”

pairs.source: 15	Others said, That it is Elias. And others said, That it is a prophet, or as one of the prophets.
pairs.target:
15 Pak-e  
ogiꞌ geh nyaꞌa deꞌ nang, “Iyoh itih nabi Elia deꞌ noꞌuh-e!” Ogiꞌ
geh nyaꞌa deꞌ nang “Iyoh itih nabi deꞌ samah kodaꞌ nabi-nabi soꞌ joman
deꞌ noꞌuh-e.”

pairs.source: 16	But when Herod heard [thereof], he said, It is John, whom I beheaded: he is risen from the dead.
pairs.target:
16 Takal Laja Herodes moꞌ ngojit gah inoh iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Iyoh pasti
Yohanes Pembaptis deꞌ noꞌuh-e, deꞌ moꞌ mokuaꞌ kuꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa notok
tunguaꞌ-e deꞌ moꞌ paliꞌ idip baꞌuh.”

pairs.source: 17	For Herod himself had sent forth and laid hold upon John, and bound him in prison for Herodias’ sake, his brother Philip’s wife: for he had married her.
pairs.target:
17 Dop-e deꞌ dioꞌ soꞌ kanoꞌ Laja Herodes itih leh deꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa takap
duoh pasung-e yohmoꞌ naꞌ kaang jel. Herodes nai wat inoh, dop-e Yohanes
Pembaptis ngalah nang Herodes mit Herodias odaꞌ jadin sowon-e. Deꞌ
dioꞌ, Herodias itih iyohleh sowon Filipus, Filipus itih madih odop Herodes.

pairs.source: 18	For John had said unto Herod, It is not lawful for thee to have thy brother’s wife.
pairs.target:
18 Yohanes moꞌ silalu ngalah Herodes nang polih nyeꞌ mit sowon madih
nyeꞌ odaꞌ jadin sowon nyeꞌ.

pairs.source: 19	Therefore Herodias had a quarrel against him, and would have killed him; but she could not:
pairs.target:
19 Iyoh ngan Herodias buꞌui tuduꞌ Yohanes,
yoh moꞌ yaꞌ ngabos-e. Pak-e yoh diꞌ-e ponai nai wat inoh,

pairs.source: 20	For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just man and an holy, and observed him; and when he heard him, he did many things, and heard him gladly.
pairs.target:
20 dop-e Herodes
pimodo tuduꞌ Yohanes. Iyoh puꞌan-e geh nang Yohanes Pembaptis ulang
deꞌ bonal, doiꞌ salah-e. Yoh ngan-e odaꞌ nyaꞌa jaga Yohanes saꞌ nyaꞌa diꞌ-e
ngabos-e. Pak-e bilang-e ngojit pingunang Yohanes, yoh moꞌ jadin bigaduh
kila-e, pak-e yoh sonang geh ngojit-e.

pairs.source: 21	And when a convenient day was come, that Herod on his birthday made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief [estates] of Galilee;
pairs.target:
21 Nyuang-nyuang-e Herodias moꞌ soꞌon olan ngan-e yaꞌ ngabos Yohanes
Pembaptis. Takal onu Herodes biluman onu limokah-e, yoh moꞌ ngunang
suaꞌ piayuh-piayuh, pimipin-pimipin sidadu, duoh ulang-ulang deꞌ timogah
deꞌ propinsi Galilea.

pairs.source: 22	And when the daughter of the said Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod and them that sat with him, the king said unto the damsel, Ask of me whatsoever thou wilt, and I will give [it] thee.
pairs.target:
22 Takal-e biluman inoh, onak dayung Herodias bitanaꞌ. Herodes duoh
suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ daang lami inoh sukup doon-e ningaꞌ iyoh bitanaꞌ. Yoh
ngan Herodes in-e, “Oni deꞌ yaꞌ mitiaꞌ muꞌ tuduꞌ okuꞌ, tanon negeh tiaꞌ kuꞌ
ngin daꞌ nyeꞌ.”

pairs.source: 23	And he sware unto her, Whatsoever thou shalt ask of me, I will give [it] thee, unto the half of my kingdom.
pairs.target:
23 Herodes moꞌ bisupah tuduꞌ onak Herodias yoh moꞌ in-e, “Oni sijaꞌ-e
deꞌ mitiaꞌ muꞌ kuꞌ ngin daꞌ nyeꞌ, bial-e sitengah soꞌ negeli deꞌ kagong kuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 24	And she went forth, and said unto her mother, What shall I ask? And she said, The head of John the Baptist.
pairs.target:
24 Onak dayung inoh moꞌ odi sikian tuduꞌ sinoꞌ-e “Oni deꞌ patut okuꞌ
mitiaꞌ-e?” In-e.
Sinoꞌ-e moꞌ nyawot-e, “Mitiaꞌ bak Yohanes Pembaptis.”

pairs.source: 25	And she came in straightway with haste unto the king, and asked, saying, I will that thou give me by and by in a charger the head of John the Baptist.
pairs.target:
25 Onak dayung inoh moꞌ paliꞌ ngaduap Herodes yohmoꞌ in-e, “Okuꞌ
mitiaꞌ bak Yohanes Pembaptis tuduꞌ ingan, katod tuduꞌ okuꞌ naꞌ daang
talam!”

pairs.source: 26	And the king was exceeding sorry; [yet] for his oath’s sake, and for their sakes which sat with him, he would not reject her.
pairs.target:
26 Takal Herodes ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ mitiaꞌ-e inoh bak Yohanes Pembaptis,
otin Herodes moꞌ sukup ngilobuꞌ, pak-e yoh moꞌ diꞌ-e ponai nalik sina-e,
dop-e moꞌ tilanyul bisupah deꞌ jowin nyaꞌa deꞌ ngunang-e.

pairs.source: 27	And immediately the king sent an executioner, and commanded his head to be brought: and he went and beheaded him in the prison,
pairs.target:
27 Iyoh moꞌ
lasuꞌ odaꞌ sidadu-e notok tunguaꞌ Yohanes Pembaptis toban tuduꞌ odop-e.  Sidadu-e moꞌ lasuꞌ odi keꞌ jel yoh moꞌ notok tunguaꞌ Yohanes.

pairs.source: 28	And brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel: and the damsel gave it to her mother.
pairs.target:
28 Mokuaꞌ
inoh yoh moꞌ toban bak Yohanes deꞌ naꞌ-e daang talam, yohmoꞌ ngin tuduꞌ
onak dayung Herodias. Onak dayung inoh moꞌ ngin tuduꞌ sinoꞌ-e lagiꞌ.

pairs.source: 29	And when his disciples heard [of it], they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb.
pairs.target:
29 Takal pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yohanes moꞌ ngojit nang Yohanes moꞌ obuah
ngabos, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ odi mit todang-e yohmoꞌ ngubul-e.

pairs.source: 30	And the apostles gathered themselves together unto Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught.
pairs.target:
30 Keꞌ simoong duwoh naꞌan rasul Yesus deꞌ pait-e inoh paliꞌ tikuluk
duoh Yesus. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ tanon suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ moꞌ nai-e duoh
oniꞌ deꞌ ngajal-e.

pairs.source: 31	And he said unto them, Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest a while: for there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.
pairs.target:
31 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ rasul-rasul-E deꞌ munoꞌ, “Jaꞌ otoꞌ
odi keꞌ topat deꞌ motug, deꞌ doiꞌ nyaꞌa daꞌ-e saꞌ otoꞌ tapod nosaꞌ loꞌo niꞌ
tiliaꞌ.” Yesus in inoh, saai nyaꞌa sikiya bogoꞌ deꞌ nog, deꞌ buu. Yesus duoh
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E diꞌ-e supot man.

pairs.source: 32	And they departed into a desert place by ship privately.
pairs.target:
32 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ buu pakai
olud, ngan-e odi keꞌ topat deꞌ doiꞌ nyaꞌa daꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 33	And the people saw them departing, and many knew him, and ran afoot thither out of all cities, and outwent them, and came together unto him.
pairs.target:
33 Pak-e bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kilin odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ buu, duoh puꞌan kaki
soꞌ-e yaꞌ odi. Nyaꞌa moꞌ obuaꞌ bikoduh soꞌ kota-kota odi keꞌ topat deꞌ soꞌ
Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E odi. Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ dioꞌ nog.

pairs.source: 34	And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep not having a shepherd: and he began to teach them many things.
pairs.target:
34 Takal
Yesus moꞌ maꞌad soꞌ olud keꞌ doyoh, Yoh moꞌ ningaꞌ nyaꞌa moꞌ bogoꞌ. Iyoh
masiꞌ tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, dop-e Yoh ningaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ samah
kodaꞌ domba deꞌ doiꞌ nyaꞌa piala-e. Noh leh ngan Yesus moꞌ mulai tanon
bogoꞌ pingajal tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 35	And when the day was now far spent, his disciples came unto him, and said, This is a desert place, and now the time [is] far passed:
pairs.target:
35 Takal onu moꞌ ngumi, pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ Yesus,
“Onu moꞌ yaꞌ ngalom, topat itih juuaꞌ soꞌ nyaꞌa.

pairs.source: 36	Send them away, that they may go into the country round about, and into the villages, and buy themselves bread: for they have nothing to eat.
pairs.target:
36 Lobih paguh Ingan
odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ mutiꞌ buu soꞌ topat itih, saꞌ-a tapod milih pinguman-e deꞌ
kupuaꞌ-kupuaꞌ deꞌ ogiꞌ sinok itih.”

pairs.source: 37	He answered and said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they say unto him, Shall we go and buy two hundred pennyworth of bread, and give them to eat?
pairs.target:
37 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Ingan negeh deꞌ ngin man tuduꞌ nyaꞌa
deꞌ mutiꞌ!”
In odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ nyawot-e, “Doiꞌ koꞌih taan milih pinguman deꞌ
loga-e duwoh latus kiping duit pilak, ngan koꞌih yaꞌ maꞌan odop-e deꞌ
kiang-kiang itih?”

pairs.source: 38	He saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five, and two fishes.
pairs.target:
38 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ bisikian tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Suba ningaꞌ dioꞌ,
duam kudu kueh ingan deꞌ ogiꞌ!” 
Takal-e mokuaꞌ ningaꞌ-e yoh moꞌ in-e, “Ogiꞌ limoh kueh, ogiꞌ duwoh
polong ikian.”

pairs.source: 39	And he commanded them to make all sit down by companies upon the green grass.
pairs.target: 39 Iyoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ guluꞌ bikuluk deꞌ tun duh.

pairs.source: 40	And they sat down in ranks, by hundreds, and by fifties.
pairs.target:
40 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ guluꞌ bikuluk ogiꞌ deꞌ ngaꞌ silatus, ogiꞌ deꞌ
ngaꞌ limoh puluꞌ daang niꞌ uluk.

pairs.source: 41	And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fishes, he looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake the loaves, and gave [them] to his disciples to set before them; and the two fishes divided he among them all.
pairs.target:
41 Yesus moꞌ mit limoh kueh baya duwoh
polong ikian inoh, Iyoh moꞌ bigalong keꞌ longit, yohmoꞌ bisukul tuduꞌ
Topaꞌ. Mokuaꞌ inoh Iyoh moꞌ nyipiak-nyipiak kueh-e, yohmoꞌ ngin tuduꞌ
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E saꞌ-e kutung tuduꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa. Watnoh geh wat-e duoh
ikian deꞌ duwoh polong inoh, Iyoh bikutung tuduꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa.

pairs.source: 42	And they did all eat, and were filled.
pairs.target:
42 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa
deꞌ munoꞌ man nog busuah-e.

pairs.source: 43	And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments, and of the fishes.
pairs.target:
43 Mokuaꞌ inoh, nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nguluk
kuban-e. Takal-e moꞌ tikuluk, aluaꞌ ogiꞌ simoong duwoh bakul.

pairs.source: 44	And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men.
pairs.target:
44 Nyaꞌa
deꞌ suwaꞌ man inoh ogiꞌ kila-kila limoh libu naꞌan dali.

pairs.source: 45	And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship, and to go to the other side before unto Bethsaida, while he sent away the people.
pairs.target:
45 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus lasuꞌ odaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E muat deꞌ olud dioꞌ odi keꞌ kota Betsaida deꞌ polad Donu Galilea. Iyoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ buu
paliꞌ.

pairs.source: 46	And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray.
pairs.target:
46 Takal nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ buu, Yesus moꞌ maꞌad keꞌ tun punguꞌ, ngan-e
yaꞌ bidoa.

pairs.source: 47	And when even was come, the ship was in the midst of the sea, and he alone on the land.
pairs.target:
47 Takal onu moꞌ ngalom, olud deꞌ pakai pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E
inoh moꞌ nog uun donu, pak-e Yesus aluaꞌ deꞌ doyoh.

pairs.source: 48	And he saw them toiling in rowing; for the wind was contrary unto them: and about the fourth watch of the night he cometh unto them, walking upon the sea, and would have passed by them.
pairs.target:
48 Yesus ningaꞌ
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E lolah posah bikayuh olud-e dop-e sobak nog soꞌ jowin
olud-e. Takal onu aluaꞌ bosow, Yesus odi tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, simadi-E
ponu tun piꞌin. Iyoh ponu mun deꞌ yaꞌ kawan odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ jaꞌ-a.

pairs.source: 49	But when they saw him walking upon the sea, they supposed it had been a spirit, and cried out:
pairs.target:
49 Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ ningaꞌ Iyoh ponu deꞌ tun piꞌin, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ sakaꞌ nang inoh munua. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nang bogan-e.

pairs.source: 50	For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and saith unto them, Be of good cheer: it is I; be not afraid.
pairs.target:
50 Suaꞌ
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ gogoh duoh tolu takal-e ningaꞌ nang inoh Yesus.
Pak-e Yesus lasuꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Maꞌ tolu! Okuꞌ itih Yesus.”

pairs.source: 51	And he went up unto them into the ship; and the wind ceased: and they were sore amazed in themselves beyond measure, and wondered.
pairs.target:
51 Yesus moꞌ maꞌad kaang olud duoh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, sobak moꞌ lasuꞌ
loꞌo, pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ sukup ilan-e.

pairs.source: 52	For they considered not [the miracle] of the loaves: for their heart was hardened.
pairs.target:
52 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ aluaꞌ geh
diꞌ-e ngiloti-e, takal-e ningaꞌ Yesus maꞌan nyaꞌa limoh libu naꞌan pakai
limoh kiping kueh, duoh pakai duwoh polong ikian, sobab otin odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ madod.

pairs.source: 53	And when they had passed over, they came into the land of Gennesaret, and drew to the shore.
pairs.target:
53 Takal Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ nog polad donu, Iyoh moꞌ
maꞌad keꞌ doyoh keꞌ topat deꞌ adon Genesaret.

pairs.source: 54	And when they were come out of the ship, straightway they knew him,
pairs.target: 54 Takal Yesus moꞌ maꞌad  soꞌ aang olud, nyaꞌa moꞌ lasuꞌ piluh nang Yoh Yesus.

pairs.source: 55	And ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in beds those that were sick, where they heard he was.
pairs.target:
55 Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ bikoduh keꞌ boli-boli nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ topat inoh. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ bitawiak toban nyaꞌa deꞌ monam deꞌ tun tilam yohmoꞌ toban tuduꞌ
Yesus. Daki sijaꞌ-e soꞌ Yesus odi takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ puꞌan-e, yoh lasuꞌ
toban nyaꞌa deꞌ monam tuduꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 56	And whithersoever he entered, into villages, or cities, or country, they laid the sick in the streets, and besought him that they might touch if it were but the border of his garment: and as many as touched him were made whole.
pairs.target:
56 Daki sijaꞌ-e Yesus odi, bait deꞌ kota, deꞌ
kupuaꞌ-kupuaꞌ deꞌ ayuh, duoh kupuaꞌ-kupuaꞌ deꞌ isit. Nyaꞌa silalu toban
ulang deꞌ monam piguling deꞌ topat nyaꞌa bijua, mitiaꞌ masiꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus
kadu-e tomaꞌ tubon jubah-E sijaꞌ-e. Yohmoꞌ suaꞌ odop-e deꞌ monam deꞌ
tomaꞌ tubon jubah Yesus mokuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 1	Then came together unto him the Pharisees, and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem.
pairs.target:
1  Ogiꞌ onu, takal kudu-kudu naꞌan ulang Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi
duoh kudu-kudu naꞌan gulu agama Yahudi soꞌ Yerusalem odi bitapod
duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: 2	And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread with defiled, that is to say, with unwashen, hands, they found fault.
pairs.target:
2 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ningaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus man
pakai tongan-e deꞌ koꞌis, diꞌ-e mamiaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 3	For the Pharisees, and all the Jews, except they wash [their] hands oft, eat not, holding the tradition of the elders.
pairs.target:
3 Dop-e suaꞌ ulang Yahudi yaꞌ diꞌ-e
man, moꞌ-e diꞌ-e mamiaꞌ tongan-e nunaꞌ adat sumuk babai-e. Amot-e ulang
Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi.

pairs.source: 4	And [when they come] from the market, except they wash, they eat not. And many other things there be, which they have received to hold, [as] the washing of cups, and pots, brasen vessels, and of tables.
pairs.target:
4 Yoh diꞌ-e soꞌon man oniꞌ deꞌ milih-e soꞌ
pasal, moꞌ-e aluaꞌ diꞌ-e mamuh. Bogoꞌ lagiꞌ adat sumuk babai-e deꞌ halus
yoh nunaꞌ-e, kodaꞌ mamiaꞌ sakil makup duoh balang-balang deꞌ soꞌ tibaga.

pairs.source: 5	Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him, Why walk not thy disciples according to the tradition of the elders, but eat bread with unwashen hands?
pairs.target:
5 Noh leh ngan uluk ulang Farisi duoh gulu-gulu agama Yahudi sikian tuduꞌ
Yesus, “Oni nai pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Muꞌ man diꞌ-e mamiaꞌ tongan-e? Oni nai-e
diꞌ-e nunaꞌ atulan adat sumuk babai otoꞌ?”

pairs.source: 6	He answered and said unto them, Well hath Esaias prophesied of you hypocrites, as it is written, This people honoureth me with [their] lips, but their heart is far from me.
pairs.target:
6 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Oi ulang deꞌ suka pulaꞌ-pulaꞌ! Tutuas kodaꞌ deꞌ
nang Topaꞌ pakai nabi Yesaya noꞌuh-e deꞌ in-e,
‘Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ jok-e nyomah Okuꞌ deꞌ bobaꞌ-e,
pak-e daang otin-e idoh.

pairs.source: 7	Howbeit in vain do they worship me, teaching [for] doctrines the commandments of men.
pairs.target:
7 Doiꞌ guna-e yoh nyomah Okuꞌ,
dop-e yoh jok-e ngajal atulan adat deꞌ nai manusia.’
Inoh leh deꞌ moꞌ tanon-e.

pairs.source: 8	For laying aside the commandment of God, ye hold the tradition of men, [as] the washing of pots and cups: and many other such like things ye do.
pairs.target:
8 Pilitah-pilitah deꞌ soꞌ Topaꞌ ingan togan-e, ingan
moꞌ ulih-ulih nunaꞌ atulan adat deꞌ nai manusia.”

pairs.source: 9	And he said unto them, Full well ye reject the commandment of God, that ye may keep your own tradition.
pairs.target:
9 Yesus moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Ponai manah geh ingan
nulak pilitah Topaꞌ, ngan ingan yaꞌ nunaꞌ atulan adat deꞌ nai manusia.

pairs.source: 10	For Moses said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and, Whoso curseth father or mother, let him die the death:
pairs.target:
10 Nabi Musa moꞌ ngin atulan wat tih, ‘Pimodo leh tuduꞌ samaꞌ sinoꞌ muꞌ,’
duoh ‘Osi deꞌ diꞌ-e pimodo duoh samaꞌ sinoꞌ-e, halus obuah ukum ngabos.’

pairs.source: 11	But ye say, If a man shall say to his father or mother, [It is] Corban, that is to say, a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me; [he shall be free].
pairs.target:
11 Pak-e ingan ngajal nang doiꞌ salah-e moꞌ ingan sina tuduꞌ pingoma ingan, ‘Doiꞌ kuꞌ tapod tulung ingan, dop-e suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ ngin kuꞌ tuduꞌ ingan
moꞌ ngin kuꞌ tuduꞌ Topaꞌ.’

pairs.source: 12	And ye suffer him no more to do ought for his father or his mother;
pairs.target:
12 Oniꞌ deꞌ ngajal ingan inoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa diꞌ-e
piduli pingoma-e.

pairs.source: 13	Making the word of God of none effect through your tradition, which ye have delivered: and many such like things do ye.
pairs.target:
13 Jadin ingan nang pilitah Topaꞌ diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ toga, pak-e
ingan moꞌ nunaꞌ atulan adat deꞌ nai manusia. Aluaꞌ bogoꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ kodaꞌ
itih deꞌ nai ingan.”

pairs.source: 14	And when he had called all the people [unto him], he said unto them, Hearken unto me every one [of you], and understand:
pairs.target:
14 Yesus moꞌ mogan nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ, Iyoh moꞌ sina tuduꞌ-e, “Ngojit dioꞌ
saꞌ ingan ngiloti-e!

pairs.source: 15	There is nothing from without a man, that entering into him can defile him: but the things which come out of him, those are they that defile the man.
pairs.target:
15 Suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ molot kaang polong nyaꞌa, doiꞌ deꞌ odaꞌ
nyaꞌa koꞌis, pak-e suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ luah soꞌ polong nyaꞌa inoh leh deꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa
koꞌis.

pairs.source: 16	If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.
pairs.target: 16 Osi deꞌ ogiꞌ kojit-e, iyoh ngojit-e!”

pairs.source: 17	And when he was entered into the house from the people, his disciples asked him concerning the parable.
pairs.target:
17 Yesus moꞌ buu togan nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ yohmoꞌ molot kaang boli,
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ sikian oni loti silita inoh.

pairs.source: 18	And he saith unto them, Are ye so without understanding also? Do ye not perceive, that whatsoever thing from without entereth into the man, [it] cannot defile him;
pairs.target:
18 Yesus moꞌ sina in-e tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, “Idoh keh diꞌ ingan
puꞌan-e, suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ molot kaang polong nyaꞌa, doiꞌ deꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa koꞌis?

pairs.source: 19	Because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly, and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats?
pairs.target:
19 Dop-e oniꞌ deꞌ man nyaꞌa diꞌ-e molot kaang otin nyaꞌa, pak-e molot kaang
toꞌin nyaꞌa, mokuaꞌ inoh nyaꞌa odi saꞌat keꞌ jaman.”
Yesus in inoh ngan-e tanon nang suaꞌ pinguman bisig, doiꞌ deꞌ polih
nyeꞌ man-e.

pairs.source: 20	And he said, That which cometh out of the man, that defileth the man.
pairs.target:
20 Yesus moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ, “Suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ luah soꞌ polong nyaꞌa inoh leh deꞌ
odaꞌ nyaꞌa koꞌis.

pairs.source: 21	For from within, out of the heart of men, proceed evil thoughts, adulteries, fornications, murders,
pairs.target:
21 Dop-e soꞌ aang otin nyaꞌa timul pikil deꞌ jaꞌat, idip kodaꞌ
sowon duoh bonon pak-e aluaꞌ diꞌ-e kawin, noku, ngabos,

pairs.source: 22	Thefts, covetousness, wickedness, deceit, lasciviousness, an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness:
pairs.target:
22 biamai, suaꞌ
oniꞌ yoh yaꞌ kakuꞌ-e, suka nai oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat, nipu, idip nunaꞌ kila odop-e
deꞌ jaꞌat, siniaꞌ, suka pijaꞌat nyaꞌa, samuh, liꞌiang bak-e.

pairs.source: 23	All these evil things come from within, and defile the man.
pairs.target: 23 Suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat inoh luah soꞌ aang otin nyaꞌa duoh kaꞌis odop-e.”

pairs.source: 24	And from thence he arose, and went into the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and entered into an house, and would have no man know [it]: but he could not be hid.
pairs.target:
24 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ buu soꞌ topat inoh yohmoꞌ odi keꞌ topat deꞌ
sinok kota Tirus. Iyoh molot kaang boli saꞌ-e doiꞌ nyaꞌa puꞌan-E. Pak-e Yoh
diꞌ-e ponai yaꞌ suan odop-E.

pairs.source: 25	For a [certain] woman, whose young daughter had an unclean spirit, heard of him, and came and fell at his feet:
pairs.target:
25 Ogiꞌ sinoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ onak dayung-e obuah
bikalui muat munua. Takal yoh moꞌ ngojit tentang Yesus, yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ
nog tuduꞌ-E yoh moꞌ bonal-bonal mitiaꞌ masiꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 26	The woman was a Greek, a Syrophenician by nation; and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil out of her daughter.
