pairs.target:
26 Iyoh mitiaꞌ
tulung tuduꞌ Yesus odaꞌ kasig muat munua soꞌ gonan onak-e. Dayung inoh
diꞌ-e ulang Yahudi. Iyoh soꞌ Fenisia deꞌ propinsi Siria.

pairs.source: 27	But Jesus said unto her, Let the children first be filled: for it is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast [it] unto the dogs.
pairs.target:
27 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Onak opot leh deꞌ dioꞌ nyeꞌ maꞌan-e, dop-e diꞌ-e
patut pinguman deꞌ yaꞌ ngin nyeꞌ tuduꞌ onak opot, nyeꞌ ngin deꞌ kosuang.”

pairs.source: 28	And she answered and said unto him, Yes, Lord: yet the dogs under the table eat of the children’s crumbs.
pairs.target:
28 Pak-e dayung inoh moꞌ nyawot-E, “Tok bonal oniꞌ deꞌ nang Ingan, pak-e
kosuang man-e geh puluh pinguman deꞌ luluh soꞌ tun mija.”

pairs.source: 29	And he said unto her, For this saying go thy way; the devil is gone out of thy daughter.
pairs.target:
29 Yesus moꞌ nyawot dayung inoh, “Dop-e muꞌu moꞌ nyawot in inoh,
paliꞌ negeh. Onak muꞌ moh moꞌ buu muat munua soꞌ gonan-e.”

pairs.source: 30	And when she was come to her house, she found the devil gone out, and her daughter laid upon the bed.
pairs.target:
30 Dayung inoh moꞌ buu. Nog boli-e, yoh moꞌ ningaꞌ onak-e guling deꞌ
topat boꞌos, dop-e muat munua moꞌ buu soꞌ gonan-e.

pairs.source: 31	And again, departing from the coasts of Tyre and Sidon, he came unto the sea of Galilee, through the midst of the coasts of Decapolis.
pairs.target:
31 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ buu soꞌ topat deꞌ
sinok kota Tirus, odi keꞌ donu Galilea ngilusuꞌ kota Sidon. Odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ moꞌ ponu keꞌ topat deꞌ nang nyaꞌa geh Simoong Kota.

pairs.source: 32	And they bring unto him one that was deaf, and had an impediment in his speech; and they beseech him to put his hand upon him.
pairs.target:
32 Takal-e
danoꞌ, kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa toban tuduꞌ Yesus niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ bongam
daang-e bebeꞌ. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ bonal-bonal mitiaꞌ odaꞌ Yesus tomaꞌ-e
saꞌ iyoh mokuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 33	And he took him aside from the multitude, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spit, and touched his tongue;
pairs.target:
33 Yesus moꞌ toban nyaꞌa inoh buu soꞌ uluk nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ,
duam odop-e duwoh jaꞌ-e. Yesus moꞌ tiluak pakai tilinyuꞌ-E soꞌ duwoh
lubang kojit nyaꞌa inoh. Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ ngujaꞌ deꞌ lupaꞌ tongan
odop-E duoh gasak loyang-E deꞌ jolaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bebeꞌ inoh.

pairs.source: 34	And looking up to heaven, he sighed, and saith unto him, Ephphatha, that is, Be opened.
pairs.target:
34 Mokuaꞌ inoh
Yesus moꞌ bigalong keꞌ longit daang-e nalik asong-E, yohmoꞌ sina tuduꞌ
nyaꞌa inoh, “Efata,” loti-e, “Tibukaꞌ mey!”

pairs.source: 35	And straightway his ears were opened, and the string of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plain.
pairs.target:
35 Takal inoh geh yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ
ponai ngojit, jolaꞌ-e moꞌ lasuꞌ dodot yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ ponai sina.

pairs.source: 36	And he charged them that they should tell no man: but the more he charged them, so much the more a great deal they published [it];
pairs.target:
36 Yesus moꞌ sibaya tuduꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ jaman kilakal tuduꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon. Pak-e makin Yesus jaman-e, makin nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ silita
katiꞌ kanih.

pairs.source: 37	And were beyond measure astonished, saying, He hath done all things well: he maketh both the deaf to hear, and the dumb to speak.
pairs.target:
37 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngojit gah inoh moꞌ ilan-e. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ in-e, “Paguh manah suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ nai-E. Nyaꞌa deꞌ bongam ponai ngojit,
duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ bebeꞌ ponai sina.”

pairs.source: 1	In those days the multitude being very great, and having nothing to eat, Jesus called his disciples [unto him], and saith unto them,
pairs.target:
1 Kudu-kudu onu mokuaꞌ inoh, ogiꞌ bilibu nyaꞌa nog baꞌuh tuduꞌ
Yesus. Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ doiꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ man-e. Yesus moꞌ mogan
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E yohmoꞌ in-e,

pairs.source: 2	I have compassion on the multitude, because they have now been with me three days, and have nothing to eat:
pairs.target:
2 “Masiꞌ nyam Kuꞌ tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ
itih neh. Moꞌ taluh onu yoh bitunaꞌ duoh Okuꞌ, moꞌ doiꞌ oni-oni deꞌ yaꞌ
man-e tiyaꞌ.

pairs.source: 3	And if I send them away fasting to their own houses, they will faint by the way: for divers of them came from far.
pairs.target:
3 Simoꞌ Kuꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ mutiꞌ paliꞌ toban toꞌin-e deꞌ pilai,
jak-e ogiꞌ deꞌ pisan deꞌ olan, dop-e ogiꞌ odop-e deꞌ mutiꞌ deꞌ nog soꞌ juuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 4	And his disciples answered him, From whence can a man satisfy these [men] with bread here in the wilderness?
pairs.target:
4 Pak-e pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-e moꞌ nyawot-e, “Daki soꞌ toꞌ yaꞌ kalik pinguman
deꞌ sukup saꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ kiang-kiang itih? Topat itih juuaꞌ soꞌ kupuaꞌ soꞌ
nyeꞌ yaꞌ milih pinguman.”

pairs.source: 5	And he asked them, How many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven.
pairs.target:
5 In Yesus sikian tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Oni kiang kueh deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ
ingan?” Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-e, “Ogiꞌ juꞌ kiping kueh.”

pairs.source: 6	And he commanded the people to sit down on the ground: and he took the seven loaves, and gave thanks, and brake, and gave to his disciples to set before [them]; and they did set [them] before the people.
pairs.target:
6 Yesus moꞌ odaꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ guluꞌ deꞌ tanaꞌ. Yesus moꞌ mit kueh
deꞌ juꞌ kiping inoh, yohmoꞌ bisukul tuduꞌ Topaꞌ. Yoh moꞌ nyipiak-nyipiak
kueh inoh, yohmoꞌ ngin tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E odaꞌ bikutung tuduꞌ suaꞌ
nyaꞌa.

pairs.source: 7	And they had a few small fishes: and he blessed, and commanded to set them also before [them].
pairs.target:
7 Ogiꞌ geh kudu-kudu polong ikian deꞌ toban odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.
Yesus moꞌ mit ikian yohmoꞌ bisukul tuduꞌ Topaꞌ, Yoh moꞌ ngin tuduꞌ
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E odaꞌ bikutung tuduꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa.

pairs.source: 8	So they did eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken [meat] that was left seven baskets.
pairs.target:
8 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa man nog
busuah-e. Mokuaꞌ inoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ nguluk kuban nyaꞌa man-e,
aluaꞌ ogiꞌ duam juꞌ bakul.

pairs.source: 9	And they that had eaten were about four thousand: and he sent them away.
pairs.target:
9 Odop-e deꞌ man inoh ogiꞌ kulang lobih pat libu
naꞌan. Mokuaꞌ man, Yesus moꞌ odaꞌ buu paliꞌ.

pairs.source: 10	And straightway he entered into a ship with his disciples, and came into the parts of Dalmanutha.
pairs.target:
10 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E lasuꞌ muat daang olud, yohmoꞌ odi keꞌ Dalmanuta.

pairs.source: 11	And the Pharisees came forth, and began to question with him, seeking of him a sign from heaven, tempting him.
pairs.target:
11 Kudu-kudu ulang Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi nog bikalah duoh Yesus, odaꞌ Yesus bitanga kuasa-E nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa, deꞌ jadin tanda nang
Iyoh tok obuah pait soꞌ Topaꞌ, saꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ dapod kalik wat olan
ngan-e nyalah Yesus.

pairs.source: 12	And he sighed deeply in his spirit, and saith, Why doth this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, There shall no sign be given unto this generation.
pairs.target:
12 Yesus moꞌ nalik asong-E omu-omu-e daang in-e,
“Aah, oni nai nyaꞌa joman deꞌ adin bigaꞌan mitiaꞌ tanda? Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ
ingan: Idoh diꞌ Kuꞌ bitanga kuasa nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa tuduꞌ ingan neh!”

pairs.source: 13	And he left them, and entering into the ship again departed to the other side.
pairs.target: 13 Yesus moꞌ buu togan odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ odi keꞌ polad donu inoh.

pairs.source: 14	Now [the disciples] had forgotten to take bread, neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.
pairs.target:
14 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus komut toban kueh, jok-e ogiꞌ niꞌ kiping kueh
daang olud, Yesus sibaya tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E,
daang olud.
in-E, “Maꞌ tauꞌ-tauꞌ duoh ragi ulang Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi duoh ragi
Laja Herodes.”

pairs.source: 15	And he charged them, saying, Take heed, beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, and [of] the leaven of Herod.
pairs.target: 15 Takal-e

pairs.source: 16	And they reasoned among themselves, saying, [It is] because we have no bread.
pairs.target:
16 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus moꞌ bolipotak si odop-e in-e, “Yoh sina in inoh
saai otoꞌ diꞌ toꞌ toban kueh, yoh ngan-e in inoh.”

pairs.source: 17	And when Jesus knew [it], he saith unto them, Why reason ye, because ye have no bread? perceive ye not yet, neither understand? have ye your heart yet hardened?
pairs.target:
17 Yesus moꞌ puꞌan oniꞌ deꞌ sobot odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, Iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Maꞌ
bigaduh nang doiꞌ kueh deꞌ toban toꞌ! Idoh diꞌ-e wat inoh wat-e oniꞌ deꞌ
nang Kuꞌ! Madod manah pikil ingan ngan diꞌ ingan dapod ngiloti!

pairs.source: 18	Having eyes, see ye not? and having ears, hear ye not? and do ye not remember?
pairs.target:
18 Boton
ingan ogiꞌ, pak-e ingan kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ. Kojit ingan ogiꞌ geh, pak-e
ingan kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bongam. Podo idoh diꞌ ingan natong-e,

pairs.source: 19	When I brake the five loaves among five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? They say unto him, Twelve.
pairs.target:
19 takal Okuꞌ
nyipiak limoh kiping kueh saꞌan limoh libu naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ man, duam
kudu kuban-e?”
Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ nyawot-e, “Duam simoong duwoh bakul.”

pairs.source: 20	And when the seven among four thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? And they said, Seven.
pairs.target:
20 “Takal juꞌ kiping kueh saꞌan pat libu naꞌan nyaꞌa, duam kudu kuban-e?”
Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-e, “Duam juꞌ bakul punuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 21	And he said unto them, How is it that ye do not understand?
pairs.target:
21 Yoh moꞌ in-e lagi tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Podo aluaꞌ geh diꞌ ingan
ngiloti-e?”

pairs.source: 22	And he cometh to Bethsaida; and they bring a blind man unto him, and besought him to touch him.
pairs.target:
22 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E nog keꞌ kota Betsaida,
kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa toban ulang deꞌ butaꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus. Yohmoꞌ mitiaꞌ
masiꞌ odaꞌ Yesus tomaꞌ ulang deꞌ butaꞌ inoh saꞌ-e tapod ningaꞌ.

pairs.source: 23	And he took the blind man by the hand, and led him out of the town; and when he had spit on his eyes, and put his hands upon him, he asked him if he saw ought.
pairs.target:
23 Yesus moꞌ
kagong tongan-e, yohmoꞌ kayak toban luah soꞌ kota inoh. Yesus moꞌ ngujaꞌ
duoh tomaꞌ soꞌ duwoh boton nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ inoh. Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ
sikian tuduꞌ-e, “Podo muꞌu moꞌ ponai kilin oniꞌ?”

pairs.source: 24	And he looked up, and said, I see men as trees, walking.
pairs.target:
24 Nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ inoh moꞌ ningaꞌ keꞌ jowin, yohmoꞌ in-e, “Okuꞌ moꞌ
ponai ningaꞌ nyaꞌa ponu, pak-e mun sibamia tongon koyuh mun-e.”

pairs.source: 25	After that he put [his] hands again upon his eyes, and made him look up: and he was restored, and saw every man clearly.
pairs.target:
25 Yesus moꞌ tomaꞌ baꞌuh boton nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ inoh. Mokuaꞌ inoh ke yoh
moꞌ tapod ningaꞌ sukup telang-e, dop-e boton-e moꞌ paguh.

pairs.source: 26	And he sent him away to his house, saying, Neither go into the town, nor tell [it] to any in the town.
pairs.target:
26 Yesus moꞌ
odaꞌ iyoh paliꞌ keꞌ boli-e, Iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Maꞌ yaꞌ nosaꞌ keꞌ kota Betsaida.”

pairs.source: 27	And Jesus went out, and his disciples, into the towns of Caesarea Philippi: and by the way he asked his disciples, saying unto them, Whom do men say that I am?
pairs.target:
27 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E odi keꞌ kupuaꞌ-kupuaꞌ deꞌ
ogiꞌ deꞌ sinok kota Kaisarea Filipi. Takal-e aluaꞌ daang pimonu-e Yesus
sikian tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, in-E, “Moꞌ-e nunaꞌ deꞌ sobot nyaꞌa, osi Okuꞌ
tih?”

pairs.source: 28	And they answered, John the Baptist: but some [say], Elias; and others, One of the prophets.
pairs.target:
28 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-e, “Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa nang Yohanes Pembaptis,
ogiꞌ geh nyaꞌa nang nabi Elia, ogiꞌ geh nyaꞌa deꞌ nang Ingan nabi deꞌ bokon.”

pairs.source: 29	And he saith unto them, But whom say ye that I am? And Peter answereth and saith unto him, Thou art the Christ.
pairs.target:
29 Pak-e Yesus sikian tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ lagiꞌ, “Moꞌ-e nunaꞌ pikil
ingan osi odop-e Okuꞌ itih?”
Petrus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Ingan leh Laja Pinyilamat deꞌ pait Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 30	And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.
pairs.target:
30 Yesus moꞌ sibaya tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E jaman tanon tuduꞌ osi sijaꞌ-e,
nang odop-E inoh leh Laja Pinyilamat.

pairs.source: 31	And he began to teach them, that the Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected of the elders, and [of] the chief priests, and scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again.
pairs.target:
31 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ tanon tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E nang odop-E
Onak Manusia deꞌ halus idip susah jolaꞌ. Iyoh obuah netang odaꞌ
pimipin-pimipin ulang Yahudi, pimipin-pimipin agama deꞌ ayuh, duoh
gulu-gulu agama. Odop-e deꞌ mutiꞌ leh deꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa ngabos Onak Manusia
inoh, pak-e takal mokuaꞌ taluh onu Onak manusia paliꞌ mokat idip.

pairs.source: 32	And he spake that saying openly. And Peter took him, and began to rebuke him.
pairs.target:
32 Yesus
moꞌ telang-telang tanon suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ yaꞌ obuah odop-E. Pak-e Petrus
moꞌ toban Yesus keꞌ tuak tanaꞌ yoh moꞌ jaman nang sina deꞌ in inoh.

pairs.source: 33	But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples, he rebuked Peter, saying, Get thee behind me, Satan: for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but the things that be of men.
pairs.target:
33 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ kos odop-e ningaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E deꞌ bokon. Iyoh
moꞌ ngalah Petrus daang-e in-e, “Buu muꞌu Laja Muat munua! Muꞌu diꞌ muꞌ
piduli oniꞌ deꞌ laꞌan Topaꞌ, muꞌu jok muꞌ piduli oniꞌ deꞌ laꞌan manusia.”

pairs.source: 34	And when he had called the people [unto him] with his disciples also, he said unto them, Whosoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.
pairs.target:
34 Yesus moꞌ mogan pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ deꞌ ogiꞌ
danoꞌ. Yoh moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ yaꞌ nunaꞌ Okuꞌ,
iyoh halus lawan kila-e, siap idip jolaꞌ kodaꞌ Okuꞌ, yohmoꞌ nah-nah nunaꞌ
Okuꞌ.

pairs.source: 35	For whosoever will save his life shall lose it; but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel’s, the same shall save it.
pairs.target:
35 Dop-e osi deꞌ ngibalaꞌ asong-e iyoh diꞌ-e soꞌon idip soꞌ Topaꞌ. Pak-e
osi deꞌ tumut asong-e ngan-e nunaꞌ Okuꞌ duoh magah Gah deꞌ Paguh, iyoh
deꞌ soꞌon idip deꞌ soꞌ Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 36	For what shall it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul?
pairs.target:
36 Nai oni ingan kakuꞌ suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ ogiꞌ daang
dunia, pak-e diꞌ ingan soꞌon idip deꞌ baꞌuh duoh Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 37	Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?
pairs.target:
37 Dop-e doiꞌ oniꞌ
deꞌ dunia itih deꞌ tapod ngan ingan yaꞌ milih idip deꞌ baꞌuh duoh Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 38	Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation; of him also shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he cometh in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.
pairs.target:
38 Dop-e osi deꞌ dasaꞌ ngakuꞌ Okuꞌ duoh oniꞌ deꞌ ngajal kuꞌ deꞌ uun
manusia deꞌ suka nai dosa duoh diꞌ-e taat tuduꞌ Topaꞌ, Okuꞌ, Onak Manusia
tuang dasaꞌ geh ngakuꞌ iyoh, takal Kuꞌ nog daang kuasa Samaꞌ Kuꞌ baya
ayua malaikat soꞌ Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 1	And he said unto them, Verily I say unto you, That there be some of them that stand here, which shall not taste of death, till they have seen the kingdom of God come with power.
pairs.target:
1 Yesus tanon lagiꞌ tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan:
Ogiꞌ soꞌ ingan deꞌ mutiꞌ deꞌ aluaꞌ totap idip nog Topaꞌ bitanga odop-E
jadin Laja deꞌ punuaꞌ kuasa-E.”

pairs.source: 2	And after six days Jesus taketh [with him] Peter, and James, and John, and leadeth them up into an high mountain apart by themselves: and he was transfigured before them.
pairs.target:
2 Mokuaꞌ nuam onu, Yesus toban Petrus, Yakobus duoh Yohanes maꞌad
keꞌ tun dolod deꞌ bigatung saꞌ-e juuaꞌ soꞌ nyaꞌa. Takal-e moꞌ deꞌ tun dolod
Yesus moꞌ bilubah jawaꞌ jowin-E.

pairs.source: 3	And his raiment became shining, exceeding white as snow; so as no fuller on earth can white them.
pairs.target:
3 Pimakai-E moꞌ jadin mopuꞌ bikilap. Doiꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ daang dunia itih deꞌ tapod mamiaꞌ pimakai-e odaꞌ mopuꞌ mun
inoh.

pairs.source: 4	And there appeared unto them Elias with Moses: and they were talking with Jesus.
pairs.target:
4 Odop-e deꞌ taluh moꞌ ningaꞌ nabi Elia duoh nabi Musa sina duoh
Yesus.

pairs.source: 5	And Peter answered and said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: and let us make three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.
pairs.target:
5 Petrus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ Yesus, “Gulu, tok-tok nyam doon-e koꞌih deꞌ
topat itih neh. Oni wat-e moꞌ koꞌih nai taluh galang, niꞌ saꞌan Ingan, niꞌ
saꞌan Musa, niꞌ saꞌan Elia.”

pairs.source: 6	For he wist not what to say; for they were sore afraid.
pairs.target:
6 Petrus nang sina deꞌ in inoh, iyoh diꞌ-e puꞌan
oni deꞌ yaꞌ nang-e, dop-e yoh sukup tolu-e.

pairs.source: 7	And there was a cloud that overshadowed them: and a voice came out of the cloud, saying, This is my beloved Son: hear him.
pairs.target:
7 Mokuaꞌ inoh abun moꞌ muun deꞌ tun odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ. Yoh moꞌ ngojit
sina soꞌ aang abun inoh deꞌ in-e, “Itihleh Onak Kuꞌ deꞌ sukup Kuꞌ ngibalaꞌ,
ngojit leh oniꞌ deꞌ tanon-E.”

pairs.source: 8	And suddenly, when they had looked round about, they saw no man any more, save Jesus only with themselves.
pairs.target:
8 Tang-tang takal odop-e deꞌ taluh kumiat katiꞌ
kanih, doiꞌ-e nak ogiꞌ osi-osi danoꞌ, jok-e ogiꞌ Yesus sijaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 9	And as they came down from the mountain, he charged them that they should tell no man what things they had seen, till the Son of man were risen from the dead.
pairs.target:
9 Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ muun soꞌ tun dolod, Yesus sibaya tuduꞌ odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ saꞌ-e diꞌ-e silita duoh osi-osi-e oniꞌ deꞌ ningaꞌ-e, nog Onak Manusia
paliꞌ idip lagiꞌ.

pairs.source: 10	And they kept that saying with themselves, questioning one with another what the rising from the dead should mean.
pairs.target:
10 Odop-e deꞌ taluh inoh moꞌ nyikon sibaya inoh daang otin-e, pak-e
odop-e deꞌ taluh mulai kilakal oni loti oniꞌ deꞌ nang-E, “Paliꞌ idip lagiꞌ.”

pairs.source: 11	And they asked him, saying, Why say the scribes that Elias must first come?
pairs.target:
11 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ sikian tuduꞌ Yesus, “Oni nai gulu-gulu agama Yahudi
nang Elia yaꞌ dioꞌ nog?”

pairs.source: 12	And he answered and told them, Elias verily cometh first, and restoreth all things; and how it is written of the Son of man, that he must suffer many things, and be set at nought.
pairs.target:
12 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Elia tok dioꞌ nog, nai suaꞌ oniꞌ odaꞌ paliꞌ paguh.
Pak-e oni nai-e ogiꞌ sina daang Kitab deꞌ nang Onak Manusia yaꞌ susah
jolaꞌ duoh obuah nulak?

pairs.source: 13	But I say unto you, That Elias is indeed come, and they have done unto him whatsoever they listed, as it is written of him.
pairs.target:
13 Pak-e Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan: Elia moꞌ bilasa
nog, nyaꞌa moꞌ adoh-adoh wat-e duoh-e samah kodaꞌ daang Kitab.”

pairs.source: 14	And when he came to [his] disciples, he saw a great multitude about them, and the scribes questioning with them.
pairs.target:
14 Takal Yesus, Petrus, Yakobus duoh Yohanes muun soꞌ dolod, odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ningaꞌ bogoꞌ nyaꞌa ngubun pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus deꞌ bokon.
Ogiꞌ geh kudu-kudu naꞌan gulu agama Yahudi deꞌ bikalah duoh odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 15	And straightway all the people, when they beheld him, were greatly amazed, and running to [him] saluted him.
pairs.target:
15 Takal nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ inoh ningaꞌ Yesus yoh moꞌ sukup nyam-e
ilan-e, yoh moꞌ bikoduh odi ngumaꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 16	And he asked the scribes, What question ye with them?
pairs.target:
16 Yesus moꞌ bisikian tuduꞌ odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ, “Oni deꞌ bikalah ingan duoh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ?”

pairs.source: 17	And one of the multitude answered and said, Master, I have brought unto thee my son, which hath a dumb spirit;
pairs.target:
17 Ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ uluk odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-E, “Gulu, okuꞌ
toban onak kuꞌ tuduꞌ Ingan. Iyoh obuah nguasa muat munua deꞌ odaꞌ yoh   
bebeꞌ.

pairs.source: 18	And wheresoever he taketh him, he teareth him: and he foameth, and gnasheth with his teeth, and pineth away: and I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out; and they could not.
pairs.target:
18 Asal muat munua nyelang gonan-e, yoh moꞌ paan-paan gonan-e
keꞌ tanaꞌ, loyang-e bijulak luah soꞌ bobaꞌ-e, daang jipon-e obuaꞌ bitatuak,
gonan-e moꞌ nisuk. Okuꞌ mitiaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Ingan odaꞌ kasig muat
munua inoh, pak-e diꞌ-e taan kasig-e.”

pairs.source: 19	He answereth him, and saith, O faithless generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I suffer you? bring him unto me.
pairs.target:
19 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Ingan deꞌ mutiꞌ tok-tok diꞌ
ingan bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Topaꞌ! Oni tian Kuꞌ yaꞌ loꞌo duoh sabal tuduꞌ ingan?
Toban onak dali inoh katiꞌ!”

pairs.source: 20	And they brought him unto him: and when he saw him, straightway the spirit tare him; and he fell on the ground, and wallowed foaming.
pairs.target:
20 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ toban onak dali inoh
tuduꞌ Yesus. Takal muat munua inoh moꞌ ningaꞌ Yesus, yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ odaꞌ
gonan onak dali inoh nisuk. Onak dali inoh moꞌ lasuꞌ tumang bigulai-gulai
deꞌ tanaꞌ daang loyang-e bijulak luah soꞌ bobaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 21	And he asked his father, How long is it ago since this came unto him? And he said, Of a child.
pairs.target:
21 Yesus moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ
samaꞌ onak dali inoh, “Moꞌ oni tian-e yoh obuah oniꞌ deꞌ wat itih?”
Samaꞌ-e moꞌ nyawot-e, “Soꞌ isoꞌ-e geh.

pairs.source: 22	And ofttimes it hath cast him into the fire, and into the waters, to destroy him: but if thou canst do any thing, have compassion on us, and help us.
pairs.target:
22 Moꞌ bogoꞌ sidoh-e muat munua
yaꞌ ngabos-e, odaꞌ tolan odop-e kaang opui, duoh odaꞌ tolan odop-e kaang
piꞌin. Simoꞌ Ingan tapod odaꞌ onak dali itih mokuaꞌ, Ingan masiꞌ leh, duoh
Ingan tulung leh koꞌih.”

pairs.source: 23	Jesus said unto him, If thou canst believe, all things [are] possible to him that believeth.
pairs.target:
23 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ-e, “Oni nai muꞌ sina: ‘Simoꞌ Ingan tapod?’ Doiꞌ
oniꞌ deꞌ diꞌ-e tapod saꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ bisayaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 24	And straightway the father of the child cried out, and said with tears, Lord, I believe; help thou mine unbelief.
pairs.target:
24 Samaꞌ onak dali inoh moꞌ lasuꞌ nang sina-e dolas-dolas, “Okuꞌ bisayaꞌ!
Pak-e aluaꞌ kulang. Tulung leh odaꞌ okuꞌ bisayaꞌ lobih lagiꞌ!”

pairs.source: 25	When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit, saying unto him, [Thou] dumb and deaf spirit, I charge thee, come out of him, and enter no more into him.
pairs.target:
25 Takal Yesus ningaꞌ makin bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nog bikubun, Yesus moꞌ
nyingak muat munua inoh daang-E sina duoh-e, “Buu! Muat deꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa
itih bongam duoh bebeꞌ! Okuꞌ odaꞌ muꞌu luah soꞌ onak dali itih duoh maꞌ
tiyaꞌ paliꞌ nguasa onak dali itih!”

pairs.source: 26	And [the spirit] cried, and rent him sore, and came out of him: and he was as one dead; insomuch that many said, He is dead.
pairs.target:
26 Muat munua inoh moꞌ nang bogan-e, yoh moꞌ odaꞌ suaꞌ gonan onak
dali inoh nisuk. Mokuaꞌ inoh muat munua moꞌ lasuꞌ buu luah soꞌ gonan
onak dali inoh. Onak dali inoh moꞌ mun nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ kobos mun-e, iyoh
leh ngan nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ in-e, “Iyoh moꞌ kobos.”

pairs.source: 27	But Jesus took him by the hand, and lifted him up; and he arose.
pairs.target:
27 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ
kagian tongan-e, Yoh moꞌ tulung odaꞌ mokat. Onak dali inoh moꞌ lasuꞌ
mokat.

pairs.source: 28	And when he was come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, Why could not we cast him out?
pairs.target:
28 Takal Yesus moꞌ daang boli, duam Yoh duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sikian, in-e, “Oni nai koꞌih diꞌ taan odaꞌ muat munua inoh
buu soꞌ onak dali inoh?”

pairs.source: 29	And he said unto them, This kind can come forth by nothing, but by prayer and fasting.
pairs.target:
29 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Muat munua deꞌ basa inoh jok toꞌ tapod kasig
pakai bidoa.”

pairs.source: 30	And they departed thence, and passed through Galilee; and he would not that any man should know [it].
pairs.target:
30 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ buu togan topat inoh ngilusuꞌ
Galilea. Yoh doliaꞌ-e odaꞌ nyaꞌa puꞌan soꞌ-e loꞌo,

pairs.source: 31	For he taught his disciples, and said unto them, The Son of man is delivered into the hands of men, and they shall kill him; and after that he is killed, he shall rise the third day.
pairs.target:
31 dop-e Yoh yaꞌ ngajal
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E jaꞌ-e. Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Onak Manusia yaꞌ obuah nyelah
tuduꞌ ulang-ulang deꞌ jaꞌat, yoh moꞌ ngabos-e, pak-e mokuaꞌ taluh onu Yoh
paliꞌ mokat idip.”

pairs.source: 32	But they understood not that saying, and were afraid to ask him.
pairs.target:
32 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E diꞌ-e ngiloti oni loti sina deꞌ nang Yesus inoh, pak-e
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ tolu yaꞌ sikian-e.

pairs.source: 33	And he came to Capernaum: and being in the house he asked them, What was it that ye disputed among yourselves by the way?
pairs.target:
33 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ nog keꞌ Kapernaum. Takal-e moꞌ
nog kaang boli, Yesus moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, “Oni deꞌ kilakal
ingan daang olan tiꞌ-e?”

pairs.source: 34	But they held their peace: for by the way they had disputed among themselves, who [should be] the greatest.
pairs.target:
34 Pak-e suaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ doiꞌ deꞌ nyawot, dop-e daang olan odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ bikalah osi deꞌ paling ayuh soꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 35	And he sat down, and called the twelve, and saith unto them, If any man desire to be first, [the same] shall be last of all, and servant of all.
pairs.target:
35 Yesus moꞌ
guluꞌ, yohmoꞌ mogan soꞌ simoong duwoh pinunaꞌ-E deꞌ sobot-E nang rasul.
Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Nyaꞌa deꞌ laꞌan jadin nomol niꞌ, yoh mesti jadin deꞌ paling
piobuaꞌ-e duoh jadin kuli nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 36	And he took a child, and set him in the midst of them: and when he had taken him in his arms, he said unto them,
pairs.target:
36 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ mit
onak opot deꞌ aluaꞌ isoꞌ, yohmoꞌ posan deꞌ uun odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, simadi-e
pakuaꞌ onak opot inoh Yesus moꞌ in-e,

pairs.source: 37	Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name, receiveth me: and whosoever shall receive me, receiveth not me, but him that sent me.
pairs.target:
37 “Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ nyamut onak opot
kodaꞌ itih, ngan yoh bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Okuꞌ, samah geh iyoh tilimaꞌ Okuꞌ. Osi
deꞌ tilimaꞌ Okuꞌ, yoh tilimaꞌ geh Topaꞌ deꞌ pait Okuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 38	And John answered him, saying, Master, we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and he followeth not us: and we forbad him, because he followeth not us.
pairs.target:
38 Yohanes moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ Yesus, “Gulu, koꞌih ningaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ diꞌ-e nunaꞌ otoꞌ kasig muat munua pakai adon Ingan. Koꞌih moꞌ jaman-e, dop-e yoh
diꞌ-e nunaꞌ otoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 39	But Jesus said, Forbid him not: for there is no man which shall do a miracle in my name, that can lightly speak evil of me.
pairs.target:
39 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ in-e, “Maꞌ yaꞌ jaman-e, dop-e niꞌ naꞌan
tuang doiꞌ geh deꞌ tapod nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa pakai adon Okuꞌ, mokuaꞌ
inoh yoh lasuꞌ pijaꞌat adon Okuꞌ.

pairs.source: 40	For he that is not against us is on our part.
pairs.target: 40 Osi deꞌ diꞌ-e netang otoꞌ, iyoh nuaꞌ otoꞌ.

pairs.source: 41	For whosoever shall give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because ye belong to Christ, verily I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward.
pairs.target:
41 Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan: Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ ngin nuak niꞌ sakil piꞌin tuduꞌ
ingan, ngan ingan jadin pinunaꞌ Laja Pinyilamat, yoh totap soꞌon upah-e.”

pairs.source: 42	And whosoever shall offend one of [these] little ones that believe in me, it is better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he were cast into the sea.
pairs.target:
42 Yesus lanyut sina-e, “Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ odaꞌ niꞌ naꞌan onak opot diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ
bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Okuꞌ, lobih paguh nyeꞌ gutan batuh deꞌ ayuh deꞌ baat deꞌ
tunguaꞌ-e, nyeꞌ moꞌ tolan kaang laut.

pairs.source: 43	And if thy hand offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter into life maimed, than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:
pairs.target:
43 Simoꞌ tongan muꞌ deꞌ odaꞌ muꞌu
nai oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat, lobih paguh muꞌ kopog-e! Dop-e lobih paguh doiꞌ tongan
muꞌ niꞌ kawa, pak-e idip deꞌ baꞌuh duoh Topaꞌ deꞌ siluga. Nai oni ogiꞌ soꞌ
duwoh tongan muꞌ, pak-e obuah tolan kaang neraka deꞌ opui-e diꞌ-e ponai
pulaꞌ?

pairs.source: 44	Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
pairs.target: 44 Deꞌ neraka olod-e diꞌ-e ponai kobos, opui-e diꞌ-e ponai pulaꞌ.

pairs.source: 45	And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:
pairs.target:
45 Simoꞌ poꞌon muꞌ deꞌ odaꞌ muꞌu nai oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat, lobih paguh muꞌ
kopog-e, dop-e lobih paguh muꞌ bojang pak-e idip deꞌ baꞌuh duoh Topaꞌ.
Nai oni ogiꞌ soꞌ duwoh poꞌon muꞌ pak-e obuah tolan kaang neraka?

pairs.source: 46	Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
pairs.target:
46 Deꞌ
neraka olod-e diꞌ-e ponai kobos, opui-e diꞌ-e ponai pulaꞌ.

pairs.source: 47	And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out: it is better for thee to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire:
pairs.target:
47 Simoꞌ boton muꞌ deꞌ odaꞌ muꞌu nai oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat, tukiat kadi-e. Lobih
paguh muꞌu molot keꞌ siluga pakai boton niꞌ. Nai oni ogiꞌ soꞌ duwoh boton
muꞌ, pak-e obuah tolan kaang neraka?

pairs.source: 48	Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
pairs.target:
48 Deꞌ neraka olod-e diꞌ-e ponai
kobos, opui-e diꞌ-e ponai pulaꞌ.

pairs.source: 49	For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt.
pairs.target:
49 Dop-e suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nunaꞌ Topaꞌ yaꞌ obuah nguji pakai idip deꞌ susah
jolaꞌ, samah kodaꞌ nyaꞌa ngoon bongoh opui, samah geh kodaꞌ dagin deꞌ
modiaꞌ nyaꞌa pakai galuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 50	Salt [is] good: but if the salt have lost his saltness, wherewith will ye season it? Have salt in yourselves, and have peace one with another.
pairs.target:
50 Galuaꞌ inoh paguh, pak-e simoꞌ-e doiꞌ sap
pidiaꞌ-e, oni wat nyeꞌ odaꞌ pidiaꞌ baꞌuh? Odaꞌ leh idip ingan biguna saꞌan
nyaꞌa, duoh silalu idip bidamai duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon.”

pairs.source: 1	And he arose from thence, and cometh into the coasts of Judaea by the farther side of Jordan: and the people resort unto him again; and, as he was wont, he taught them again.
pairs.target:
1 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ buu soꞌ kota Kapernaum, Iyoh moꞌ odi
keꞌ propinsi Yudea duoh motas polad sungi Yordan. Nyaꞌa moꞌ
siuah-siuah nog tuduꞌ-E. Iyoh moꞌ ngajal nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ kodaꞌ deꞌ silalu
Iyoh nai-e.

pairs.source: 2	And the Pharisees came to him, and asked him, Is it lawful for a man to put away [his] wife? tempting him.
pairs.target:
2 Kudu-kudu naꞌan ulang Yahudi soꞌ uluk ulang Farisi nog yaꞌ suba
Yesus. Yoh moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ Yesus in-e, “Soꞌon yeh dali deꞌ moꞌ kawin
posan sowon-e?”

pairs.source: 3	And he answered and said unto them, What did Moses command you?
pairs.target:
3 Pak-e Yesus moꞌ nyawot odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Oni in sibaya nabi Musa
noꞌuh-e tuduꞌ ingan?”

pairs.source: 4	And they said, Moses suffered to write a bill of divorcement, and to put [her] away.
pairs.target:
4 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-e, “Musa nang soꞌon nyaꞌa biposan,
asal-e nai sulat biposan-e tuduꞌ sowon-e.”

pairs.source: 5	And Jesus answered and said unto them, For the hardness of your heart he wrote you this precept.
pairs.target:
5 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Musa nai sibaya deꞌ in inoh dop-e ingan sikiya
kolas yaꞌ nai oniꞌ deꞌ laꞌan odop ingan.

pairs.source: 6	But from the beginning of the creation God made them male and female.
pairs.target:
6 Pak-e sibungas-e Topaꞌ nai dunia
itih, ‘Iyoh moꞌ nai niꞌ dali duoh niꞌ dayung.’

pairs.source: 7	For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and cleave to his wife;
pairs.target:
7 ‘Iyoh leh ngan-e dali deꞌ
kawin togan samaꞌ sinoꞌ-e, iyoh moꞌ tikuluk duoh sowon-e,

pairs.source: 8	And they twain shall be one flesh: so then they are no more twain, but one flesh.
pairs.target:
8 odop-e deꞌ
duwoh moꞌ jadin niꞌ.’ Jadin, yoh diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ duwoh, pak-e niꞌ.

pairs.source: 9	What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.
pairs.target:
9 Iyoh leh
ngan-e nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ nguluk Topaꞌ, diꞌ soꞌon yaꞌ biposan.”

pairs.source: 10	And in the house his disciples asked him again of the same [matter].
pairs.target:
10 Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ daang boli, pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E paliꞌ sikian
tentang nyaꞌa deꞌ biposan.

pairs.source: 11	And he saith unto them, Whosoever shall put away his wife, and marry another, committeth adultery against her.
pairs.target:
11 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Osi
sijaꞌ-e deꞌ posan sowon-e, yohmoꞌ kawin baꞌuh duoh dayung deꞌ bokon,
iyoh biamai.

pairs.source: 12	And if a woman shall put away her husband, and be married to another, she committeth adultery.
pairs.target:
12 Wat noh geh dayung deꞌ posan bonon-e, iyoh moꞌ kawin
duoh dali deꞌ bokon, iyoh tuang biamai geh.”

pairs.source: 13	And they brought young children to him, that he should touch them: and [his] disciples rebuked those that brought [them].
pairs.target:
13 Mokuaꞌ inoh ogiꞌ kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa toban onak opot-e tuduꞌ
Yesus, saꞌ Yesus tomaꞌ-e duoh blokat-e, pak-e pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus moꞌ
malah tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 14	But when Jesus saw [it], he was much displeased, and said unto them, Suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God.
pairs.target:
14 Takal Yesus ningaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E malah
tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ, Yesus moꞌ malah tuduꞌ-e. Iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Tanah saꞌ
onak opot deꞌ munoꞌ odi tuduꞌ Okuꞌ. Dop-e nyaꞌa deꞌ kodaꞌ onak opot deꞌ
mutiꞌ leh deꞌ tilimaꞌ Topaꞌ militah daang idip-e.

pairs.source: 15	Verily I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child, he shall not enter therein.
pairs.target:
15 Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan:
Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ diꞌ-e tilimaꞌ pilitah Topaꞌ kodaꞌ onak opot, iyoh diꞌ-e tapod
jadin ayua umat Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 16	And he took them up in his arms, put [his] hands upon them, and blessed them.
pairs.target:
16 Mokuaꞌ sina in inoh, Yesus moꞌ pakuaꞌ onak
opot deꞌ munoꞌ yohmoꞌ tomaꞌ bak-e, daang-e blokat-e.

pairs.source: 17	And when he was gone forth into the way, there came one running, and kneeled to him, and asked him, Good Master, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?
pairs.target:
17 Takal Yesus lanyut pimonu-E, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan dali odi tuduꞌ Yesus. Iyoh
guluꞌ bikunyug yohmoꞌ in-e sikian tuduꞌ Yesus, “Gulu deꞌ paguh, oni deꞌ
halus kuꞌ nai-e saꞌ kuꞌ soꞌon idip deꞌ baꞌuh duoh Topaꞌ takal kuꞌ moꞌ kobos?”

pairs.source: 18	And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? [there is] none good but one, [that is], God.
pairs.target:
18 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Oni nai muꞌ nang Okuꞌ deꞌ paguh? Doiꞌ nyaꞌa
deꞌ paguh, jok-e Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 19	Thou knowest the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Defraud not, Honour thy father and mother.
pairs.target:
19 Muꞌu moꞌ puꞌan pilitah-pilitah Topaꞌ: Maꞌ ngabos nyaꞌa, maꞌ biamai,
maꞌ noku, maꞌ jadin tukang tanon deꞌ pibulaꞌ, maꞌ ngakal-nipu nyaꞌa,
pimodo leh duoh samaꞌ sinoꞌ muꞌ.”

pairs.source: 20	And he answered and said unto him, Master, all these have I observed from my youth.
pairs.target:
20 Dali inoh moꞌ in-e, “Gulu, suaꞌ pilitah deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nai kuꞌ soꞌ isoꞌ
kuꞌ geh.”

pairs.source: 21	Then Jesus beholding him loved him, and said unto him, One thing thou lackest: go thy way, sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come, take up the cross, and follow me.
pairs.target:
21 Yesus moꞌ ningaꞌ nyaꞌa inoh daang kila-E masiꞌ yohmoꞌ in-e, “Duam
niꞌ deꞌ kulang deꞌ aluaꞌ diꞌ muꞌ nai-e. Odi jua suaꞌ halta muꞌ nyeꞌ moꞌ
bikutung duit-e duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ botak. Mokuaꞌ inoh muꞌu moꞌ yaꞌ soꞌon
halta deꞌ siluga. Mokuaꞌ inoh paliꞌ katiꞌ nunaꞌ Okuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 22	And he was sad at that saying, and went away grieved: for he had great possessions.
pairs.target:
22 Takal-e ngojit sina
Yesus deꞌ in inoh, yoh moꞌ nesal-e yohmoꞌ buu, dop-e iyoh bogoꞌ halta-e.

pairs.source: 23	And Jesus looked round about, and saith unto his disciples, How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!
pairs.target:
23 Yesus moꞌ ningaꞌ tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, Iyoh moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ-e,
“Susah manah nyaꞌa deꞌ kaya yaꞌ jadin ayua umat Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 24	And the disciples were astonished at his words. But Jesus answereth again, and saith unto them, Children, how hard is it for them that trust in riches to enter into the kingdom of God!
pairs.target:
24 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E ilan ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ nang-E. Pak-e Yesus moꞌ in-e
lagiꞌ, “Onak-onak Kuꞌ, sukup susah-e nyaꞌa yaꞌ jadin ayua umat Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 25	It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.
pairs.target:
25 Sonang dooꞌ unta molot kaang lubang tuas soꞌ ulang deꞌ kaya yaꞌ jadin
ayua umat Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 26	And they were astonished out of measure, saying among themselves, Who then can be saved?
pairs.target:
26 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E makin ilan-e, daang-e bisikian si odop-e, “Simoꞌ-e
wat inoh osi deꞌ tapod silamat?”

pairs.source: 27	And Jesus looking upon them saith, With men [it is] impossible, but not with God: for with God all things are possible.
pairs.target:
27 Yesus moꞌ ningaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ daang-e in-e, “Manusia diꞌ-e tapod
nyilamat odop-e, pak-e Topaꞌ tapod nyilamat manusia. Doiꞌ deꞌ diꞌ Topaꞌ
tapod nai-e.”

pairs.source: 28	Then Peter began to say unto him, Lo, we have left all, and have followed thee.
pairs.target:
28 Petrus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ Yesus, “Koꞌih moꞌ togan suaꞌ oniꞌ ngan koꞌih
nunaꞌ Ingan.”

pairs.source: 29	And Jesus answered and said, Verily I say unto you, There is no man that hath left house, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my sake, and the gospel’s,
pairs.target:
29 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ muꞌu: Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ togan
boli-e, atou madih ayua-e, atou pingoma-e, atou onak-e, atou umoh-e
ngan-e nunaꞌ okuꞌ duoh magah Gah deꞌ Paguh,

pairs.source: 30	But he shall receive an hundredfold now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and lands, with persecutions; and in the world to come eternal life.
pairs.target:
30 daang idip-e deꞌ dunia
itih geh yoh yaꞌ soꞌon silatus sidoh bogoꞌ boli-e, madih ayua-e, pingoma-e,
onak-e duoh umoh-e, duoh susah jolaꞌ tuang ogiꞌ geh. Pak-e tiaꞌ ijoꞌ deꞌ
Dunia deꞌ Baꞌuh, iyoh yaꞌ soꞌon idip deꞌ baꞌuh duoh Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 31	But many [that are] first shall be last; and the last first.
pairs.target:
31 Pak-e bogoꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ dioꞌ adin yaꞌ ponai sunih, nyaꞌa deꞌ sunih adin yaꞌ ponai dioꞌ.”

pairs.source: 32	And they were in the way going up to Jerusalem; and Jesus went before them: and they were amazed; and as they followed, they were afraid. And he took again the twelve, and began to tell them what things should happen unto him,
pairs.target:
32 Daang pimonu Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E nuju Yerusalem, Yesus
ponu dioꞌ nuaꞌ jowin. Suaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E bigaduh duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon
deꞌ suwaꞌ deꞌ nunaꞌ dug-e tuang tolu geh. Mokuaꞌ inoh, Yesus ngijaꞌ lagiꞌ
soꞌ simoong duwoh naꞌan pinunaꞌ-E odaꞌ odi okon soꞌ-o, saꞌ-e diꞌ-e sinok  nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon. Yesus moꞌ tanon tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ oni wat nyaꞌa
yaꞌ duoh odop-E.

pairs.source: 33	[Saying], Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be delivered unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes; and they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles:
pairs.target:
33 Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Otoꞌ yaꞌ odi keꞌ Yerusalem, danih nyaꞌa yaꞌ nyelah
Okuꞌ Onak Manusia tuduꞌ pimipin-pimipin agama deꞌ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu
agama Yahudi. Yoh moꞌ yaꞌ ngukum ngabos Okuꞌ. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ yaꞌ
ngin tuduꞌ ulang deꞌ diꞌ-e ulang Yahudi.

pairs.source: 34	And they shall mock him, and shall scourge him, and shall spit upon him, and shall kill him: and the third day he shall rise again.
pairs.target:
34 Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ yaꞌ ngine Okuꞌ,
yoh yaꞌ ngujaꞌ, pijolaꞌ, duoh ngabos Okuꞌ. Pak-e mokuaꞌ taluh onu Okuꞌ
yaꞌ paliꞌ idip.”

pairs.source: 35	And James and John, the sons of Zebedee, come unto him, saying, Master, we would that thou shouldest do for us whatsoever we shall desire.
pairs.target:
35 Yakobus duoh Yohanes, onak-onak Zebedeus moꞌ odi sinok Yesus.
Yoh moꞌ in-e, “Gulu, ogiꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ mitiaꞌ koꞌih tuduꞌ Ingan, odaꞌ Ingan nai-e.”

pairs.source: 36	And he said unto them, What would ye that I should do for you?
pairs.target: 36 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Oni deꞌ mitiaꞌ ingan odaꞌ Okuꞌ nai-e?”

pairs.source: 37	They said unto him, Grant unto us that we may sit, one on thy right hand, and the other on thy left hand, in thy glory.
pairs.target:
37 Yoh moꞌ nyawot-e, “Takal Ingan militah jadin Laja deꞌ ayuh odaꞌ leh
koꞌih guluꞌ, niꞌ naꞌan nuaꞌ toꞌuh, niꞌ naꞌan nuaꞌ boit Ingan.”

pairs.source: 38	But Jesus said unto them, Ye know not what ye ask: can ye drink of the cup that I drink of? and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with?
pairs.target:
38 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Ingan diꞌ ingan ngiloti oniꞌ deꞌ mitiaꞌ ingan.
Podo ingan moꞌ siap tilimaꞌ susah jolaꞌ kodaꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ obuah Okuꞌ? Podo
ingan taan yaꞌ obuah pijolaꞌ kodaꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ obuah Okuꞌ?”

pairs.source: 39	And they said unto him, We can. And Jesus said unto them, Ye shall indeed drink of the cup that I drink of; and with the baptism that I am baptized withal shall ye be baptized:
pairs.target:
39 Odop-e deꞌ duwoh moꞌ nyawot lagiꞌ, “Koꞌih taan.”
Yesus moꞌ in-e lagiꞌ, “Tok ingan yaꞌ kiꞌan susah jolaꞌ duoh obuah pijolaꞌ
samah kodaꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ obuah Okuꞌ.

pairs.source: 40	But to sit on my right hand and on my left hand is not mine to give; but [it shall be given to them] for whom it is prepared.
pairs.target:
40 Pak-e Okuꞌ doiꞌ hak Kuꞌ, yaꞌ notap osi
deꞌ guluꞌ nuaꞌ toꞌuh duoh osi deꞌ nuaꞌ boit Kuꞌ. Inoh Topaꞌ sidia saꞌan nyaꞌa
deꞌ moꞌ nyok-E.”

pairs.source: 41	And when the ten heard [it], they began to be much displeased with James and John.
pairs.target:
41 Takal simoong pinunaꞌ-E deꞌ bokon ngojit oniꞌ deꞌ mitiaꞌ odop-e deꞌ
duwoh, yoh moꞌ malah tuduꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 42	But Jesus called them [to him], and saith unto them, Ye know that they which are accounted to rule over the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and their great ones exercise authority upon them.
pairs.target:
42 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ mogan suaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E yohmoꞌ in-e,
“Pimipin-pimipin dunia militah layat-e pakai paksa duoh pijolaꞌ.

pairs.source: 43	But so shall it not be among you: but whosoever will be great among you, shall be your minister:
pairs.target:
43 Pak-e
ingan diꞌ soꞌon wat inoh! Osi deꞌ yaꞌ jadin pimipin deꞌ soꞌ ingan, iyoh halus
jadin pilayan.

pairs.source: 44	And whosoever of you will be the chiefest, shall be servant of all.
pairs.target:
44 Duoh osi deꞌ yaꞌ jadin ulang timogah, iyoh sidia jadin kuli
saꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon.

pairs.source: 45	For even the Son of man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many.
pairs.target:
45 Dop-e Onak Manusia nog idoh diꞌ-e odaꞌ nyaꞌa
layan odop-E, pak-e Yoh yaꞌ layan duoh ngin asong-E ngan-e nyilamat
nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 46	And they came to Jericho: and as he went out of Jericho with his disciples and a great number of people, blind Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus, sat by the highway side begging.
pairs.target:
46 Yesus duoh suaꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ nog keꞌ Kota Yerikho. Takal
Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E buu luah soꞌ Kota inoh, nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ
siuah-siuah nunaꞌ-E. Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ deꞌ tukang mitiaꞌ-mitiaꞌ deꞌ guluꞌ
deꞌ bingon olan deꞌ adon Bartimeus onak Timeus.

pairs.source: 47	And when he heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to cry out, and say, Jesus, [thou] Son of David, have mercy on me.
pairs.target:
47 Takal Bartimeus moꞌ ngojit nang Yesus deꞌ soꞌ Nazaret ponu ngilusuꞌ
odop-e, iyoh moꞌ nang bogan-e mitiaꞌ masiꞌ, “Yesus onak sukun Laja Daud!
Masiꞌ leh tuduꞌ okuꞌ!”

pairs.source: 48	And many charged him that he should hold his peace: but he cried the more a great deal, [Thou] Son of David, have mercy on me.
pairs.target:
48 Nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ moꞌ malah daꞌ-a daang-e odaꞌ yoh loꞌo, pak-e yoh
makin dolas nang bogan-e, “Yesus onak sukun Laja Daud! Masiꞌ leh tuduꞌ
okuꞌ!”

pairs.source: 49	And Jesus stood still, and commanded him to be called. And they call the blind man, saying unto him, Be of good comfort, rise; he calleth thee.
pairs.target:
49 Yesus moꞌ loꞌo daang-e sina, “Mogan odaꞌ iyoh odi katiꞌ!” Odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ moꞌ mogan nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ inoh simadi-e sina tuduꞌ-e, “Notod negeh
kila muꞌ, mokat likas-e, Yesus mogan muꞌu!”

pairs.source: 50	And he, casting away his garment, rose, and came to Jesus.
pairs.target:
50 Nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ inoh moꞌ lasuꞌ bukaꞌ jubah-e, iyoh moꞌ lasuꞌ mujuag,
iyoh moꞌ odi tuduꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 51	And Jesus answered and said unto him, What wilt thou that I should do unto thee? The blind man said unto him, Lord, that I might receive my sight.
pairs.target:
51 Yesus moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ-e, “Oni deꞌ mitiaꞌ ingan odaꞌ Okuꞌ nai-e?”
Nyaꞌa deꞌ butaꞌ inoh moꞌ nyawot-e, “Gulu, okuꞌ mitiaꞌ odaꞌ boton kuꞌ ponai
ningaꞌ!”

pairs.source: 52	And Jesus said unto him, Go thy way; thy faith hath made thee whole. And immediately he received his sight, and followed Jesus in the way.
pairs.target:
52 Yesus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ-e, “Dop-e muꞌu bisayaꞌ, muꞌu mokuaꞌ.Paliꞌ
leh.” Takal inoh geh yoh lasuꞌ ponai ningaꞌ. Yoh moꞌ nunaꞌ Yesus daang
pimonuꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 1	And when they came nigh to Jerusalem, unto Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount of Olives, he sendeth forth two of his disciples,
pairs.target:
1 Takal Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ yaꞌ nog Yerusalem, odop-e
deꞌ munoꞌ nog keꞌ kupuaꞌ Betfage duoh kupuaꞌ Betania. Soꞌ duoh
kupuaꞌ inoh ogiꞌ deꞌ tilipang Punguꞌ Zaitun. Takal-e danoꞌ, Yesus odaꞌ
duwoh naꞌan pinunaꞌ-E ponu dioꞌ.

pairs.source: 2	And saith unto them, Go your way into the village over against you: and as soon as ye be entered into it, ye shall find a colt tied, whereon never man sat; loose him, and bring [him].
pairs.target:
2 Yoh moꞌ sibaya tuduꞌ-e in-E, “Odi leh
keꞌ kupuaꞌ deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ nuaꞌ jowin toꞌ inoh. Takal muꞌ molot kanoꞌ, muꞌu
ningaꞌ ogiꞌ niꞌ polong keledai deꞌ aluaꞌ mudaꞌ deꞌ obuah mokos, deꞌ aluaꞌ
doiꞌ nyaꞌa muat daꞌ-e. Nyeꞌ moꞌ nukas-e, nyeꞌ moꞌ toban katiꞌ.

pairs.source: 3	And if any man say unto you, Why do ye this? say ye that the Lord hath need of him; and straightway he will send him hither.
pairs.target:
3 Simoꞌ-e
ogiꞌ nyaꞌa sikian-e, oni nai muꞌ mit keledai inoh? Nyeꞌ tanon tuduꞌ-e, ‘Gulu
pilelu keledai itih, mokuaꞌ inoh Iyoh yaꞌ lasuꞌ paliꞌ-e.’ ”

pairs.source: 4	And they went their way, and found the colt tied by the door without in a place where two ways met; and they loose him.
pairs.target:
4 Soꞌ duwoh pinunaꞌ-e moꞌ odi. Yoh moꞌ tapod ogiꞌ niꞌ polong onak
keledai deꞌ mokos nyaꞌa deꞌ jowin boli-e sinok olan. Odop-e deꞌ duwoh  moꞌ nukas tolin-e.

pairs.source: 5	And certain of them that stood there said unto them, What do ye, loosing the colt?
pairs.target:
5 Kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ mujuag sinok topat inoh
moꞌ sikian-e, “Oni nai ingan nukas keledai inoh neh?”

pairs.source: 6	And they said unto them even as Jesus had commanded: and they let them go.
pairs.target:
6 Odop-e deꞌ duwoh moꞌ nyawot nunaꞌ deꞌ tanon Yesus tuduꞌ-e, yohmoꞌ
nyaꞌa danoꞌ moꞌ tanah odaꞌ iyoh toban-e.

pairs.source: 7	And they brought the colt to Jesus, and cast their garments on him; and he sat upon him.
pairs.target:
7 Iyoh moꞌ toban keledai inoh
tuduꞌ Yesus. Iyoh moꞌ nopas tun dug keledai inoh pakai jubah-e. Yesus moꞌ
nyikoh guluꞌ deꞌ tun-e.

pairs.source: 8	And many spread their garments in the way: and others cut down branches off the trees, and strawed [them] in the way.
pairs.target:
8 Bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nopas olan deꞌ yaꞌ ngilusuꞌ Yesus
pakai jubah-e. Ogiꞌ geh nyaꞌa deꞌ nopas olan pakai dowon-dowon koyuh
deꞌ mit-e soꞌ kobon-e.

pairs.source: 9	And they that went before, and they that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna; Blessed [is] he that cometh in the name of the Lord:
pairs.target:
9 Ayua deꞌ nunaꞌ Yesus deꞌ nuaꞌ jowin duoh nyaꞌa
deꞌ nunaꞌ nuaꞌ dug-e moꞌ nang bobaꞌ-e,
“Mudi Topaꞌ deꞌ siluga! Obuah bilokat Iyoh deꞌ nog daang adon Topaꞌ!

pairs.source: 10	Blessed [be] the kingdom of our father David, that cometh in the name of the Lord: Hosanna in the highest.
pairs.target:
10 Obuah bilokat leh Onak sukun Laja Daud itih, deꞌ yaꞌ militah otoꞌ odaꞌ
paguh! Mudi leh Topaꞌ otoꞌ deꞌ siluga!”

pairs.source: 11	And Jesus entered into Jerusalem, and into the temple: and when he had looked round about upon all things, and now the eventide was come, he went out unto Bethany with the twelve.
pairs.target:
11 Takal Yesus nog keꞌ Yerusalem, Iyoh moꞌ molot keꞌ awah Boli Topaꞌ.
Iyoh ningaꞌ suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ awah Boli Topaꞌ inoh, dop-e onu moꞌ yaꞌ
ngalom Iyoh duoh pinunaꞌ-E deꞌ simoong duwoh naꞌan moꞌ odi keꞌ kupuaꞌ
Betania.

pairs.source: 12	And on the morrow, when they were come from Bethany, he was hungry:
pairs.target:
12 Onu tiaꞌ pagi-e, takal Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E buu soꞌ Betania
odi keꞌ Yerusalem, Yesus noman toꞌin-e pilai.

pairs.source: 13	And seeing a fig tree afar off having leaves, he came, if haply he might find any thing thereon: and when he came to it, he found nothing but leaves; for the time of figs was not [yet].
pairs.target:
13 Soꞌ juuaꞌ Iyoh moꞌ ningaꞌ
tongon ara deꞌ bidonom dowon-e. Iyoh moꞌ odi keꞌ puꞌun-e, podo-podo-e ogiꞌ
buaꞌ-e. Pak-e takal Yesus moꞌ nog libuaꞌ-e Iyoh moꞌ ningaꞌ jok-e ogiꞌ dowon-e
sijaꞌ-e, dop-e aluaꞌ diꞌ-e musim tongon ara inoh bibuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 14	And Jesus answered and said unto it, No man eat fruit of thee hereafter for ever. And his disciples heard [it].
pairs.target:
14 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E
moꞌ ngojit Yesus sina in-e tuduꞌ tongon ara inoh, “Mulai soꞌ adin doiꞌ tiyaꞌ
nyaꞌa yaꞌ man buaꞌ soꞌ tongon muꞌ!”

pairs.source: 15	And they come to Jerusalem: and Jesus went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the moneychangers, and the seats of them that sold doves;
pairs.target:
15 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ nog keꞌ Yerusalem. Iyoh moꞌ molot
keꞌ awah Boli Topaꞌ, Iyoh moꞌ kasig nyaꞌa deꞌ bijua danoꞌ. Yesus moꞌ
ngibolui mija topat nyaꞌa nukal duit duoh mija topat nyaꞌa jua manuk
asang.

pairs.source: 16	And would not suffer that any man should carry [any] vessel through the temple.
pairs.target:
16 Yoh moꞌ jaman osi sijaꞌ-e diꞌ soꞌon toban balang deꞌ yaꞌ jua-e
ngilusuꞌ awah boli Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 17	And he taught, saying unto them, Is it not written, My house shall be called of all nations the house of prayer? but ye have made it a den of thieves.
pairs.target:
17 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ ngajal nyaꞌa danoꞌ
in-e, “Ogiꞌ deꞌ obuah nulis daang Kitab deꞌ in-e, ‘Boli kuꞌ nyaꞌa sobot nang

pairs.source: 18	And the scribes and chief priests heard [it], and sought how they might destroy him: for they feared him, because all the people was astonished at his doctrine.
pairs.target:
18 Ayua pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu agama Yahudi
moꞌ ngojit sina Yesus inoh, yoh moꞌ kalik olan ngan-e yaꞌ ngabos Yesus.
Pak-e yoh tolu tuduꞌ Yesus dop-e bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ sonang duoh oniꞌ deꞌ
ngajal Yesus.

pairs.source: 19	And when even was come, he went out of the city.
pairs.target:
19 Takal onu moꞌ yaꞌ ngalom Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E buu soꞌ kota
inoh.

pairs.source: 20	And in the morning, as they passed by, they saw the fig tree dried up from the roots.
pairs.target:
20 Tiaꞌ pagi-e takal Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E ponu ngilusuꞌ tongon
ara inoh, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ningaꞌ tongon ara inoh moꞌ kobos pisok
nog aat-e.

pairs.source: 21	And Peter calling to remembrance saith unto him, Master, behold, the fig tree which thou cursedst is withered away.
pairs.target:
21 Petrus moꞌ natong oniꞌ deꞌ nai Yesus sumia-e yoh moꞌ in-e,
“Gulu, ningaꞌ mey tongon ara deꞌ obuah nyupah Ingan sumia-e moꞌ pisok.”

pairs.source: 22	And Jesus answering saith unto them, Have faith in God.
pairs.target: 22 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Bisayaꞌ negeh tuduꞌ Topaꞌ!

pairs.source: 23	For verily I say unto you, That whosoever shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea; and shall not doubt in his heart, but shall believe that those things which he saith shall come to pass; he shall have whatsoever he saith.
pairs.target:
23 Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ
ingan: Osi sijaꞌ-e deꞌ sina tuduꞌ dolod itih, ‘Bilalih leh duoh obuah tolan
kaang laut,’ suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ nang ingan inoh yaꞌ jadi, asal ingan diꞌ ingan
bigaduh duoh totap bisayaꞌ nang oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ bonal-bonal jadi.

pairs.source: 24	Therefore I say unto you, What things soever ye desire, when ye pray, believe that ye receive [them], and ye shall have [them].
pairs.target:
24 Yoh
ngan Kuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan: Oni sijaꞌ-e deꞌ mitiaꞌ muꞌ daang doa muꞌ,
bisayaꞌ negeh nang muꞌu moꞌ soꞌon-e, muꞌu pasti yaꞌ soꞌon-e.

pairs.source: 25	And when ye stand praying, forgive, if ye have ought against any: that your Father also which is in heaven may forgive you your trespasses.
pairs.target:
25 Siniaꞌ sijaꞌ-e
takal muꞌu bidoa, simoꞌ muꞌ natong muꞌu ogiꞌ monam otin tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ
bokon, muꞌu halus ngapun dioꞌ salah-e, saꞌ Samaꞌ muꞌ deꞌ siluga ngapun-E
geh muꞌu.

pairs.source: 26	But if ye do not forgive, neither will your Father which is in heaven forgive your trespasses.
pairs.target:
26 Pak-e simoꞌ muꞌ diꞌ ngapun salah nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon, Samaꞌ muꞌ
deꞌ siluga tuang doliaꞌ-e geh ngapun dosa muꞌ.”

pairs.source: 27	And they come again to Jerusalem: and as he was walking in the temple, there come to him the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders,
pairs.target:
27 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ odi lagiꞌ keꞌ Yerusalem. Takal Yesus ponu-ponu deꞌ limang Boli Topaꞌ, pimipin-pimipin agama duoh gulu-gulu agama ulang
Yahudi duoh pimipin-pimipin ulang Yahudi deꞌ bokon bitapod duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: 28	And say unto him, By what authority doest thou these things? and who gave thee this authority to do these things?
pairs.target:
28 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ Yesus, “Osi deꞌ odaꞌ Muꞌu nai oniꞌ
deꞌ mutiꞌ? Osi deꞌ ngin tugas tuduꞌ Muꞌu nai suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ mutiꞌ?”

pairs.source: 29	And Jesus answered and said unto them, I will also ask of you one question, and answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.
pairs.target:
29 Yesus
moꞌ nyawot-e, “Okuꞌ tuang yaꞌ sikian geh tuduꞌ ingan. Simoꞌ ingan tapod
nyawot, Okuꞌ tuang tanon Kuꞌ geh osi deꞌ odaꞌ Okuꞌ nai suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ mutiꞌ.

pairs.source: 30	The baptism of John, was [it] from heaven, or of men? answer me.
pairs.target: 30 Osi deꞌ odaꞌ Yohanes Pembaptis baptis nyaꞌa? Manusia keh Topaꞌ?”

pairs.source: 31	And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then did ye not believe him?
pairs.target:
31 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ biloneng si odop-e, “Moꞌ toꞌ nang ‘Topaꞌ deꞌ
odaꞌ’, Iyoh pasti nang ‘Oni nai diꞌ muꞌ bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Yohanes?’

pairs.source: 32	But if we shall say, Of men; they feared the people: for all [men] counted John, that he was a prophet indeed.
pairs.target:
32 Pak-e
idoh geh diꞌ otoꞌ ponai nang ‘Manusia deꞌ odaꞌ.’ ” Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ nang
in inoh saai yoh tolu deꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ yaꞌ malah tuduꞌ odop-e, dop-e
suaꞌ nyaꞌa bisayaꞌ nang Yohanes inoh nabi.

pairs.source: 33	And they answered and said unto Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus answering saith unto them, Neither do I tell you by what authority I do these things.
pairs.target:
33 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-E, “Koꞌih diꞌ koꞌih puꞌan-e.”
Yesus moꞌ nyawot in-e, “Okuꞌ tuang idoh geh diꞌ kuꞌ tanon osi Nyaꞌa
deꞌ odaꞌ Okuꞌ nai suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ.”

pairs.source: 1	And he began to speak unto them by parables. A [certain] man planted a vineyard, and set an hedge about [it], and digged [a place for] the winefat, and built a tower, and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country.
pairs.target:
1 Yesus mulai sina tuduꞌ pimipin-pimipin agama deꞌ ayuh, gulu-gulu
agama, duoh pimipin-pimipin Yahudi deꞌ bokon pakai nang silita,
in-e, “Ogiꞌ nyaꞌa nai kobon anggul, yoh moꞌ ngijuam-e, mokuaꞌ inoh yoh
moꞌ nai lubang topat nyaꞌa misiat piꞌin buaꞌ anggul. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ
nai pangal topat nyaꞌa jaga kobon, yoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa nyewa kobon-e,
odop-e moꞌ buu keꞌ negeli deꞌ bokon.

pairs.source: 2	And at the season he sent to the husbandmen a servant, that he might receive from the husbandmen of the fruit of the vineyard.
pairs.target:
2 Takal-e nog musim ngutuam buaꞌ
anggul, nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh moꞌ pait kuli-e odaꞌ odi mit duman
soꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ nyewa kobon-e.

pairs.source: 3	And they caught [him], and beat him, and sent [him] away empty.
pairs.target:
3 Pak-e nyaꞌa deꞌ nyewa kobon inoh moꞌ
takap kuli deꞌ pait nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon. Yoh moꞌ bipupuꞌ duoh-e, yohmoꞌ
odaꞌ paliꞌ boloh.

pairs.source: 4	And again he sent unto them another servant; and at him they cast stones, and wounded [him] in the head, and sent [him] away shamefully handled.
pairs.target:
4 Nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh moꞌ pait kuli-e deꞌ bokon,
pak-e odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ mupuꞌ bak-e yohmoꞌ kasig odaꞌ buu, daang-e
makiꞌ-mutaꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 5	And again he sent another; and him they killed, and many others; beating some, and killing some.
pairs.target:
5 Nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh moꞌ pait kuli-e deꞌ bokon,
pak-e odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ngabos-e. Watnoh geh yoh duoh kuli-e deꞌ
bogoꞌ deꞌ pait-e deꞌ bokon. Ogiꞌ deꞌ mupuꞌ-e, ogiꞌ geh deꞌ ngabos-e.

pairs.source: 6	Having yet therefore one son, his wellbeloved, he sent him also last unto them, saying, They will reverence my son.
pairs.target:
6 Adin
moꞌ doiꞌ tiyaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon deꞌ yaꞌ pait nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh,
duam onak odop-e deꞌ ngibalaꞌ-e jaꞌ-e. Yoh moꞌ in-e daang pikil-e, ‘Paguh
okuꞌ odaꞌ onak odop kuꞌ deꞌ odi, saꞌ-e pimodo daꞌ-e.’

pairs.source: 7	But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours.
pairs.target:
7 Pak-e takal nyaꞌa deꞌ
nyewa kobon ningaꞌ onak nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh nog, yoh moꞌ sina
tipan odop-e, in-e, ‘Ningaꞌ onak nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon itih! Iyoh leh deꞌ
yaꞌ kakuꞌ suaꞌ kobon itih, takal samaꞌ-e kobos. Jaꞌ toꞌ ngabos-e saꞌ otoꞌ deꞌ
kakuꞌ kobon itih.’

pairs.source: 8	And they took him, and killed [him], and cast [him] out of the vineyard.
pairs.target:
8 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ takap duoh ngabos onak nyaꞌa
deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh, yoh moꞌ tolan todang-e keꞌ sopaꞌ kobon.”

pairs.source: 9	What shall therefore the lord of the vineyard do? he will come and destroy the husbandmen, and will give the vineyard unto others.
pairs.target:
9 Yesus mokuaꞌ silita, yohmoꞌ sikian tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ, “Oni wat
oniꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ nai nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ kobon inoh? Pasti odop-e sadiꞌ-e deꞌ yaꞌ nog   
ngabos nyaꞌa deꞌ nyewa kobon-e inoh. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa
deꞌ bokon deꞌ nyewa.

pairs.source: 10	And have ye not read this scripture; The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner:
pairs.target:
10 Pasti moꞌ ogiꞌ ingan basa daang Kitab deꞌ in-e,
‘Batuh deꞌ tolan tukang boli,
moꞌ jadin batuh deꞌ sukup biguna-e.

pairs.source: 11	This was the Lord’s doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?
pairs.target:
11 Itih leh oniꞌ deꞌ nai Topaꞌ,
deꞌ sukup otoꞌ ilan-e.’ ”

pairs.source: 12	And they sought to lay hold on him, but feared the people: for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them: and they left him, and went their way.
pairs.target:
12 Ayua pimipin Yahudi deꞌ ngojit silita inoh moꞌ kagaꞌ odop-e yaꞌ takap
Yesus, dop-e silita deꞌ nang Yesus inoh nados odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ. Pak-e
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ tolu tuduꞌ nyaꞌa' deꞌ bogoꞌ, inoh leh ngan odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ moꞌ buu togan Yesus.

pairs.source: 13	And they send unto him certain of the Pharisees and of the Herodians, to catch him in [his] words.
pairs.target:
13 Mokuaꞌ inoh ayua pimipin Yahudi moꞌ odaꞌ kudu-kudu naꞌan soꞌ uluk
ulang Farisi duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ nuaꞌ Laja Herodes odi tuduꞌ Yesus ngan-e odaꞌ
Yesus yaꞌ nang sina deꞌ diꞌ-e bonal, saꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ dapod nyalah
Yesus.

pairs.source: 14	And when they were come, they say unto him, Master, we know that thou art true, and carest for no man: for thou regardest not the person of men, but teachest the way of God in truth: Is it lawful to give tribute to Caesar, or not?
pairs.target:
14 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nog tuduꞌ Yesus, yohmoꞌ in-e, “Gulu, koꞌih
puꞌan nang Ingan tanon oniꞌ deꞌ bonal duoh diꞌ Ingan piduli oni in sina
nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon. Ingan diꞌ Ingan tolu, bait tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ timogah, bait
tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ diꞌ-e timogah, pak-e Ingan suang-suang in Ingan ngajal wat
ki wat manusia idip nunaꞌ deꞌ laꞌan Topaꞌ. Adin, suba tanon tuduꞌ koꞌih,
moꞌ-e nunaꞌ atulan agama otoꞌ, soꞌon kedoh keh otoꞌ bayal suke tuduꞌ Laja
Roma deꞌ paling ayuh? Halus keh idoh otoꞌ bayal-e?”

pairs.source: 15	Shall we give, or shall we not give? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said unto them, Why tempt ye me? bring me a penny, that I may see [it].
pairs.target:
15 Yesus puꞌan nang odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ pulaꞌ-pulaꞌ paguh. Iyoh moꞌ
nyawot-e, “Oni nai ingan siaji ingan odaꞌ Okuꞌ yaꞌ nang sina deꞌ diꞌ-e
bonal? Suba bitanga tuduꞌ Okuꞌ niꞌ kiping duit pilak!”

pairs.source: 16	And they brought [it]. And he saith unto them, Whose [is] this image and superscription? And they said unto him, Caesar’s.
pairs.target:
16 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ngin tuduꞌ-E. Yesus moꞌ sikian in-E, “Gamal
duoh adon osi deꞌ ogiꞌ datiꞌ?” Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ nyawot-e, “Gamal
duoh adon Laja Roma deꞌ paling ayuh.”

pairs.source: 17	And Jesus answering said unto them, Render to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s. And they marvelled at him.
pairs.target:
17 Yesus moꞌ in-e, “Moꞌ-e wat inoh, oni deꞌ kakuꞌ laja, ngin tuduꞌ laja.
Oni deꞌ kakuꞌ Topaꞌ, ngin tuduꞌ Topaꞌ!” Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sukup ilan-e.

pairs.source: 18	Then come unto him the Sadducees, which say there is no resurrection; and they asked him, saying,
pairs.target:
18 Uluk ulang Saduki iyoh leh uluk ulang deꞌ diꞌ-e bisayaꞌ nang nyaꞌa deꞌ
kobos tapod paliꞌ idip. Ogiꞌ kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa soꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ  deꞌ nog tuduꞌ Yesus.Yoh bisikian tuduꞌ Yesus, in-e,

pairs.source: 19	Master, Moses wrote unto us, If a man’s brother die, and leave [his] wife [behind him], and leave no children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.
pairs.target:
19 “Gulu, Musa nulis
atulan itih saꞌan otoꞌ: ‘Simoꞌ-e ogiꞌ dali deꞌ moꞌ kawin, yoh moꞌ kobos, pak-e
yoh doiꞌ onak-e, yohmoꞌ madih-e deꞌ dali deꞌ bokon mit bokas sowon-e,
odaꞌ jadin sowon odop-e, saꞌ-e ogiꞌ onak saꞌan bonon-e deꞌ moꞌ kobos.’

pairs.source: 20	Now there were seven brethren: and the first took a wife, and dying left no seed.
pairs.target:
20 Deꞌ dioꞌ, ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ sikiaꞌ-sudiꞌ juꞌ madih odop-e deꞌ dali. Madih-e deꞌ
pinuan kawin, yoh moꞌ dioꞌ kobos ngan-e aluaꞌ doiꞌ onak-e.

pairs.source: 21	And the second took her, and died, neither left he any seed: and the third likewise.
pairs.target:
21 Mokuaꞌ inoh
madih-e deꞌ keꞌ duwoh-e mit bokas sowon-e inoh odaꞌ jadin sowon-e, yoh
tuang dioꞌ kobos geh ngan-e aluaꞌ doiꞌ onak-e. Wat noh geh, madih-e deꞌ keꞌ
taluh-e,

pairs.source: 22	And the seven had her, and left no seed: last of all the woman died also.
pairs.target:
22 telus nog madih-e deꞌ ke' juꞌ-e, wat inoh geh yoh kobos ngan-e
aluaꞌ doiꞌ onak-e. Mokuaꞌ inoh dayung inoh tuang kobos geh.

pairs.source: 23	In the resurrection therefore, when they shall rise, whose wife shall she be of them? for the seven had her to wife.
pairs.target:
23 Takal suaꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ kobos paliꞌ idip, dayung inoh jadin sowon osi? Dop-e soꞌ juꞌ
madih odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ kawin duoh-e.”

pairs.source: 24	And Jesus answering said unto them, Do ye not therefore err, because ye know not the scriptures, neither the power of God?
pairs.target:
24 Yesus moꞌ nyawot odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ in-e, “Pikil ingan moꞌ salah.
Ingan diꞌ ingan puꞌan Kitab duoh kuasa Topaꞌ.

pairs.source: 25	For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage; but are as the angels which are in heaven.
pairs.target:
25 Dop-e takal nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ
kobos mokat paliꞌ idip, doiꞌ tiyaꞌ nyaꞌa yaꞌ kawin, suaꞌ nyaꞌa idip kodaꞌ
malaikat deꞌ siluga.

pairs.source: 26	And as touching the dead, that they rise: have ye not read in the book of Moses, how in the bush God spake unto him, saying, I [am] the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob?
pairs.target:
26 Tentang nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ kobos mokat paliꞌ idip, podo
doiꞌ sidoh ingan basa daang buk deꞌ nulis nabi Musa, takal Topaꞌ bitanga
odop-E tuduꞌ Musa soꞌ totaꞌ lojaꞌ deꞌ biduduꞌ opui daꞌ-e? Topaꞌ in-e, ‘Okuꞌ
leh Topaꞌ deꞌ obuah nyomah odaꞌ Abraham, Ishak duoh Yakub,’

pairs.source: 27	He is not the God of the dead, but the God of the living: ye therefore do greatly err.
pairs.target:
27 Iyoh
idoh diꞌ-e Topaꞌ deꞌ obuah nyomah odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kobos, pak-e Iyoh Topaꞌ
deꞌ obuah nyomah odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ idip. Ingan diꞌ ingan ngiloti-e!”

pairs.source: 28	And one of the scribes came, and having heard them reasoning together, and perceiving that he had answered them well, asked him, Which is the first commandment of all?
pairs.target:
28 Takal Yesus aluaꞌ bikalah duoh uluk ulang Saduki, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan
gulu agama Yahudi suwaꞌ ngojit-e. Yoh ningaꞌ Yesus nyawot oni deꞌ sikian
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ sukup bonal-e. Gulu agama Yahudi inoh moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ
Yesus in-e, “Ki pilitah deꞌ paling penting soꞌ susuaꞌ pilitah soꞌ Topaꞌ?”

pairs.source: 29	And Jesus answered him, The first of all the commandments [is], Hear, O Israel; The Lord our God is one Lord:
pairs.target:
29 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Pilitah deꞌ paling penting keꞌ niꞌ-e iyoh leh:
‘Ngojit leh ingan oi ulang Israel! Topaꞌ otoꞌ jok-e niꞌ.

pairs.source: 30	And thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength: this [is] the first commandment.
pairs.target:
30 Ngibalaꞌ leh Topaꞌ
daang suaꞌ otin muꞌ, suaꞌ asong muꞌ, suaꞌ pikil-kila muꞌ, duoh suaꞌ tenaga
muꞌ.’

pairs.source: 31	And the second [is] like, [namely] this, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. There is none other commandment greater than these.
pairs.target:
31 Pilitah deꞌ keꞌ duwoh-e iyoh leh: ‘Ngibalaꞌ leh siodop muꞌ manusia,
samah kodaꞌ muꞌu ngibalaꞌ odop muꞌ. Doiꞌ pilitah deꞌ bokon deꞌ paling
penting soꞌ pilitah deꞌ duwoh itih.’ ”

pairs.source: 32	And the scribe said unto him, Well, Master, thou hast said the truth: for there is one God; and there is none other but he:
pairs.target:
32 Gulu agama Yahudi inoh moꞌ sina tuduꞌ Yesus, “Bonal manah oniꞌ deꞌ
nang Ingan, pak Gulu-e! Iyoh jok-e niꞌ, doiꞌ Topaꞌ deꞌ bokon.

pairs.source: 33	And to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love [his] neighbour as himself, is more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices.
pairs.target:
33 Manusia
halus ngibalaꞌ Topaꞌ daang suaꞌ otin-e, pakai suaꞌ pikil kila-e, duoh suaꞌ   
tenaga-e, duoh halus ngibalaꞌ si odop-e manusia, samah kodaꞌ iyoh ngibalaꞌ
odop-e sadiꞌ-e. Itih lobih paguh soꞌ binatang deꞌ ngabos nyeꞌ ngan nyeꞌ
nyomah Topaꞌ, duoh deꞌ bokon-bokon-e deꞌ ngin nyeꞌ tuduꞌ Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 34	And when Jesus saw that he answered discreetly, he said unto him, Thou art not far from the kingdom of God. And no man after that durst ask him [any question].
pairs.target:
34 Yesus ningaꞌ gulu agama ulang Yahudi inoh sikiya ponai nyawot
sina-E, Yesus moꞌ sina lagiꞌ tuduꞌ-e, “Muꞌu moꞌ siap yaꞌ tilimaꞌ Topaꞌ militah
daang idip muꞌ.”
Mokuaꞌ inoh suaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ puus sikian oni-oni-e tuduꞌ
Yesus.

pairs.source: 35	And Jesus answered and said, while he taught in the temple, How say the scribes that Christ is the Son of David?
pairs.target:
35 Takal Yesus aluaꞌ ngajal deꞌ awah Boli Topaꞌ, Yesus moꞌ in-E, “Oni
wat gulu-gulu agama ulang Yahudi tapod tanon nang Laja Pinyilamat soꞌ
onak sukun Laja Daud?

pairs.source: 36	For David himself said by the Holy Ghost, The LORD said to my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool.
pairs.target:
36 Noꞌuh-e Laja Daud sibonal-e obuah nutuan Iyang
Topaꞌ yohmoꞌ in-e,
‘Topaꞌ sina tuduꞌ Tuan kuꞌ:
guluꞌ nuaꞌ toꞌuh Kuꞌ saꞌ Muꞌ militah jadin Laja,
nog kuꞌ odaꞌ musuh-musuh Muꞌ tunuak tuduꞌ Muꞌu.’

pairs.source: 37	David therefore himself calleth him Lord; and whence is he [then] his son? And the common people heard him gladly.
pairs.target:
37 Simoꞌ-e Daud sobot nang Laja Pinyilamat inoh Tuan-e, jadin Iyoh
nak-e jok-e onak sukun Daud, Iyoh pasti lobih ayuh kuasa-E soꞌ Daud.”
Nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ danoꞌ sukup sonang-e ngojit pingajal Yesus.

pairs.source: 38	And he said unto them in his doctrine, Beware of the scribes, which love to go in long clothing, and [love] salutations in the marketplaces,
pairs.target:
38 Yesus tanon geh tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Maꞌ tauꞌ-tauꞌ yaꞌ nunaꞌ
gaya gulu-gulu agama deꞌ munoꞌ. Iyoh suka ponu pakai jubah deꞌ omu, yoh
magah nang odop-e ulang timogah, duoh suka odaꞌ nyaꞌa mudi odop-e deꞌ
pasal.

pairs.source: 39	And the chief seats in the synagogues, and the uppermost rooms at feasts:
pairs.target:
39 Iyoh suka guluꞌ deꞌ topat-topat nuaꞌ jowin daang topat simayang
agama Yahudi, duoh deꞌ topat-topat nyaꞌa man ayuh.

pairs.source: 40	Which devour widows’ houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these shall receive greater damnation.
pairs.target:
40 Iyoh suka nipu
sinoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ janda duoh mit lomin boli-e. Iyoh suka bidoa tuui-tuui
deꞌ jowin nyaꞌa ngan-e magah nang odop-e paguh . Tiaꞌ ijoꞌ odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ lobih baat ukum deꞌ yaꞌ tilimaꞌ-e.”

pairs.source: 41	And Jesus sat over against the treasury, and beheld how the people cast money into the treasury: and many that were rich cast in much.
pairs.target:
41 Takal Yesus guluꞌ ngaduap topat nyaꞌa ngin duit tuduꞌ Topaꞌ deꞌ Boli
Topaꞌ, Yesus ningaꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kibalot duit-e daang kutak inoh. Bogoꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ kaya kibalot duit-e lobih bogoꞌ.

pairs.source: 42	And there came a certain poor widow, and she threw in two mites, which make a farthing.
pairs.target:
42 Ogiꞌ geh sinoꞌ janda deꞌ botak suwaꞌ odi, iyoh kibalot duwoh kiping
duit tibaga deꞌ mulah loga-e.

pairs.source: 43	And he called [unto him] his disciples, and saith unto them, Verily I say unto you, That this poor widow hath cast more in, than all they which have cast into the treasury:
pairs.target:
43 Yesus moꞌ mogan pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, Iyoh moꞌ sina, “Okuꞌ tanon tuduꞌ
ingan: Duit deꞌ kibalot sinoꞌ janda inoh lobih ayuh loga-e soꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ
bokon.

pairs.source: 44	For all [they] did cast in of their abundance; but she of her want did cast in all that she had, [even] all her living.
pairs.target:
44 Dop-e nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon ngin soꞌ lobih-e. Pak-e sinoꞌ janda inoh
bial yoh botak, iyoh ngin suaꞌ duit-e deꞌ ogiꞌ. Dop-e duam inoh jaꞌ-e duit-e
deꞌ ogiꞌ.”

pairs.source: 1	And as he went out of the temple, one of his disciples saith unto him, Master, see what manner of stones and what buildings [are here]!
pairs.target:
1 Takal Yesus luah soꞌ awah Boli Topaꞌ, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E sina tuduꞌ Yesus, “Gulu, suba ningaꞌ! Batuh-batuh
Boli Topaꞌ inoh sangon manah! Wat inoh geh duoh sinung-sinung-e!”

pairs.source: 2	And Jesus answering said unto him, Seest thou these great buildings? there shall not be left one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.
pairs.target:
2 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Suba ingan ningaꞌ batuh-batuh duoh
sinung-sinung deꞌ sangon inoh. Ogiꞌ onu takal-e suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ ningaꞌ
ingan itih yaꞌ asul. Niꞌ tuang doiꞌ geh deꞌ soꞌ suaꞌ Boli Topaꞌ inoh deꞌ yaꞌ
wat-wat-e geh, suaꞌ-e yaꞌ obuah pilubuh.”

pairs.source: 3	And as he sat upon the mount of Olives over against the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately,
pairs.target:
3 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ odi keꞌ Punguꞌ Zaitun,
Yoh moꞌ guluꞌ deꞌ topat deꞌ ngaduap Boli Topaꞌ. Petrus, Yakobus, Yohanes
duoh Andreas moꞌ nog tuduꞌ Yesus, ngan-e yaꞌ sikian sadiꞌ-e tuduꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 4	Tell us, when shall these things be? and what [shall be] the sign when all these things shall be fulfilled?
pairs.target:
4 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ sikian in-e, “Tanon tuduꞌ koꞌih siniaꞌ soꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ
yaꞌ jadi? Oni tanda-tanda suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ yaꞌ jadi, saꞌ koꞌih puꞌan-e?”

pairs.source: 5	And Jesus answering them began to say, Take heed lest any [man] deceive you:
pairs.target:
5 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Silalu jaga-jaga, maꞌ sape ingan obuah nipu odaꞌ
nyaꞌa pakai pingajal deꞌ salah!

pairs.source: 6	For many shall come in my name, saying, I am [Christ]; and shall deceive many.
pairs.target:
6 Yoh moꞌ bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ yaꞌ nog pakai adon
Okuꞌ yohmoꞌ sina nang, ‘Okuꞌ leh Laja Pinyilamat’, yoh moꞌ nipu nyaꞌa
deꞌ bogoꞌ.

pairs.source: 7	And when ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars, be ye not troubled: for [such things] must needs be; but the end [shall] not [be] yet.
pairs.target:
7 Simoꞌ ingan ngojit sowoꞌ polang duoh gah-gah polang, maꞌ yaꞌ
tolu. Suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ yaꞌ jadi. Pak-e aluaꞌ diꞌ-e kiamat.

pairs.source: 8	For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be earthquakes in divers places, and there shall be famines and troubles: these [are] the beginnings of sorrows.
pairs.target:
8 Bangsa deꞌ
niꞌ yaꞌ nyelang bangsa deꞌ bokon. Negli deꞌ niꞌ yaꞌ lawan negli deꞌ bokon.
Daki-daki-e yaꞌ ogiꞌ topat deꞌ tiguyang tigusuak, suaꞌ nyaꞌa yaꞌ sibolok.   
Pak-e suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ jadin puꞌun nyaꞌa yaꞌ mulai jolaꞌ soꞌ suaꞌ-e deꞌ
yaꞌ jadi. Samah kodaꞌ dayung bitiiaꞌ deꞌ mulai noman toꞌin-e monam yaꞌ
milaꞌ.

pairs.source: 9	But take heed to yourselves: for they shall deliver you up to councils; and in the synagogues ye shall be beaten: and ye shall be brought before rulers and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them.
pairs.target:
9 Pak-e ingan masim-masim ati-ati! Nyaꞌa yaꞌ takap ingan duoh toban keꞌ
Pengadilan Agama Yahudi. Yoh yaꞌ pijolaꞌ ingan deꞌ topat-topat simayang
agama Yahudi. Yoh toban ingan ngaduap piayuh-piayuh duoh laja-laja.
Suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ yaꞌ obuah ingan, dop-e ingan pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Okuꞌ.
Inoh leh onu-e saꞌ ingan tapod magah Gah deꞌ Paguh tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 10	And the gospel must first be published among all nations.
pairs.target:
10 Gah deꞌ Paguh inoh halus lobih dioꞌ nyeꞌ magah-e tuduꞌ suaꞌ
bangsa takal onu kiamat aluaꞌ diꞌ-e nog.

pairs.source: 11	But when they shall lead [you], and deliver you up, take no thought beforehand what ye shall speak, neither do ye premeditate: but whatsoever shall be given you in that hour, that speak ye: for it is not ye that speak, but the Holy Ghost.
pairs.target:
11 Simoꞌ ingan obuah takap duoh
obuah toban keꞌ topat nyaꞌa bilituang, maꞌ bigaduh oni in sina deꞌ yaꞌ nang
ingan. Pak-e tanon negeh oni in deꞌ tanon Iyang Topaꞌ tuduꞌ ingan takal
inoh. Sibonal-e idoh diꞌ-e soꞌ odop ingan deꞌ tanon in inoh, Iyang Topaꞌ leh
deꞌ odaꞌ ingan tanon-e.

pairs.source: 12	Now the brother shall betray the brother to death, and the father the son; and children shall rise up against [their] parents, and shall cause them to be put to death.
pairs.target:
12 Takal inoh yaꞌ ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ ngin madih-e odaꞌ
nyaꞌa ngabos-e. Samaꞌ ngin onak-e deꞌ nyaꞌa odaꞌ ngabos-e. Wat noh geh
onak-e ngin pingoma-e, odaꞌ nyaꞌa ngabos-e.

pairs.source: 13	And ye shall be hated of all [men] for my name’s sake: but he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.
pairs.target:
13 Bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ yaꞌ buꞌui
tuduꞌ ingan dop-e ingan jadin pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Okuꞌ. Pak-e nyaꞌa deꞌ taan
naan nog piobuaꞌ idip-e yoh leh deꞌ yaꞌ silamat.”

pairs.source: 14	But when ye shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing where it ought not, (let him that readeth understand,) then let them that be in Judaea flee to the mountains:
pairs.target:
14 “Ingan yaꞌ ningaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ sisiꞌ nyaꞌa daꞌ-a duoh oniꞌ deꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa
kobos tulah deꞌ yaꞌ mujuag daang Boli Topaꞌ ngan-e yaꞌ kaꞌis-e, topat
deꞌ diꞌ-e soꞌon yoh molot daang-e. (Nyaꞌa deꞌ basa itih halus bonal-bonal
ngiloti hal itih.) Takal inoh ulang-ulang deꞌ loꞌo deꞌ propinsi Yudea halus
bikoduh buu keꞌ dolod-dolod.

pairs.source: 15	And let him that is on the housetop not go down into the house, neither enter [therein], to take any thing out of his house:
pairs.target:
15 Ayua deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ tun bungan boli-e, maꞌ
tiyaꞌ yaꞌ muun kalik oniꞌ kaang boli, lasuꞌ negeh bikoduh buu.

pairs.source: 16	And let him that is in the field not turn back again for to take up his garment.
pairs.target:
16 Nyaꞌa
deꞌ aluaꞌ kiloja deꞌ umoh-e, maꞌ tiyaꞌ yaꞌ moliꞌ mit pimakai-e.

pairs.source: 17	But woe to them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days!
pairs.target:
17 Takal onu
inoh, todah mun sinoꞌ-sinoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ balut duoh deꞌ aluaꞌ siduaꞌ onak-e.

pairs.source: 18	And pray ye that your flight be not in the winter.
pairs.target: 18 Bidoa leh tuduꞌ Topaꞌ, saꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ munoꞌ diꞌ-e nog takal musim modud.

pairs.source: 19	For [in] those days shall be affliction, such as was not from the beginning of the creation which God created unto this time, neither shall be.
pairs.target:
19 Dop-e takal inoh nyaꞌa yaꞌ sukup jolaꞌ-e, deꞌ doiꞌ onu nyaꞌa obuah-e,
mulai soꞌ sibungas Topaꞌ nai dunia nog adin. Susah jolaꞌ inoh diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ yaꞌ
obuah dunia.

pairs.source: 20	And except that the Lord had shortened those days, no flesh should be saved: but for the elect’s sake, whom he hath chosen, he hath shortened the days.
pairs.target:
20 Simoꞌ Topaꞌ diꞌ-e sagot onu jolaꞌ inoh, doiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ taan
bitaan idip. Pak-e Topaꞌ masiꞌ tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ pilih-E odaꞌ nunaꞌ odop-E,
yoh ngan-e sagot onu-e.

pairs.source: 21	And then if any man shall say to you, Lo, here [is] Christ; or, lo, [he is] there; believe [him] not:
pairs.target:
21 Takal inoh, simoꞌ ogiꞌ nyaꞌa nang, ‘Ningaꞌ Laja Pinyilamat ogiꞌ datiꞌ,
ogiꞌ danih,’ maꞌ yaꞌ bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 22	For false Christs and false prophets shall rise, and shall shew signs and wonders, to seduce, if [it were] possible, even the elect.
pairs.target:
22 Dop-e nyaꞌa deꞌ ngakuꞌ odop-e Laja  Pinyilamat duoh nabi-nabi pibulaꞌ yaꞌ nog. Iyoh bogoꞌ nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan
nyaꞌa ngan-e yaꞌ nipu nyaꞌa, nog nyaꞌa deꞌ bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Topaꞌ deꞌ moꞌ
pilih-E, tadoꞌ-tadoꞌ-e yaꞌ obuah nipu geh.

pairs.source: 23	But take ye heed: behold, I have foretold you all things.
pairs.target:
23 Jadin maꞌ tauꞌ-tauꞌ bisayaꞌ, suaꞌ-e moꞌ dioꞌ Kuꞌ tanon-e tuduꞌ ingan
takal-e aluaꞌ diꞌ-e jadi.”

pairs.source: 24	But in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light,
pairs.target:
24 “Pak-e takal-e moꞌ mokuaꞌ onu-onu nyaꞌa jolaꞌ inoh, boton onu
yaꞌ mopung, bulan diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ jawaꞌ.

pairs.source: 25	And the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken.
pairs.target:
25 Bitang-bitang obuaꞌ luluh duoh
kuasa-kuasa deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ longit obuaꞌ tiguyang.

pairs.source: 26	And then shall they see the Son of man coming in the clouds with great power and glory.
pairs.target:
26 Takal inoh nyaꞌa yaꞌ ningaꞌ Onak Manusia nog deꞌ abun pakai kuasa-e
deꞌ ayuh duoh jawaꞌ-e deꞌ telang.

pairs.source: 27	And then shall he send his angels, and shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from the uttermost part of the earth to the uttermost part of heaven.
pairs.target:
27 Yoh moꞌ odaꞌ malaikat-malaikat odi nguluk nyaꞌa deꞌ moꞌ pilih-e odaꞌ
nunaꞌ odop-e, deꞌ ogiꞌ deꞌ suaꞌ tun dunia itih, soꞌ nyuang bumi nog tubon
longit.

pairs.source: 28	Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When her branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is near:
pairs.target:
28 Bilajal leh soꞌ silita tongon ara. Takal daꞌan-daꞌan-e moꞌ dodot duoh
mulai ngilotad, onu moꞌ yaꞌ logaꞌ.
