pairs.source: 29	So ye in like manner, when ye shall see these things come to pass, know that it is nigh, [even] at the doors.
pairs.target:
29 Wat inoh geh moꞌ ingan ningaꞌ moꞌ ogiꞌ tanda-tanda deꞌ tanon Kuꞌ
tiꞌ-e, inoh loti-e moꞌ sinok onu-e. Duam-e yaꞌ nog.

pairs.source: 30	Verily I say unto you, that this generation shall not pass, till all these things be done.
pairs.target:
30 Ngojit bonal-bonal-e!
Suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ mutiꞌ yaꞌ jadi takal nyaꞌa deꞌ idip adin aluaꞌ diꞌ-e suaꞌ-e
kobos.

pairs.source: 31	Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away.
pairs.target:
31 Longit duoh tanaꞌ yaꞌ musuap, pak-e pingunang Kuꞌ totap ogiꞌ
silamaꞌ-lamaꞌ-e.”

pairs.source: 32	But of that day and [that] hour knoweth no man, no, not the angels which are in heaven, neither the Son, but the Father.
pairs.target:
32 “Pak-e siniaꞌ onu-e duoh siniaꞌ takal-e yaꞌ jadi doiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ puꞌan,
malaikat deꞌ siluga tuang doh geh diꞌ-e puꞌan-e. Pak-e jok-e Samaꞌ deꞌ
siluga deꞌ puꞌan. Onak-E tuang idoh geh diꞌ-e puꞌan-e.

pairs.source: 33	Take ye heed, watch and pray: for ye know not when the time is.
pairs.target:
33 Maꞌ tauꞌ-tauꞌ duoh silalu jaga-jaga! Dop-e ingan diꞌ ingan puꞌan siniaꞌ
takal-e.

pairs.source: 34	[For the Son of man is] as a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and commanded the porter to watch.
pairs.target:
34 Onak Manusia yaꞌ nog samah kodaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ yaꞌ buu togan
boli-e. Takal-e aluaꞌ diꞌ-e buu, yoh moꞌ bikutung kiloja tuduꞌ kuli-kuli-e
odaꞌ ngatul boli-e. Yoh sibaya tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tukang jaga tiban-e, maꞌ
sape yoh yaꞌ komut kiloja-e nog nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ boli paliꞌ. Mokuaꞌ inoh ke
yoh moꞌ odi keꞌ topat deꞌ juuaꞌ.

pairs.source: 35	Watch ye therefore: for ye know not when the master of the house cometh, at even, or at midnight, or at the cockcrowing, or in the morning:
pairs.target:
35 Inoh leh ngan nyeꞌ silalu jaga singonu
singalom, dop-e diꞌ ingan puꞌan siniaꞌ takal-e nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ boli inoh yaꞌ
nog. An onu ngumi, an tuluap ngalom, an suam-suam pagi, an takal boton   
onu moꞌ tumuꞌ.

pairs.source: 36	Lest coming suddenly he find you sleeping.
pairs.target:
36 Saꞌ-e simoꞌ iyoh tang-tang nog, maꞌ sape iyoh nog ningaꞌ
ingan aluaꞌ boꞌos.

pairs.source: 37	And what I say unto you I say unto all, Watch.
pairs.target:
37 Oni deꞌ tanon Kuꞌ tuduꞌ ingan, Kuꞌ tanon geh tuduꞌ
suaꞌ nyaꞌa: Maꞌ tauꞌ-tauꞌ duoh silalu jaga-jaga!”

pairs.source: 1	After two days was [the feast of] the passover, and of unleavened bread: and the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by craft, and put [him] to death.
pairs.target:
1 Duwoh onu lagiꞌ ulang Yahudi yaꞌ nyamut Onu Ayuh Paskah duoh
nyamut Onu Ayuh Kueh deꞌ doiꞌ Ragi-e. Pimipin-pimipin agama
Yahudi deꞌ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu agama Yahudi yaꞌ takap duoh yaꞌ ngabos
Yesus. Pak-e odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ doliaꞌ-e odaꞌ nyaꞌa puꞌan oni deꞌ yaꞌ nai-e.

pairs.source: 2	But they said, Not on the feast [day], lest there be an uproar of the people.
pairs.target:
2 Yoh moꞌ bipokat diꞌ-e takap Yesus daang onu ayuh, in odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ,
“Maꞌ sape oniꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ nai otoꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ nang liuak daluag-e.”

pairs.source: 3	And being in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he sat at meat, there came a woman having an alabaster box of ointment of spikenard very precious; and she brake the box, and poured [it] on his head.
pairs.target:
3 Yesus aluaꞌ loꞌo deꞌ kupuaꞌ Betania, iyoh moꞌ odi boli Simon, nyaꞌa
deꞌ dioꞌ soꞌ kanoꞌ obuah onam kulit deꞌ bijakit. Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
julah-e man, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan dayung nog toban niꞌ jobul inyuaꞌ wangi deꞌ
maal loga-e, duoh jobul-e tuang maal geh. Yoh moꞌ mugat tunguaꞌ jobul
inoh yohmoꞌ duwan inyuaꞌ inoh deꞌ tun bak Yesus.

pairs.source: 4	And there were some that had indignation within themselves, and said, Why was this waste of the ointment made?
pairs.target:
4 Pak-e ogiꞌ kudu-kudu
naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ moꞌ malah, daang-e sina tipan odop-e, “Nai oni
saꞌat inyuaꞌ deꞌ maal wat inoh?

pairs.source: 5	For it might have been sold for more than three hundred pence, and have been given to the poor. And they murmured against her.
pairs.target:
5 Lobih paguh nyeꞌ jua negeh inyuaꞌ wangi
inoh! Loga-e samah duoh gaji nyaꞌa kiloja deꞌ niꞌ sowaꞌ. Duit-e tapod nyeꞌ
bikutung tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ sotok!” Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ malah tuduꞌ dayung
inoh.

pairs.source: 6	And Jesus said, Let her alone; why trouble ye her? she hath wrought a good work on me.
pairs.target:
6 Yesus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Tanah negeh! Doiꞌ nyeꞌ jolaꞌ
malah tuduꞌ-e. Iyoh nai oniꞌ deꞌ paling paguh-e saꞌan Okuꞌ.

pairs.source: 7	For ye have the poor with you always, and whensoever ye will ye may do them good: but me ye have not always.
pairs.target:
7 Dop-e nyaꞌa
deꞌ sotok, silalu ogiꞌ sinok ingan, siniaꞌ sijaꞌ-e ingan tapod tulung-e. Pak-e
Okuꞌ diꞌ kuꞌ silamaꞌ-lamaꞌ-e yaꞌ duoh ingan.

pairs.source: 8	She hath done what she could: she is come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying.
pairs.target:
8 Dayung itih moꞌ nai oni deꞌ
tapod yoh nai-e tuduꞌ Okuꞌ, iyoh moꞌ dioꞌ ngiyuaꞌ gonan-Kuꞌ takal Kuꞌ aluaꞌ
idip. Inoh samah geh iyoh ngiyuaꞌ todang Kuꞌ takal Kuꞌ kobos.

pairs.source: 9	Verily I say unto you, Wheresoever this gospel shall be preached throughout the whole world, [this] also that she hath done shall be spoken of for a memorial of her.
pairs.target:
9 Natong
bonal-bonal-e! Daki sijaꞌ-e nyaꞌa magah Gah deꞌ Paguh tentang Okuꞌ deꞌ
tun dunia itih, wat inoh geh nyaꞌa silita oni deꞌ moꞌ nai dayung itih. Saꞌ
nyaꞌa silalu natong oniꞌ deꞌ moꞌ nai-e tuduꞌ Okuꞌ adin.”

pairs.source: 10	And Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve, went unto the chief priests, to betray him unto them.
pairs.target:
10 Yudas Iskariot, niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ simoong duwoh pinunaꞌ Yesus inoh, moꞌ
odi tuduꞌ pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh ngan-e yaꞌ nyelah Yesus
tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 11	And when they heard [it], they were glad, and promised to give him money. And he sought how he might conveniently betray him.
pairs.target:
11 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sukup doon-e ngojit oniꞌ
deꞌ tanon-e, yoh moꞌ bipokat yaꞌ ngin duit tuduꞌ Yudas. Yudas moꞌ kalik
wat olan ngan-e yaꞌ nyelah Yesus tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 12	And the first day of unleavened bread, when they killed the passover, his disciples said unto him, Where wilt thou that we go and prepare that thou mayest eat the passover?
pairs.target:
12 Takal onu keꞌ niꞌ-e nyaꞌa nyamut Onu Ayuh Kueh deꞌ doiꞌ Ragi-e,
daang onu inoh nyaꞌa mulai simoliah domba ngan-e yaꞌ nyamut Onu Ayuh
Paskah. Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ bisikian tuduꞌ Yesus, “Gulu, daki topat soꞌ
otoꞌ yaꞌ man nyamut Onu Ayuh Paskah? Saꞌ koꞌih sidia pinguman deꞌ topat
inoh.”

pairs.source: 13	And he sendeth forth two of his disciples, and saith unto them, Go ye into the city, and there shall meet you a man bearing a pitcher of water: follow him.
pairs.target:
13 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ pait duwoh naꞌan pinunaꞌ-e yohmoꞌ sibaya
tuduꞌ-e, “Odi kaang kota. Danih ingan yaꞌ bitapod duoh niꞌ naꞌan dali deꞌ
toban kobuk deꞌ punuaꞌ odaꞌ piꞌin, nyeꞌ moꞌ ponu bitunaꞌ duoh-e.

pairs.source: 14	And wheresoever he shall go in, say ye to the goodman of the house, The Master saith, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?
pairs.target:
14 Takal
iyoh molot kaang boli, nyeꞌ moꞌ tanon tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ boli, ‘Gulu
sikian daki aluang boli topat Iyoh duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E yaꞌ man nyamut
Onu Ayuh Paskah?’

pairs.source: 15	And he will shew you a large upper room furnished [and] prepared: there make ready for us.
pairs.target:
15 Nyaꞌa deꞌ kakuꞌ boli inoh moꞌ yaꞌ tanon tuduꞌ ingan,
ogiꞌ niꞌ aluang deꞌ longah deꞌ ayuh, deꞌ moꞌ suaꞌ-e siap oniꞌ daang-e. Danoꞌ
leh ingan sidia pinguman ngan toꞌ nyamut Paskah.”

pairs.source: 16	And his disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found as he had said unto them: and they made ready the passover.
pairs.target:
16 Mokuaꞌ odop-e deꞌ duwoh ngojit sibaya Yesus, yoh moꞌ odi molot
kaang kota. Danoꞌ yoh bitapod duoh nyaꞌa, bonal-bonal samah kodaꞌ deꞌ
tanon Yesus. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sidia pinguman ngan-e nyamut Onu
ayuh Paskah danoꞌ.

pairs.source: 17	And in the evening he cometh with the twelve.
pairs.target:
17 Takal onu moꞌ ngalom, Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-E deꞌ simoong duwoh
naꞌan moꞌ odi keꞌ boli inoh.

pairs.source: 18	And as they sat and did eat, Jesus said, Verily I say unto you, One of you which eateth with me shall betray me.
pairs.target:
18 Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ julah-e man, Yesus
moꞌ sina, “Natong bonal-bonal-e! Ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ ingan deꞌ mutiꞌ deꞌ yaꞌ
nyelah Okuꞌ tuduꞌ musuh-musuh Kuꞌ. Odop-e ogiꞌ man samah-samah duoh
Okuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 19	And they began to be sorrowful, and to say unto him one by one, [Is] it I? and another [said, Is] it I?
pairs.target:
19 Takal-e ngojit sina Yesus inoh, pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ susah kila-e.
Yoh moꞌ masim-masim sina nang, “Okuꞌ keh idoh, Gulu?”

pairs.source: 20	And he answered and said unto them, [It is] one of the twelve, that dippeth with me in the dish.
pairs.target:
20 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Ogiꞌ odop-e datiꞌ, soꞌ simoong duwoh naꞌan
pinunaꞌ Kuꞌ itih, deꞌ man niꞌ pingian samah-samah duoh Okuꞌ.

pairs.source: 21	The Son of man indeed goeth, as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! good were it for that man if he had never been born.
pairs.target:
21 Onak
Manusia tok yaꞌ kobos, nunaꞌ deꞌ moꞌ obuah nulis daang Kitab, pak-e nyaꞌa   
deꞌ nyelah Iyoh yaꞌ tulah idip-e. Lobih paguh moꞌ-e yoh diꞌ-e obuah milaꞌ
daang dunia itih.”

pairs.source: 22	And as they did eat, Jesus took bread, and blessed, and brake [it], and gave to them, and said, Take, eat: this is my body.
pairs.target:
22 Takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ aluaꞌ man, Yesus moꞌ mit kueh, yohmoꞌ
bisukul tuduꞌ Topaꞌ. Iyoh moꞌ nyipiak kutung tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-E daang-e in-e,
“Mit nyeꞌ moꞌ man-e, itih gonan Kuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 23	And he took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave [it] to them: and they all drank of it.
pairs.target:
23 Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ mit sakil deꞌ ogiꞌ piꞌin anggul daang-e, yoh moꞌ
bisukul tuduꞌ Topaꞌ. Mokuaꞌ inoh Iyoh moꞌ ngin tuduꞌ suaꞌ pinunaꞌ-E nuak
soꞌ sakil inoh.

pairs.source: 24	And he said unto them, This is my blood of the new testament, which is shed for many.
pairs.target:
24 Yoh moꞌ sina lagi, “Itih doyaꞌ Kuꞌ, doyaꞌ deꞌ nogap janyi
Topaꞌ duoh manusia, doyaꞌ deꞌ soyang saꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ.

pairs.source: 25	Verily I say unto you, I will drink no more of the fruit of the vine, until that day that I drink it new in the kingdom of God.
pairs.target:
25 Natong
bonal-bonal-e! Tok idoh diꞌ Kuꞌ tiyaꞌ nuak piꞌin soꞌ buaꞌ anggul nog onu
Okuꞌ nuak soꞌ buaꞌ anggul deꞌ baꞌuh takal Topaꞌ nog militah jadin Laja.”

pairs.source: 26	And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives.
pairs.target:
26 Mokuaꞌ inoh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ ngilagu mudi Topaꞌ yohmoꞌ odi keꞌ
Punguꞌ Zaitun.

pairs.source: 27	And Jesus saith unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night: for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered.
pairs.target:
27 Takal-e aluaꞌ daang olan, Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E,
“Suaꞌ ingan yaꞌ buu togan Okuꞌ, dop-e ogiꞌ deꞌ nulis daang Kitab, ‘Topaꞌ yaꞌ
ngabos nyaꞌa deꞌ tukang jaga koming domba-e, yoh moꞌ koming domba-e
yaꞌ buu katiꞌ kanih.’

pairs.source: 28	But after that I am risen, I will go before you into Galilee.
pairs.target:
28 Pak-e takal Okuꞌ yaꞌ paliꞌ idip, Okuꞌ yaꞌ dioꞌ kajon
ingan deꞌ Galilea.”

pairs.source: 29	But Peter said unto him, Although all shall be offended, yet [will] not I.
pairs.target:
29 Petrus moꞌ in-e nyawot Yesus, “Okuꞌ idoh! Simoꞌ nyaꞌa buu togan
Ingan, okuꞌ totap idoh!”

pairs.source: 30	And Jesus saith unto him, Verily I say unto thee, That this day, [even] in this night, before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice.
pairs.target:
30 Yesus moꞌ nyawot Petrus, in-E, “Natong bonal-bonal-e! Ngalom itih
geh takal babang siuak aluaꞌ diꞌ-e bitadu duwoh sidoh, muꞌu moꞌ taluh
sidoh sukan nang odop muꞌ diꞌ muꞌ piluh Okuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 31	But he spake the more vehemently, If I should die with thee, I will not deny thee in any wise. Likewise also said they all.
pairs.target:
31 Pak-e Petrus isin-isin in-e, “Simoꞌ okuꞌ tipaksa suwaꞌ kobos duoh
Ingan, idoh geh diꞌ kuꞌ sukan nang odop kuꞌ diꞌ kuꞌ piluh Ingan.”
Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus deꞌ bokon tuang inoh geh in-e.

pairs.source: 32	And they came to a place which was named Gethsemane: and he saith to his disciples, Sit ye here, while I shall pray.
pairs.target: 32 Yesus duoh pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E nog keꞌ topat deꞌ adon Getsemani. Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, “Guluꞌ datiꞌ dioꞌ, Okuꞌ yaꞌ odi bidoa.”

pairs.source: 33	And he taketh with him Peter and James and John, and began to be sore amazed, and to be very heavy;
pairs.target:
33 Yesus moꞌ ngijaꞌ Petrus, Yakobus duoh Yohanes odi duoh odop-E.
Yesus sikiya nyam kila-E tolu, otin-e ulih-ulih susah.

pairs.source: 34	And saith unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful unto death: tarry ye here, and watch.
pairs.target:
34 Iyoh moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ
odop-e deꞌ taluh inoh, “Ulih-ulih nyam susah otin Kuꞌ sape yaꞌ kobos nyam
Kuꞌ odaꞌ-e. Loꞌo kajon datiꞌ maꞌ yaꞌ boꞌos!”

pairs.source: 35	And he went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.
pairs.target:
35 Yesus moꞌ ponu muaꞌ juꞌan-e soꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ. Yoh moꞌ guluꞌ
bikunyug nog jowin-E obuah tanaꞌ, ngan-e bidoa. Daang doa-E, Iyoh mitiaꞌ
tuduꞌ Topaꞌ, moꞌ-e tapod saꞌ susah jolaꞌ diꞌ-e obuah odop-E.

pairs.source: 36	And he said, Abba, Father, all things [are] possible unto thee; take away this cup from me: nevertheless not what I will, but what thou wilt.
pairs.target:
36 Iyoh bidoa
in-e, “Oi Samaꞌ Kuꞌ! Suaꞌ oniꞌ tapod Ingan nai-e. Okuꞌ mitiaꞌ saꞌ Ingan odaꞌ
Okuꞌ lopas soꞌ susah jolaꞌ itih. Pak-e nai negeh kodaꞌ deꞌ laꞌan Ingan, idoh
diꞌ-e kodaꞌ deꞌ laꞌan Okuꞌ.”

pairs.source: 37	And he cometh, and findeth them sleeping, and saith unto Peter, Simon, sleepest thou? couldest not thou watch one hour?
pairs.target:
37 Mokuaꞌ bidoa Yesus moꞌ paliꞌ tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-E deꞌ taluh naꞌan inoh.
Iyoh moꞌ ningaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ boꞌos, yohmoꞌ in-e tuduꞌ Simon
Petrus, “Simon, boꞌos yeh muꞌu neh? Idoh diꞌ muꞌ taan nijon boton muꞌ
niꞌ jam negeh?”

pairs.source: 38	Watch ye and pray, lest ye enter into temptation. The spirit truly [is] ready, but the flesh [is] weak.
pairs.target:
38 Yesus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, in-e, “Silalu
jaga-jaga duoh bidoa, saꞌ diꞌ ingan nai oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat. Otin kila ingan laꞌan-e
yaꞌ nai oniꞌ deꞌ bonal, pak-e gonan ingan deꞌ diꞌ-e taan.”

pairs.source: 39	And again he went away, and prayed, and spake the same words.
pairs.target:
39 Yesus moꞌ odi lagiꞌ muaꞌ juꞌan-e soꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E, yohmoꞌ
bidoa samah kodaꞌ in deꞌ tiꞌ-e.

pairs.source: 40	And when he returned, he found them asleep again, (for their eyes were heavy,) neither wist they what to answer him.
pairs.target:
40 Mokuaꞌ bidoa, Yesus paliꞌ lagiꞌ tuduꞌ
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ obuaꞌ boꞌos, dop-e diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ taan
nijon boton-e. Takal Yesus guyang odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ yohmoꞌ sina tuduꞌ-e,
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ diꞌ-e tiyaꞌ puꞌan oni in-e yaꞌ nyawot Yesus.

pairs.source: 41	And he cometh the third time, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take [your] rest: it is enough, the hour is come; behold, the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
pairs.target:
41 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ paliꞌ keꞌ taluh sidoh-e. Iyoh moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Aluaꞌ boꞌos keh ingan? Moh tiyaꞌ! Ningaꞌ Onak Manusia
obuah nyelah tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bidosa.

pairs.source: 42	Rise up, let us go; lo, he that betrayeth me is at hand.
pairs.target:
42 Mokat tiyaꞌ, jaꞌ toꞌ buu. Ningaꞌ!
Nyaꞌa deꞌ yaꞌ nyelah Okuꞌ moꞌ nog!”

pairs.source: 43	And immediately, while he yet spake, cometh Judas, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.
pairs.target:
43 Takal Yesus aluaꞌ sina, tang-tang mun Yudas nog. Yudas itih niꞌ naꞌan
soꞌ simoong duwoh pinunaꞌ Yesus. Yudas nog samah-samah duoh nyaꞌa
deꞌ bogoꞌ deꞌ toban podang duoh pakung. Ayua pimipin agama Yahudi
deꞌ ayuh, gulu-gulu agama duoh pimipin ulang Yahudi deꞌ bokon deꞌ pait
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ odaꞌ odi saꞌ-e takap Yesus.

pairs.source: 44	And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he; take him, and lead [him] away safely.
pairs.target:
44 Yudas, nyaꞌa deꞌ nyelah   
Yesus, moꞌ dioꞌ tanon tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ in-e, “Nyaꞌa deꞌ sium kuꞌ tiaꞌ
inoh leh odop-E. Takap Iyoh nyeꞌ moꞌ ngawal toban buu.”

pairs.source: 45	And as soon as he was come, he goeth straightway to him, and saith, Master, master; and kissed him.
pairs.target:
45 Takal Yudas nog yoh moꞌ lasuꞌ odi tuduꞌ Yesus yoh moꞌ in-e “Gulu!”
Yoh moꞌ sium Yesus.

pairs.source: 46	And they laid their hands on him, and took him.
pairs.target:
46 Ayua deꞌ munoꞌ lasuꞌ takap-E yohmoꞌ bikagong
duoh-E.

pairs.source: 47	And one of them that stood by drew a sword, and smote a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.
pairs.target:
47 Niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ ayua deꞌ nunaꞌ Yesus nyitak podang-e, yoh moꞌ
lasuꞌ kawiang podang-e nyopaꞌ kuli pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ paling ayuh.
Kojit-e moꞌ lasuꞌ sopial.

pairs.source: 48	And Jesus answered and said unto them, Are ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and [with] staves to take me?
pairs.target:
48 Yesus moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ ayua deꞌ nog takap odop-E,
“Baꞌ ingan nang Okuꞌ pinyamun? Ingan nog sape toban podang, toban
pakung ngan ingan takap Okuꞌ.

pairs.source: 49	I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and ye took me not: but the scriptures must be fulfilled.
pairs.target:
49 Tibilang konu Okuꞌ samah-samah ngajal
deꞌ awah Boli Topaꞌ deꞌ jowin ingan, pak-e doiꞌ nak ingan takap Okuꞌ danoꞌ.
Pak-e adin takap leh Okuꞌ, saꞌ-e bonal-bonal samah kodaꞌ deꞌ obuah nulis
daang Kitab.”

pairs.source: 50	And they all forsook him, and fled.
pairs.target: 50 Mokuaꞌ inoh suaꞌ pinunaꞌ-E bikoduh buu togan Iyoh.

pairs.source: 51	And there followed him a certain young man, having a linen cloth cast about [his] naked [body]; and the young men laid hold on him:
pairs.target:
51 Takal inoh, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan onak mudaꞌ deꞌ jok-e bisabuak kain ngan-e
nutu gonan-e bitunaꞌ duoh Yesus. Ayua deꞌ munoꞌ yaꞌ nyonguam takap-e.

pairs.source: 52	And he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked.
pairs.target: 52 Kain deꞌ gonan-e moꞌ lusut yoh moꞌ bikoduh buu sitagual.

pairs.source:
53	And they led Jesus away to the high priest: and with him were assembled all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes.
  54	And Peter followed him afar off, even into the palace of the high priest: and he sat with the servants, and warmed himself at the fire.
  55	And the chief priests and all the council sought for witness against Jesus to put him to death; and found none.
pairs.target:
55 Mokuaꞌ inoh ayua deꞌ munoꞌ toban Yesus odi keꞌ boli pimipin
agama deꞌ paling ayuh. Yohmoꞌ suaꞌ pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ
ayuh, pimipin-pimipin Yahudi deꞌ bokon duoh gulu-gulu agama tikuluk
danoꞌ. Pak-e Petrus nunaꞌ Yesus soꞌ juuaꞌ nog keꞌ limang boli pimipin agama
Yahudi deꞌ paling ayuh. Iyoh moꞌ guluꞌ ngosah nyaꞌa deꞌ jaga simadi-e
ngunuh sinok opui. Pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh duoh suaꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ daang pengadilan agama kalik bukti ngan-e yaꞌ nyalah Yesus
saꞌ-e tapod ngukum Yesus odaꞌ kobos, pak-e doiꞌ-e nak tapod salah Yesus.

pairs.source: 56	For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together.
pairs.target:
56 Bogoꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ mokat nang sina pibulaꞌ-e ngan-e nyalah Yesus, pak-e
oniꞌ deꞌ nang odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ diꞌ-e niꞌ in.

pairs.source: 57	And there arose certain, and bare false witness against him, saying,
pairs.target:
57 Yohmoꞌ kudu-kudu naꞌan odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ mujuag nang sina pibulaꞌ
napo Yesus in-e,

pairs.source: 58	We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.
pairs.target:
58 “Koꞌih moꞌ ngojit Yoh itih sina, ‘Okuꞌ yaꞌ pilubuh Boli
Topaꞌ itih deꞌ obuah nai tongan manusia. Daang taluh onu Okuꞌ yaꞌ kajuag
deꞌ baꞌuh deꞌ diꞌ-e tongan manusia deꞌ nai.’ ”

pairs.source: 59	But neither so did their witness agree together.
pairs.target:
59 Pak-e oniꞌ deꞌ nang nyaꞌa
deꞌ munoꞌ tuang idoh geh diꞌ-e niꞌ in.

pairs.source: 60	And the high priest stood up in the midst, and asked Jesus, saying, Answerest thou nothing? what [is it which] these witness against thee?
pairs.target:
60 Pimipin agama deꞌ paling ayuh mokat mujuag deꞌ uun odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ. Iyoh moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ Yesus in-e, “Idoh diꞌ muꞌ yaꞌ nyawot sina
nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ deꞌ napo Muꞌu neh?”

pairs.source: 61	But he held his peace, and answered nothing. Again the high priest asked him, and said unto him, Art thou the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?
pairs.target:
61 Pak-e Yesus loꞌo jaꞌ-e, diꞌ-e nyawot-e. Pimipin agama deꞌ paling ayuh
sikian niꞌ sidoh lagiꞌ in-e, “Podo Muꞌu yeh Laja Pinyilamat Onak Topaꞌ deꞌ
nyomah toꞌ?”

pairs.source: 62	And Jesus said, I am: and ye shall see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.
pairs.target:
62 Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Bonal, Okuꞌ leh Odop-E. Suaꞌ ingan yaꞌ ningaꞌ
Onak Manusia guluꞌ nuaꞌ toꞌuh Topaꞌ deꞌ Ayuh Kuasa-E. Yohmoꞌ ingan yaꞌ
ningaꞌ Iyoh yaꞌ nog daang abun!”

pairs.source: 63	Then the high priest rent his clothes, and saith, What need we any further witnesses?
pairs.target:
63 Pimipin agama deꞌ paling ayuh inoh moꞌ notak pimakai-e, yoh in-e,
“Dusah tiyaꞌ toꞌ sikian tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon neh!

pairs.source: 64	Ye have heard the blasphemy: what think ye? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death.
pairs.target:
64 Ingan moꞌ ngojit sina-E
deꞌ nguyat Topaꞌ. Oni wat otoꞌ yaꞌ duoh Iyoh itih?”
Yohmoꞌ suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ situju Yesus halus obuah ukum ngabos.

pairs.source: 65	And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him, and to say unto him, Prophesy: and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands.
pairs.target:
65 Mokuaꞌ inoh kudu-kudu naꞌan nyaꞌa mulai ngujaꞌ-E. Nyaꞌa deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ kuab jowin Yesus yoh moꞌ bibokut duoh-E daang-e in-e tuduꞌ-E, “Suba
sobot, osi deꞌ bokut Muꞌu tih?” Nyaꞌa deꞌ jaga danoꞌ suwaꞌ bitapal duoh-E.

pairs.source: 66	And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there cometh one of the maids of the high priest:
pairs.target:
66 Takal Petrus aluaꞌ ogiꞌ guluꞌ deꞌ limang boli pimipin agama deꞌ paling
ayuh, ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan kuli-e deꞌ dayung nog kanoꞌ.

pairs.source: 67	And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked upon him, and said, And thou also wast with Jesus of Nazareth.
pairs.target:
67 Takal-e ningaꞌ Petrus
guluꞌ ngunuh kibangoh gonan-e sinok opui, yoh moꞌ bonal-bonal ngibotoh
jowin Petrus. Iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Bah idoh diꞌ-e ingan itih deꞌ silalu nunaꞌ
Yesus ulang Nazaret inoh neh?”

pairs.source: 68	But he denied, saying, I know not, neither understand I what thou sayest. And he went out into the porch; and the cock crew.
pairs.target:
68 Pak-e yoh moꞌ sukan-e. Iyoh moꞌ in-e, “Okuꞌ diꞌ kuꞌ puꞌan oni deꞌ nang
muꞌ inoh.” Mokuaꞌ inoh Petrus moꞌ buu keꞌ limang deꞌ sinok tiban pagal
boli pimipin agama deꞌ paling ayuh. Takal inoh geh babang siuak bitadu.

pairs.source: 69	And a maid saw him again, and began to say to them that stood by, This is [one] of them.
pairs.target:
69 Takal kuli deꞌ dayung inoh ningaꞌ Petrus lagiꞌ, yoh moꞌ in-e tuduꞌ
nyaꞌa deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ, “Iyoh itih ulang deꞌ silalu bitunaꞌ duoh Yesus.”

pairs.source: 70	And he denied it again. And a little after, they that stood by said again to Peter, Surely thou art [one] of them: for thou art a Galilaean, and thy speech agreeth [thereto].
pairs.target:
70 Pak-e
Petrus aluaꞌ geh sukan-e. Aluaꞌ diꞌ-e tuui mokuaꞌ inoh, nyaꞌa danoꞌ in-e
lagiꞌ tuduꞌ Petrus, “Diꞌ muꞌ tiyaꞌ ponai sukan-e. Muꞌu pasti soꞌ ayua deꞌ
munoꞌ dop-e muꞌu ulang Galilea.”

pairs.source: 71	But he began to curse and to swear, [saying], I know not this man of whom ye speak.
pairs.target:
71 Petrus moꞌ sina bisupah in-e, “Doiꞌ kuꞌ piluh osi deꞌ nang ingan inoh
neh! Asal kuꞌ pibulaꞌ, tanah saꞌ Topaꞌ ngukum okuꞌ!”

pairs.source: 72	And the second time the cock crew. And Peter called to mind the word that Jesus said unto him, Before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice. And when he thought thereon, he wept.
pairs.target:
72 Takal inoh geh babang siuak bitadu keꞌ duwoh sidoh-e. Petrus moꞌ
gos nyam-e natong sina Yesus deꞌ dioꞌ, deꞌ in-E, “Aluaꞌ diꞌ babang siuak
bitadu duwoh sidoh, muꞌu moꞌ taluh sidoh sukan nang odop muꞌ diꞌ muꞌ
piluh Okuꞌ.” Mokuaꞌ inoh kila Petrus moꞌ ngilobuꞌ yohmoꞌ siꞌian.

pairs.source: 1	And straightway in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried [him] away, and delivered [him] to Pilate.
pairs.target:
1 Suam-suam pagi ayua pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh duoh ayua
pimipin ulang Yahudi deꞌ bokon baya gulu-gulu agama Yahudi,
suaꞌ odop-e deꞌ mutiꞌ moꞌ sipakat. Yoh moꞌ odaꞌ nyaꞌa mokos Yesus, mokuaꞌ
inoh yoh moꞌ matak Yesus toban tuduꞌ gubelnul deꞌ propinsi Yudea deꞌ
adon Pilatus.

pairs.source: 2	And Pilate asked him, Art thou the King of the Jews? And he answering said unto him, Thou sayest [it].
pairs.target:
2 Gubelnul Pilatus moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ Yesus in-e, “Podo tok Muꞌu
laja ulang Yahudi?” Yesus moꞌ nyawot-e, “Muꞌu deꞌ sobot nang inoh.”

pairs.source: 3	And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing.
pairs.target:
3 Ayua pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh moꞌ nuduh nang Yoh bogoꞌ nai
oniꞌ deꞌ jaꞌat.

pairs.source: 4	And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answerest thou nothing? behold how many things they witness against thee.
pairs.target:
4 Mokuaꞌ inoh Pilatus sikian lagiꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus, “Ngojit, bogoꞌ
oniꞌ deꞌ nuduh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ tuduꞌ Muꞌu. Oni nai diꞌ muꞌ nyawot-e?”

pairs.source: 5	But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marvelled.
pairs.target: 5 Pak-e niꞌ doiꞌ geh sina-e deꞌ nyawot Yesus, yoh ngan Pilatus ilan-e.

pairs.source: 6	Now at [that] feast he released unto them one prisoner, whomsoever they desired.
pairs.target:
6 Moꞌ adat-e bilang Onu Ayuh Paskah, Pilatus pilopas niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa
deꞌ obuah jel nunaꞌ deꞌ pilih nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ.

pairs.source: 7	And there was [one] named Barabbas, [which lay] bound with them that had made insurrection with him, who had committed murder in the insurrection.
pairs.target:
7 Ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa deꞌ adon
Barabas. Iyoh obuah jel samah-samah duoh ayua nyaꞌa deꞌ lawan kerajaan
Romawi, dop-e ayua deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ ngabos nyaꞌa takal nyaꞌa nai liuak
daluag-e.

pairs.source: 8	And the multitude crying aloud began to desire [him to do] as he had ever done unto them.
pairs.target:
8 Nyaꞌa deꞌ bogoꞌ deꞌ tikuluk danoꞌ moꞌ mitiaꞌ tuduꞌ Pilatus odaꞌ
pilopas niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ jel, nunaꞌ adat-e.

pairs.source: 9	But Pilate answered them, saying, Will ye that I release unto you the King of the Jews?
pairs.target:
9 Pilatus moꞌ sikian tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ
bogoꞌ, “Podo ingan mitiaꞌ odaꞌ okuꞌ pilopas laja ulang Yahudi inoh saꞌan
ingan?”

pairs.source: 10	For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him for envy.
pairs.target:
10 Dop-e Pilatus moꞌ puꞌan pimipin-pimipin agama ulang Yahudi
deꞌ ayuh deꞌ munoꞌ nyelah Yesus tuduꞌ odop-e, dop-e yoh siniaꞌ tuduꞌ Yesus.

pairs.source: 11	But the chief priests moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.
pairs.target:
11 Pak-e ayua pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh moꞌ kibangoh kila nyaꞌa
deꞌ bogoꞌ odaꞌ pilopas Barabas saꞌan odop-e.

pairs.source: 12	And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do [unto him] whom ye call the King of the Jews?
pairs.target:
12 Pilatus moꞌ sikian lagiꞌ keꞌ
duwoh sidoh-e tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Moꞌ-e wat inoh, oni wat kuꞌ yaꞌ
duoh nyaꞌa deꞌ nang ingan laja ulang Yahudi inoh?”

pairs.source: 13	And they cried out again, Crucify him.
pairs.target:
13 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ sina daang-e nang bogan-e, “Masak Iyoh tun
salip!”

pairs.source: 14	Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil hath he done? And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.
pairs.target:
14 Pilatus sikian lagiꞌ tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Pak-e oni wat oniꞌ deꞌ
jaꞌat deꞌ nai-E?” Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ makin dolas nang bogan-e, “Masak Iyoh
tun salip!”

pairs.source: 15	And [so] Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged [him], to be crucified.
pairs.target:
15 Pilatus moꞌ pilopas Barabas, saꞌ diꞌ nyaꞌa tiyaꞌ nang liuak daluag-e.
Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ odaꞌ sidadu-sidadu-e pijolaꞌ Yesus duoh masak tun
salip.

pairs.source: 16	And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they call together the whole band.
pairs.target:
16 Sidadu-sidadu Roma moꞌ toban Yesus kaang boli topat gubelnul
militah. Yoh moꞌ mogan suaꞌ sidadu deꞌ bokon odaꞌ tikuluk danoꞌ.

pairs.source: 17	And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his [head],
pairs.target:
17 Ayua
sidadu deꞌ munoꞌ pasang jubah walna ungu tuduꞌ Yesus, duoh naꞌ mahkota
deꞌ nai-e pakai daꞌan koyuh deꞌ bilojaꞌ deꞌ bak Yesus.

pairs.source: 18	And began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!
pairs.target:
18 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ pulaꞌ-pulaꞌ mudi Yesus, daang-e in-e, “Idip laja ulang Yahudi!”

pairs.source: 19	And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing [their] knees worshipped him.
pairs.target:
19 Ayua
sidadu deꞌ munoꞌ makung bak Yesus pakai sikuud, ogiꞌ geh odop-e deꞌ
ngujaꞌ Yesus. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ guluꞌ bikunyug deꞌ sulung jowin Yesus
pulaꞌ-pulaꞌ pimodo tuduꞌ-E.

pairs.source: 20	And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him.
pairs.target:
20 Takal-e mokuaꞌ adoh-adoh wat-e duoh Yesus,
odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ bukaꞌ jubah-E deꞌ walna ungu inoh, yoh moꞌ paliꞌ
pasang bojuh odop Yesus. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ toban buu ngan-e yaꞌ
nyalip-E.

pairs.source: 21	And they compel one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming out of the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.
pairs.target:
21 Takal-e deꞌ lopot olan, sidadu deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ paksa niꞌ naꞌan nyaꞌa
deꞌ adon Simon odaꞌ golong salip Yesus. Simon itih tuang-e nog soꞌ kupuaꞌ
yaꞌ molot keꞌ kota. Iyoh nyaꞌa soꞌ Kirene, samaꞌ Aleksander duoh Rufus.

pairs.source: 22	And they bring him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull.
pairs.target:
22 Sidadu-sidadu deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ toban Yesus keꞌ topat deꞌ adon Golgota,
loti-e, “Topat Tikuluak.”

pairs.source: 23	And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received [it] not.
pairs.target:
23 Deꞌ danoꞌ, ogiꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ yaꞌ ngin piꞌin anggul
deꞌ sapul-e duoh potok koyuh deꞌ sobot-e nang Mur, deꞌ tapod odaꞌ nyaꞌa
diꞌ-e sikiya noman gonan-e monam, pak-e Yesus doliaꞌ-e nuak-e.

pairs.source: 24	And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them, what every man should take.
pairs.target:
24 Mokuaꞌ
inoh, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ mabak pasak deꞌ tongan poꞌon Yesus deꞌ tun
koyuh salip. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ bikutung pimakai Yesus pakai ngundi,
saꞌ-e puꞌan osi deꞌ soꞌon bojuh-E duoh osi deꞌ soꞌon jubah-E.

pairs.source: 25	And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.
pairs.target:
25 Nyaꞌa nyalip
Yesus inoh takal pukul piliꞌi pagi.

pairs.source: 26	And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
pairs.target:
26 Deꞌ tun salip-E ogiꞌ tulis deꞌ nopia
nyaꞌa, ngan-e sobot luban nyaꞌa nyalip Yesus deꞌ in-e, “Laja ulang Yahudi.”

pairs.source: 27	And with him they crucify two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.
pairs.target:
27 Ogiꞌ duwoh naꞌan pinyamun deꞌ obuah nyalip bibaya-baya duoh Yesus.
Niꞌ naꞌan nuaꞌ toꞌuh-E, niꞌ naꞌan nuaꞌ boit-E.

pairs.source: 28	And the scripture was fulfilled, which saith, And he was numbered with the transgressors.
pairs.target:
28 Oniꞌ deꞌ obuah Yesus inoh,
moꞌ bonal-bonal jadi samah duoh deꞌ moꞌ obuah nulis daang Kitab, deꞌ
in-e, “Nyaꞌa moꞌ nang Iyoh samah duoh ulang jaꞌat.”

pairs.source: 29	And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, thou that destroyest the temple, and buildest [it] in three days,
pairs.target:
29 Nyaꞌa deꞌ ngilusuꞌ topat inoh moꞌ adoh-adoh in-e duoh Yesus, daang-e
kuting bak-e, yohmoꞌ in-e, “No mey-e, patut Muꞌu nang odop Muꞌ yaꞌ
pilubuh Boli Topaꞌ, duoh yaꞌ paliꞌ kajuag baꞌuh daang taluh onu

pairs.source: 30	Save thyself, and come down from the cross.
pairs.target:
30 Suba
muun soꞌ tun salip, nyilamat odop Muꞌ!”

pairs.source: 31	Likewise also the chief priests mocking said among themselves with the scribes, He saved others; himself he cannot save.
pairs.target:
31 Watnoh geh pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi deꞌ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu
agama Yahudi suwaꞌ geh adoh-adoh in-e duoh Yesus. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
moꞌ sina tipan odop-e, “Nyaꞌa deꞌ bokon Iyoh nyilamat-e, pak-e Iyoh diꞌ-e
taan nyilamat Odop-E sadiꞌ-e!

pairs.source: 32	Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And they that were crucified with him reviled him.
pairs.target:
32 Simoꞌ Iyoh tok-tok Laja Pinyilamat ulang
Israel, tanah saꞌ-e muun soꞌ salip, saꞌ otoꞌ ningaꞌ-E, otoꞌ moꞌ bisayaꞌ.” Wat
inoh geh pinyamun deꞌ suwaꞌ obuah nyalip samah-samah duoh Yesus,
suwaꞌ geh adoh-adoh in-e duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: 33	And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.
pairs.target:
33 Takal uun onu pukul simoong duwoh, suaꞌ pulou moꞌ mopung, nog
pukul taluh ngumi.

pairs.source: 34	And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani? which is, being interpreted, My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?
pairs.target:
34 Takal pukul taluh ngumi inoh Yesus moꞌ nang
bogan-e, in-E, “Eloi, Eloi, lema sabakhtani?” Deꞌ loti-e, “Topaꞌ Kuꞌ, Topaꞌ
Kuꞌ, oni nai Ingan togan Okuꞌ?”

pairs.source: 35	And some of them that stood by, when they heard [it], said, Behold, he calleth Elias.
pairs.target:
35 Takal nyaꞌa danoꞌ ngojit Yesus nang bogan-e, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ
in-e, “Ngojit, Iyoh mogan adon nabi Elia!”

pairs.source: 36	And one ran and filled a spunge full of vinegar, and put [it] on a reed, and gave him to drink, saying, Let alone; let us see whether Elias will come to take him down.
pairs.target:
36 Ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan soꞌ odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ odi mit lumut deꞌ nyolap piꞌin, yoh moꞌ suad daang piꞌin anggul deꞌ
masuam, yoh moꞌ naꞌ deꞌ tubon tisuk koyuh ngan-e nyog deꞌ bobaꞌ Yesus,
daang-e sina, “Jaꞌ toꞌ kajon-e! Toꞌ ningaꞌ-e podo nabi Elia nog pimuun Iyoh
soꞌ tun salip.”

pairs.source: 37	And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the ghost.
pairs.target: 37 Yesus moꞌ nang bogan-e lagiꞌ, mokuaꞌ inoh asong-e moꞌ doiꞌ.

pairs.source: 38	And the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom.
pairs.target:
38 Takal inoh geh tabial daang Boli Topaꞌ moꞌ totak jadin duwoh amal
soꞌ somu nog douꞌ.

pairs.source: 39	And when the centurion, which stood over against him, saw that he so cried out, and gave up the ghost, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God.
pairs.target:
39 Takal piayuh sidadu Roma deꞌ mujuag deꞌ jowin salip Yesus moꞌ
ningaꞌ pingobos-E deꞌ wat inoh, yoh moꞌ in-e, “Tok bonal Nyaꞌa itih Onak
Topaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 40	There were also women looking on afar off: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;
pairs.target:
40 Ogiꞌ geh bala dayung deꞌ suwaꞌ ningaꞌ nyaꞌa nyalip Yesus soꞌ juuaꞌ.
Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ Maria Magdalena, Salome, baya Maria sinoꞌ Yakobus deꞌ
mudaꞌ duoh Yoses.

pairs.source: 41	(Who also, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered unto him;) and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.
pairs.target:
41 Dayung-dayung deꞌ mutiꞌ leh deꞌ bitunaꞌ duoh Yesus
takal-e deꞌ Galilea ngan-e tulung-E. Bogoꞌ geh dayung-dayung deꞌ bokon
deꞌ ogiꞌ danoꞌ deꞌ suwaꞌ nog keꞌ Yerusalem samah-samah duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: 42	And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,
43	Joseph of Arimathaea, an honourable counseller, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus.
pairs.target:
43 Takal onu moꞌ yaꞌ ngalom Yusuf soꞌ kupuaꞌ Arimatea nog.Yusuf
itih suwaꞌ jadin ayua soꞌ Pengadilan Agama Yahudi deꞌ pimodo nyaꞌa daꞌ-e.
Yoh itih tuang suwaꞌ geh kajon Topaꞌ yaꞌ nog militah jadin Laja. Onu inoh,  nyaꞌa moꞌ siap-siap yaꞌ nyamut Onu Sabat. Inoh leh ngan-e yoh maksa-e
jaꞌ-e odop-e odi ngaduap Pilatus, yohmoꞌ mitiaꞌ todang Yesus ngan-e yaꞌ
ngubul-e.

pairs.source: 44	And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling [unto him] the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.
pairs.target:
44 Pilatus moꞌ ilan-e takal-e ngojit Yesus moꞌ kobos. Iyoh moꞌ mogan
piayuh sidadu ngan-e yaꞌ sikian podo Yesus moꞌ bonal-bonal kobos.

pairs.source: 45	And when he knew [it] of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.
pairs.target:
45 Takal-e moꞌ ngojit soꞌ piayuh sidadu inoh nang Yesus moꞌ kobos, yoh
moꞌ odaꞌ Yusuf mit todang Yesus.

pairs.source: 46	And he bought fine linen, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a sepulchre which was hewn out of a rock, and rolled a stone unto the door of the sepulchre.
pairs.target:
46 Yusuf moꞌ milih kain mopuꞌ ngan-e
yaꞌ molut todang. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh moꞌ pimuun todang Yesus, yoh moꞌ
molut-e, yoh moꞌ naꞌ daang kubul gua. Mokuaꞌ inoh yoh pigulai batuh
deꞌ ayuh ngan-e kuab kubul gua inoh.

pairs.source: 47	And Mary Magdalene and Mary [the mother] of Joses beheld where he was laid.
pairs.target:
47 Takal inoh ogiꞌ Maria Magdalena
duoh Maria sinoꞌ Yoses suwaꞌ ningaꞌ topat nyaꞌa piguling todang Yesus.

pairs.source: 1	And when the sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the [mother] of James, and Salome, had bought sweet spices, that they might come and anoint him.
pairs.target:
1 Takal mokuaꞌ onu Sabat, Maria Magdalena, Salome, duoh Maria
sinoꞌ Yakobus odi milih inyuaꞌ wangi deꞌ yaꞌ toban-e keꞌ kubul gua,
ngan-e yaꞌ nginyuaꞌ todang Yesus.

pairs.source: 2	And very early in the morning the first [day] of the week, they came unto the sepulchre at the rising of the sun.
pairs.target:
2 Daang puꞌun minggu inoh, suam-suam
pagi takal boton onu moꞌ tumuꞌ, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ odi keꞌ kubul gua.

pairs.source: 3	And they said among themselves, Who shall roll us away the stone from the door of the sepulchre?
pairs.target:
3 Deꞌ lopot olan yoh moꞌ bisikian si odop-e, “Osi deꞌ taan gulai batuh deꞌ
kuab kubul gua saꞌan otoꞌ?”

pairs.source: 4	And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away: for it was very great.
pairs.target:
4 Pak-e takal-e moꞌ sinok kubul gua inoh, yoh
moꞌ ningaꞌ batuh deꞌ sukup ayuh inoh moꞌ tigulai.

pairs.source: 5	And entering into the sepulchre, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a long white garment; and they were affrighted.
pairs.target:
5 Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ
molot kaang kubul gua inoh, yoh moꞌ gogoh takal-e ningaꞌ ogiꞌ niꞌ naꞌan
onak mudaꞌ deꞌ pakai bojuh mopuꞌ guluꞌ nuaꞌ toꞌuh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ.

pairs.source: 6	And he saith unto them, Be not affrighted: Ye seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified: he is risen; he is not here: behold the place where they laid him.
pairs.target:
6 Onak mudaꞌ inoh moꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, “Maꞌ tolu! Okuꞌ
puꞌan nang ingan kalik Yesus ulang Nazaret deꞌ moꞌ obuah nyalib inoh. Iyoh
moꞌ doiꞌ datiꞌ! Iyoh moꞌ paliꞌ idip! Ningaꞌ itih topat nyaꞌa posan todang-E.

pairs.source: 7	But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goeth before you into Galilee: there shall ye see him, as he said unto you.
pairs.target:
7 Buu paliꞌ adin, tanon gah itih tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E baya Petrus. In
nyeꞌ tanon tuduꞌ-e, ‘Yesus dioꞌ odi kajon ingan deꞌ Galilea. Danih leh ingan
yaꞌ bitapod duoh Iyoh kodaꞌ deꞌ moꞌ dioꞌ-e tanon-E.’ ”

pairs.source: 8	And they went out quickly, and fled from the sepulchre; for they trembled and were amazed: neither said they any thing to any [man]; for they were afraid.
pairs.target:
8 Daang kila deꞌ gogoh duoh sukup tolu-e odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ moꞌ bikoduh
luah togan kubul gua inoh. Odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ diꞌ-e tanon oni-oni-e tuduꞌ
suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tapod-e deꞌ olan dop-e yoh tolu.

pairs.source: 9	Now when [Jesus] was risen early the first [day] of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.
pairs.target:
9 Mokuaꞌ Yesus moꞌ paliꞌ idip, suam-suam pagi deꞌ puꞌun minggu inoh,
Iyoh moꞌ bitanga odop-E, sibungas-e tuduꞌ Maria Magdalena. Iyoh itih leh   
deꞌ ogiꞌ onu Yesus kasig juꞌ muat munua soꞌ gonan-e.

pairs.source: 10	[And] she went and told them that had been with him, as they mourned and wept.
pairs.target:
10 Mokuaꞌ inoh Maria
Magdalena moꞌ odi tanon tuduꞌ pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ Yesus deꞌ aluaꞌ siꞌian,
dop-e yoh aluaꞌ susah otin-e.

pairs.source: 11	And they, when they had heard that he was alive, and had been seen of her, believed not.
pairs.target:
11 Pak-e takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ ngojit soꞌ
Maria Magdalena nang yoh kilin Yesus paliꞌ mokat idip, odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ
diꞌ-e bisayaꞌ.

pairs.source: 12	After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked, and went into the country.
pairs.target:
12 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ bitanga Odop-E tuduꞌ duwoh naꞌan pinunaꞌ-E,
pak-e okon mun jowin-E, takal odop-e deꞌ duwoh daang pimonu-e soꞌ
Yerusalem odi keꞌ kupuaꞌ deꞌ bokon.

pairs.source: 13	And they went and told [it] unto the residue: neither believed they them.
pairs.target:
13 Odop-e deꞌ duwoh moꞌ paliꞌ tuduꞌ
dingan-dingan-e yohmoꞌ tanon suaꞌ oniꞌ deꞌ kilin-e. Pak-e ayua dingan-e
tuang idoh geh diꞌ-e bisayaꞌ.

pairs.source: 14	Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at meat, and upbraided them with their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they believed not them which had seen him after he was risen.
pairs.target:
14 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus sadiꞌ-e lasuꞌ bitapod duoh simoong niꞌ naꞌan
pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E takal odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ aluaꞌ julah-e man. Yesus moꞌ
ngalah odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, dop-e suaꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ liꞌiang bak-e duoh
doliaꞌ-e bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ tanon nang odop-e moꞌ ningaꞌ Yesus takal-e
paliꞌ idip.

pairs.source: 15	And he said unto them, Go ye into all the world, and preach the gospel to every creature.
pairs.target:
15 Mokuaꞌ inoh Yesus moꞌ sina tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, in-E, “Kodak
leh nog tubon longit nyeꞌ moꞌ magah Gah deꞌ Paguh soꞌ Topaꞌ tuduꞌ suaꞌ
nyaꞌa.

pairs.source: 16	He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved; but he that believeth not shall be damned.
pairs.target:
16 Nyaꞌa deꞌ bisayaꞌ duoh obuah baptis iyoh yaꞌ silamat. Pak-e nyaꞌa
deꞌ diꞌ-e bisayaꞌ yaꞌ obuah ngukum.

pairs.source: 17	And these signs shall follow them that believe; In my name shall they cast out devils; they shall speak with new tongues;
pairs.target:
17 Suaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ bisayaꞌ tuduꞌ Okuꞌ,
Okuꞌ ngin kuasa tuduꞌ-e odaꞌ nai oniꞌ deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa. Ingan tapod kasig
muat munua daang adon Okuꞌ, ponai nang sina deꞌ aluaꞌ doiꞌ sidoh ingan
bilajal-e.

pairs.source: 18	They shall take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them; they shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.
pairs.target:
18 Moꞌ nyam ingan kagian dipoh duoh nuak lasun doiꞌ geh oni-oni
wat ingan odaꞌ-e. Moꞌ nyam ingan tomaꞌ nyaꞌa deꞌ monam, iyoh tapod
mokuaꞌ.”

pairs.source: 19	So then after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven, and sat on the right hand of God.
pairs.target:
19 Takal-e mokuaꞌ sina duoh odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ, Topaꞌ Yesus moꞌ tipa'ad
keꞌ siluga. Danih Iyoh moꞌ militah samah-samah duoh Topaꞌ Samaꞌ deꞌ
siluga.

pairs.source: 20	And they went forth, and preached every where, the Lord working with [them], and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.
pairs.target:
20 Pinunaꞌ-pinunaꞌ-E moꞌ odi niꞌ pulou-pulou tanon Gah deꞌ Paguh soꞌ
Topaꞌ. Odop Topaꞌ tuang suwaꞌ geh kiloja samah-samah duoh odop-e deꞌ
munoꞌ. Iyoh ngin-e geh kuasa tuduꞌ odop-e deꞌ munoꞌ saꞌ-e nai bogoꞌ oniꞌ
deꞌ ilan nyaꞌa, saꞌ-e jadin tanda nang gah deꞌ tanon-e inoh bonal-bonal soꞌ
Topaꞌ.
